title: two and five pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and
butter.
Add
one egg at a time, until all beaten well.
Add flour; beat well.
Add vanilla.
Bake in tube pan in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt dipping chocolate according to package directions. Combine margarine, peanut butter and sugar.
Shape peanut butter candy mixture into balls.
Chill thoroughly.
Dip balls in chocolate and let set on waxed paper until not sticky.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, combine flour, cornmeal, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat together the egg, milk and margarine.
Add egg mixture and sour cream to flour mixture.
Stir just until blended.
Pour mixture into an 8-inch square baking pan, coated with vegetable cooking spray.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 9 servings (each serving contains 222 calories).

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Add flour, baking powder, soda, salt, pumpkin spice and nuts and raisins (optional). Grease 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter; stir in flour, salt and pepper.
Bring just to boil, then cook until smooth.
Stir in vegetables.
Boil 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add milk.
Heat on simmer. Serve.

title: peanut butter cake
directions: Cream butter and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugar, beating well at medium speed.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Combine flour, powder and salt.
Add to above, alternating with milk.
Begin and end with flour.
Mix after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and frost with your favorite chocolate frosting.

title: cheesy easy tuna casserole
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Add soup, tuna and milk.
Season to taste.
Top with bread crumbs and microwave for 5 minutes.
(Add peas, if desired.)
Serves 4.

title: doughnuts
directions: Combine butter, water and salt in medium saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Remove from heat.
Add flour; beat with wooden spoon. Return to heat; beat for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and let cool. Beat in 1 egg at a time.
Add vanilla; continue beating until mixture is smooth.
Press mixture through fluted tip cookie press with 1/2-inch wide opening.
Cut into 2-inch strips with wet scissors.
Drop into 350° fat.
Fry several at a time for 2 minutes on each side.
Drain well.
Roll in cinnamon mixture or sugar mixture.
Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Place chicken in bottom of baking dish.
Combine sour cream and cream of chicken soup; pour over chicken.
Sprinkle Ritz crackers over soup mixture.
Pour melted butter over crackers. Sprinkle poppy seed over crackers.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.
May be served over noodles or rice.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice or dice apples into an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Stir rest of ingredients until it crumbles.
Sprinkle over apples.
Dot with cinnamon.
Pour 1/4 to 1/2 cup butter over all.
Bake at 350° until apples are done.

title: french fried cauliflower
directions: Combine flour and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine egg, milk and oil in a small mixing bowl.
Add egg mixture to flour mixture, stirring just until moistened.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff; add the rest of ingredients.
Put in greased pie pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 370°.

title: chicken rice supreme
directions: Grease casserole dish well.
Spread rice in dish and add water.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Cover with onion soup, mushroom soup, and parsley.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350 degrees for 2 hours.

title: zesty pot roast
directions: Combine all ingredients except roast.
Pour mixture over meat and marinate covered in refrigerator for 24 hours or overnight, turning occasionally.
Drain meat.
Reserve liquid.
Brown in shortening in Dutch oven or heavy kettle.
Add marinade and simmer tightly covered for 3 hours or until meat is tender.
A little water may be added if gravy becomes too thick.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes the last 40 to 45 minutes of cooking if desired. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: chart house mud pie
directions: Crush wafers and add butter.
Mix well and press into 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with soft coffee ice cream.
Put into freezer until ice cream is firm.
Top with cold fudge sauce (place in freezer first to make spreading easier).
Store pie in freezer approximately 10 hours.

title: tex-mex spaghetti(4 servings)
directions: Cook ground beef, onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add tomatoes with juice, tomato sauce, vinegar, chili powder, cumin and cinnamon.
Simmer for 20 minutes.
While this is simmering, cook spaghetti until done.
Drain and serve with sauce and grated cheese sprinkled on top.
Serve with salad and garlic bread.

title: crab delights fettuccine
directions: I double the sauce recipe; makes it delicious.

title: sausage brunch dish
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart shallow baking dish.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over mixture and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.
Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over top of casserole.
Return to oven and cook 5 to 10 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Makes 6 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, salt and vinegar.
Add onion juice and stir in thoroughly.
Add oil slowly and continue to beat until thick.
Add poppy seed and beat a few minutes.
Store in a cool place or refrigerate.
Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: baking powder biscuits
directions: Measure flour and sift all the dry ingredients together.
Cut in butter until the mixture resembles coarse meal.
Form a wet dough with the milk.
Knead 8 or 10 times.
With a floured hand, pat dough out to a 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out biscuits with a floured biscuit cutter.
Pat out scraps and cut again until all dough is used and refrigerate biscuits for 1 hour.
Preheat oven to 450°.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden.

title: our mom's homemade bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Cream sugar and Crisco together.
Add to yeast and water.
Mix salt and flour together.
Add flour mixture and water mixture alternately until dough is not sticky.
Put in large bowl and cover with towel; let rise until double in size, then punch down and knead. Then form dough into small loaves or buns.
Place in greased pans. Let rise again until doubled.
When bread has risen, bake until brown, 25 to 30 minutes.
Brush with butter.
Remove from pans while hot.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and water together in heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat to 250° on candy thermometer.
Add butter, vanilla and soda and stir briskly.
Pour over popped corn. Squeeze together while warm into balls.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: In mixing bowl, blend softened butter with warm sweet potatoes.
Add remaining filling ingredients and beat in mixer at low speed until mixture is smooth.
Pour into pie shell and bake in preheated 375° oven for 50 minutes or until a knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: chewy chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, stir cocoa and margarine until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Let dough stand 10 minutes; drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes or until set (do not overbake).
Cook 5 minutes; remove from baking sheets. Cool completely.
Store tightly covered.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: red rice with sausage
directions: Saute 1st three ingredients.
Add tomato paste and water; bring to a boil.
Add rice and stir well.
Add sausage.
Stir and bring to a slow boil.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.
Halfway through cooking time, stir and add water, if necessary.

title: pasta with double tomato sauce
directions: Start cooking the pasta.
In a 9-inch nonstick skillet, heat oil.
Add onion and garlic; cook over medium heat until softened, about 2 minutes.
Stir in plum tomatoes and sundried tomatoes. Reduce heat to low; gradually stir in milk.
Stir in parsley. Cook, stirring occasionally, for 5 minutes.
Add pasta to tomato mixture; stir to combine.

title: cabbage and peas(indian style)
directions: Cut cabbage very fine.
Heat small amount of oil in frying pan.
Add turmeric, cabbage and peas.
Add red pepper and salt. Mix.
Cover.
Cook until peas are tender.

title: sausage balls
directions: Combine all ingredients by hand; form into small balls.
Bake at 400° on cookie sheet until golden brown.

title: chilled chocolate tortoni(serves 12)
directions: Line 12 muffin cups with paper liners.
In 3-quart saucepan, stir chocolate and syrup over low heat just until chocolate melts, then remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 cup heavy cream until blended. Refrigerate 15 minutes or until cool.
Beat remaining cream until soft peaks; gently stir into chocolate mixture.
Stir in cookies and nuts.
Spoon into muffin cups.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Let stand a few minutes before serving.
Store in covered dish in freezer up to 1 month.

title: fudge cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add flour and liquids. Bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 11 1/2-inch pan.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat. Add onion and saute until tender. Stir in tomato paste, water and garlic. Simmer for 20 minutes, then add the beans and chili seasoning.
Simmer for 15 minutes more. Top with grated cheese when served.

title: campfire potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes and onions on large piece of foil. Dot with butter. Combine cheese, parsley, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Sprinkle over potatoes; fold foil and seal. Grill 30 to 40 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Reserve 1 tablespoon of seasoning; add the rest to the hamburger.
Select extra large bowl to toss salad, allowing enough room to toss salad at serving time.
Layer salad ingredients in bowl, starting with lettuce and ending with cheese.
Cover; refrigerate until serving time.
Toss salad with dressing and taco chips just before serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: In iron skillet brown bacon slices until crisp.
Add onions and brown.
Add uncooked rice and brown.
To this add tomatoes, salt, chili powder and water; cook over medium fire until boiling, then simmer approximately 30 minutes.

title: pork chops o'brien
directions: Brown pork chops. Combine soup, milk and sour cream.
Season with salt, pepper and seasoning salt. Stir in potatoes, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 of the onions.
Pour potato mixture in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put pork chops over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Top with cheese and onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: apple crisp
directions: Combine oats, flour, sugars, butter, cinnamon and nutmeg. Blend together until crumbly.
Place apple slices in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with the oat mixture.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cold.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: double toffee delight cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients in large mixer bowl and beat 2 minutes.
Pour 1/3 batter in greased 13 x 9-inch pan; sprinkle with 1/3 brown sugar mixture.
Pour remaining batter over this and top with remaining brown sugar mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Can be layered in 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan and baked 20 to 25 minutes for bar cookies.
Delicious served warm as coffee cake.

title: yum yum bars
directions: Melt until smooth in double boiler or microwave.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork in hot fat.
Add 1/2 cup water.
Cover and simmer (do not boil) until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add pineapple syrup, vinegar, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork; cook and stir until gravy thickens.
Add pineapple, green pepper, onion and bean sprouts.
Cook 3 minutes or longer.
Serve over rice or chow mein noodles.

title: white bread
directions: Mix yeast and sugar.
Add warm water.
Add flour and salt, working as much flour in as needed to make a smooth dough.
Put in a large greased bowl and let rise 20 minutes.
Punch down and let rise again until doubled.
Make into loaves and let rise again. Bake in a 375° oven until done.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Put in pot with cream of chicken soup, butter and broth.
Bring to a boil.
Pour into a 8 x 9-inch pan and set aside.

title: hardee's biscuits
directions: Don't let touch in pan.
Sift together all dry ingredients. Dough will be soft; use flour on hands, rolling pin and tabletop. Lightly roll dough and cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 425° until done.
Makes 12 to 14.

title: chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine wafers, almonds (if desired), butter and 1/3 cup sugar.
Press mixture onto bottom and 2 inches up sides of a buttered spring-form pan.

title: diabetic salad
directions: Mix all together in medium bowl.
Chill well before serving.

title: chicken
directions: In frypan brown chicken both sides.
Add soup, mushrooms and wine.
Cover and cook until chicken is done.
Serve with noodles.

title: preachers casserole
directions: *Or use 1 lb. hamburger.

title: meatballs
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for 5 minutes.
Combine all ingredients except soup, and shape into small balls.
Place in a casserole bowl and bake until brown (about 30 minutes).

title: secret kiss cookies
directions: In large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add flour and nuts; beat on low speed of mixer until well blended.
Cover, refrigerate 1 to 2 hours or until firm enough to handle.
Remove wrappers from candy.
Heat oven to 375°.
Use 1 tablespoon dough for each cookie, shape dough around candy; roll to make ball.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until cookies are set but not brown.
Cool slightly; remove from cookie sheet to wire rack.
While still warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool completely.
Store in tightly covered container.
Roll again in powdered sugar just before serving.
Yields 3 dozen cookies.

title: diane's pot roast
directions: Rub meat with cut side of garlic.
Mix flour, basil and pepper; coat meat with flour mixture.
Heat oil in Dutch oven. Brown meat in oil over medium heat.
Add tomatoes, onion, water and beef bouillon.
Cover and simmer until meat is almost tender, 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: pineapple-carrot mold
directions: Drain pineapple and add enough water to syrup to make 1 1/2 cups.
Heat; add to Jell-O.
Stir in sugar, salt and lemon juice. Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in pineapple and grated carrot.
Whip cream and fold into Jell-O mixture.
Pour into 8-inch ring mold.
Best to make a day ahead to be sure it is thoroughly set.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown roast.
Put in crock-pot with 1 quart water and let simmer all day.

title: mary anne's cheese potato soup(empire magazine)
directions: Melt butter in a large kettle over moderate heat.
Add onions; saute over moderate heat until onions are soft, stirring frequently.
Add potatoes, carrots, celery and up to 12 cups of water.
(The amount of water will vary, depending on desired consistency of soup and the type of bread that is later crumbled into it for thickening purposes.
Start soup with a smaller amount of water, then taste it frequently as it cooks, adding more water, if desired.)
Add pepper, salt, parsley, dill and crumbled bread. Bring to a boil, reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 1 hour. Stir cheese into soup during last few minutes of cooking time.

title: jello pie
directions: Place applesauce in a pan and bring to a boil.
Add sugar and jello.
Cool
until thickened.
Whip evaporated milk and lemon juice until peaks form or may use Cool Whip.
Add to applesauce and gelatin mixture.
Pour into a ready baked crust or a graham cracker crust.
Chill.

title: summer corn salad
directions: Combine ingredients except bacon. Chill. Crumble bacon on top before serving.

title: divinity puffs
directions: Cook sugar, Karo and water to thin syrup stage.
Slowly pour 1/3 of syrup over egg whites, beating while pouring.
Cook syrup to thread stage (232°).
Add half of syrup to egg mixture.
Cook remaining syrup to firm ball stage (248°); add to egg mixture. Add vanilla.
Beat until mixture holds shape when dropped from a spoon.
Add cherries or pecans.

title: boiled custard
directions: Mix flour well with sugar to prevent lumping.
Scald milk in double boiler.
Beat eggs well and add to flour and sugar.
Beat this into scalded milk.
Stir until thickened.
Remove from heat and add flavoring, keep stirring.
Pour into containers and chill before serving.

title: garbage(a good snack anytime)
directions: Melt margarine in pan and add the Worcestershire sauce, bacon fat, celery salt, garlic salt, sesame seed and Tabasco sauce.
Mix together; pour over dry mixture.
Mix well in large roaster and bake at 200° for 3 to 4 hours.
Stir every 1/2 hour.
Freezes well.

title: italian style meat loaf
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients and mix well.
Place in 4 1/2-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour; drain.
Makes 6 servings.

title: ten layer chocolate cake
directions: Beat eggs and shortening together.
Add sugar, alternately adding flour and milk.
Add vanilla.
Grease as many cake pans as you have.
Place about 2 big dipping spoonfuls of batter in each pan and cook at 350° for about 10 minutes or until done.
Layer will be thin.
Make icing ahead and stack and ice as the layers come from the oven.
Re-grease pans each time you use.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown sausage; drain well.
Add undrained tomatoes, tomato paste, water, basil and garlic.
Simmer, covered, 15 to 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cook noodles; drain.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese, parsley, 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.

title: harvest festival dish
directions: Thickly slice apples and sweet potatoes.
Place one layer in casserole, cover with pumpkin.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over this layer.
Continue layering until all is done.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until apples are done.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Cook cornbread.
Cool and crumble in bottom of large glass bowl.
Place drained beans on top of bread.
Next, layer the following ingredients:
diced green peppers, tomato, green onion and Mexican whole kernel corn.
Combine together Ranch dressing, sour cream and mayonnaise.
Spread on top.
Toss just before serving.

title: maraschino cherry cookies
directions: Place shortening, vanilla, sugar, brown sugar and egg in mixing bowl.
Beat thoroughly.
Add nuts and cherries; mix.
Sift together flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Divide into 2 portions.
Add 1/2 to first mixture; mix well.
Add remaining half; beat thoroughly.
Knead dough with hands until smooth.
Pack very firmly and shape into 2 bars (2 x 2-inch square).
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill in refrigerator until firm. Cut in 1/8-inch slices; place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Makes 60 cookies.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: Prepare brownie mix; bake as directed on package for cake-type brownies.
Immediately sprinkle marshmallows over brownies. Continue baking until marshmallows begin to melt.
Melt chips with milk over low heat, stirring until smooth.
Drizzle over marshmallows; sprinkle with nuts.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: country style chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter; add flour and allow to bubble 1 minute.
Add broth; bring to boil and simmer for few minutes.
Add lemon juice and cream.
Drain vegetables and add to sauce; add seasonings and chicken.
Pour into deep 2-quart casserole.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: pure grape jelly
directions: Ingredients apply to each batch.

title: strawberry pie
directions: In saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Mash 1 cup strawberries and add water to make 2 cups.
Stir with sugar mixture and cook to boil 2 minutes.
Add butter, jello and lemon juice.
Chill until partially set.
Pour mixture over rest of strawberries that you have arrange in a baked pie shell.

title: fruit cake
directions: Combine mincemeat, nuts and fruit.
Sift together the flour, sugar and salt; add to fruit mixture.
Dissolve soda in boiling water and stir into the batter.
Mix thoroughly.
Bake in a slow oven (275°) for about 2 1/2 hours.
Two loaves of bread will be made with this recipe.

title: slow-cook chicken
directions: *Add more of cans as needed.

title: fresh cucumber slices
directions: Place cucumbers in dish.
Combine other ingredients and stir until sugar dissolves.
Pour over cucumbers.
Chill.
Can layer cucumbers and onion slices.

title: ice cream cake
directions: Mix peanut butter, Karo syrup, and Rice Krispies and pat into a 9 x 13-inch size dish.
Let ice cream stand until soft and put over rice crispy crust.
Freeze and cut into bars or squares.

title: rhubarb crisp
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and put in bottom of buttered baking dish.
Mix flour, sugars, oatmeal and margarine until crumbly and spread on top of rhubarb mixture.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Melt margarine and sugar; bring to a boil.
Add cinnamon. Gradually add 7-Up, stirring constantly.
Roll biscuits; add chopped apples.
Bring edges up and twist.
Place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Pour mixture over dumplings.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: marinade for meat
directions: Mix all together.
Pour over meat to be barbecued.
Marinate in refrigerator 12 hours.
Remove from sauce and barbecue.

title: hobo dinner
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Layer the hamburger in a greased casserole.
Next, layer the potatoes, then the carrots.
Pour cream of mushroom soup (do not add water) over the layers of meat and vegetables.
Season to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: pumpkin whoopie pies
directions: Beat egg yolks, brown sugar and vegetable oil together until smooth.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Drop by spoonful on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Cool.
Spread with filling.

title: stuffed mushrooms(yield: 16 mushrooms)
directions: Clean mushrooms with a damp paper towel.
Remove and chop stems fine.
You should have about 1/2 cup.
Put butter, chopped mushrooms, onion and pepper in a medium size bowl.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes, stirring once halfway through cooking time, until vegetables are crisp-tender. Stir in bread crumbs and seasoning.
Spoon into mushroom caps, mounding slightly.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Place ground meat in large bowl.
Add bread crumbs, onion, garlic powder, parsley, egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well with hands. Make meatballs.
Cook on top of stove or in the oven.
Drain. Spread sauce over all.
Simmer on top of stove or in oven for 45 minutes.

title: sugar-free cranapple snow
directions: Put cranberries and apples in blender with jello.
Blend well until berries are very fine.
Pour in bowl and add finely chopped celery (adds texture).
Do not blend celery with berries and apples.
Good with fowl.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: In greased casserole, stir together rice, onion, soup and water.
Put seasoned chicken on top of rice.
Spoon cream of chicken soup on top.
Bake, covered, 1 hour and 15 minutes, then 15 minutes, uncovered, at 350°.

title: bacon and potato soup
directions: In bacon fat, saute onion 2 to 3 minutes.
Drain.
In a pot with sauteed onion, add potatoes and water; bring to a boil. Cover and simmer for about 15 minutes, or until potatoes are tender.
Stir in soup, sour cream and crumbled bacon.
Add milk, salt, pepper and parsley.
Heat to serving temperature.
Do not boil.

title: chicken surprise
directions: Place chicken breasts in slow cooker on medium temperature. Combine all ingredients, except noodles or rice.
Simmer for 4 hours.
Eat over noodles or rice.

title: mushroom casserole
directions: Clean mushrooms with damp paper towels.
Remove stems and reserve for other uses.
Slice caps and set aside.
Cream the butter, flour, salt, mustard, nutmeg and pepper at medium speed on electric mixer.
Add sour cream, parsley and onion; stir well. Place half of mushroom slices in a greased 2-quart baking dish. Top with half of the sour cream mix, spreading evenly.
Repeat layers.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until casserole is thoroughly heated.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: world's fastest fudge
directions: Mix first two ingredients into a microwave bowl.
Time for 2 minutes.
Immediately stir ingredients; add walnuts and pour into a square buttered Pyrex dish.
Cool completely and cut into squares.
Delicious.

title: pudding dessert
directions: Cut together flour and oleo; add pecans.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan and press flat to bottom.
Bake about 30 minutes at 350° and cool.
Cream together cream cheese and powdered sugar; add 1/2 bowl of Cool Whip.
Spread this mixture on baked crust.
Beat together pudding with milk on low speed for 2 minutes.
Spread on top of 1st mixture.
Chill for 5 minutes, then add the rest of bowl of Cool Whip on top and chill.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 5-inch loaf pan (or larger).
In mixing bowl assemble all ingredients, form into loaf in pan and bake for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Sprinkle nuts and coconut in bottom of well-greased 10 x 14-inch pan.
Mix cake according to directions on box.
Pour over nuts and coconut.
Mix butter, cheese and powdered sugar together (mixture will be very thick).
Drop by teaspoon over top of cake. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bacon-cheese muffins
directions: In large skillet, cook bacon over medium-high heat until crisp.
Drain, reserving drippings.
If necessary, add oil to make 1/3 cup.
In small bowl, combine dripping mixture, egg and milk; set aside.
Crumble bacon; set aside.
In large bowl combine flour, sugar and baking powder.
Make well in center.
Add egg mixture all at once; stir until moistened.
(Batter should be lumpy.)
Fold in bacon, cheese and cereal.
Spoon into greased muffin cups, fill about 3/4 full.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Remove from pan.
Cool on wire rack.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: corn cakes
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients well. Heat a large, heavy skillet over medium-high heat. Add the oil. When hot, drop by heaping tablespoons and cook until bottoms are golden, about 1 minute. Turn cakes over and brown the other side. Repeat using all the batter. Makes 4 servings.

title: potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water; set aside.
In saucepan, combine milk, shortening and potatoes.
Cook and stir over low heat just until shortening is melted.
Remove from heat and place in a large bowl with sugar, salt, 2 cups of the flour and yeast mixture.
Add eggs, mixing well.
Cover loosely and allow to stand for 2 hours (the dough will be like a sponge).
Stir in enough of remaining flour to make soft dough.
Turn dough out onto floured surface and knead until smooth and elastic, about 6 minutes.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease top.
Cover and let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 hour.

title: jiffy dessert
directions: Bake Jiffy cake mix in 9 x 12-inch loaf pan as directed on package.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese with milk until smooth.
Then add pudding (mix as you would to make pudding).
Pour over cooled cake.
Let set up.
Then put on a layer of fruit (strawberries or blueberries or whatever).
Then cover with Cool Whip. Refrigerate.

title: instant cappuccino
directions: Mix up and store in container.
Use 1 heaping tablespoonful per cup.
Add boiling water and stir.
If desired, add sugar to taste.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam. Spread coconut in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle pecan pieces over coconut.
Pour cake batter over this.
Mix powdered sugar, butter and cream cheese together and plop tablespoon of mixture on cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Place foil under cake as it may boil over.

title: snowball cake
directions: Wet Jell-O with 2 tablespoons cold water, after dissolved, pour in 1 cup boiling water, sugar and strawberries.
Refrigerate until partially congealed.
Mix 2 packages Dream Whip as per instructions.
Fold into partially congealed Jell-O mixture.
Tear or cut angel food cake into bite size pieces.
Butter tube pan. Make layers of cake pieces and Jell-O mixture, beginning with cake and ending with same.
Press into pan firmly.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan and ice with remaining 2 packages Dream Whip.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook together in salted water the squash and onions for 5 minutes or until partly tender.
Drain.

title: icicle pickles
directions: 1st Step:
Cover with brine made of 1 gallon of boiling water and salt.
Let stand 1 week.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt margarine and mix with crumbs and press into 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix pudding and milk and pour over graham cracker crumbs.
Next, cut up bananas and layer over pudding.
Cover that with pineapple chunks and frost with Cool Whip.
Decorate with pecans and cherries.
Chill and serve.

title: easy yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add margarine and sugar, then add flour until all is mixed well.
Grease muffin pan and fill 1/2 full.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Keep dough refrigerated when not using.

title: tex-mex beans and rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain and chop tomatoes.
Reserve juice; add enough water to juice to equal 2 1/2 cups liquid. Combine tomatoes, liquid and all ingredients, except pepper and cheese, in a 13 x 9-inch bake dish.
Mix well.
Cover tightly with foil; bake for 45 minutes or until most of liquid is absorbed.
Uncover and stir.
Sprinkle with green pepper and cheese.
Return to oven to melt cheese.

title: salmon souffle
directions: Mix butter, flour and milk over low heat on stove (makes a white sauce).
Slowly add small amount of white sauce to egg yolks and stir into remaining sauce.
Add salt, nutmeg, pepper and salmon.
Fold in egg whites.
Bake in a greased casserole dish at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetables or chips and mix well.
Serve chilled with vegetables or chips.
Cut vegetables in small bite size pieces.

title: hot lemony coffee
directions: Pour hot coffee into saucepan.
Stir in sugar and simmer until dissolved.
Add orange and lemon juice.
Stir in rind.
Pour coffee mixture into 4 cups.
Top with whipped cream and garnish with orange rind.

title: banana croquettes
directions: Beat egg.
Add sugar, stirring until smooth.
Add vinegar. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens. Let cool.
Grind nuts moderately fine.
Peel bananas and cut into thirds.
Dip each slice in the peanuts.

title: fantastic fudge
directions: Grease pan with margarine or butter; heat chocolate chips over low heat, stirring until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir sweetened condensed milk into chocolate, along with vanilla and salt.
Pour fudge into pan.
Spread it evenly in pan with back of spoon.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Cut it into 1-inch pieces.

title: low-fat spinach lasagne
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Saute onion and garlic in a small amount of water.
Add tomatoes and liquid from one can of the tomatoes, tomato sauce, mushrooms (drained), spices and zucchini.
Simmer slowly for 20 minutes.
Drain spinach between paper towels.
Place spinach and cottage cheese in a bowl and mix well.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking dish with Pam, then layer sauce, noodles and cottage cheese and spinach mixtures.
Repeat until all are used up, ending with cottage cheese mixture and sauce on top.

title: blueberry-orange-pecan quick bread
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Lightly grease and flour loaf pan.
Sift together the first 6 ingredients and mix in the pecans.
In a separate bowl, beat eggs with milk, orange juice and zest.	Blend in the melted butter.
Pour liquids into the dry ingredients; stir until barely moistened.
Gently fold in blueberries.
Bake for 1 hour or until a pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in 12 inch nonstick oven proof skillet over low heat.
Remove from heat; stir in sugar. Arrange pineapple slices over sugar mixture.
Place cherry half, round side down, in center of each slice; sprinkle with nuts.
Add enough water to saved pineapple juice to measure 1 1/3 cups; pour into large mixing bowl.
Add cake mix, eggs and oil; beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Pour over fruit in skillet.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Remove from oven and cool for about 5 minutes. Carefully loosen edge of cake and invert into serving plate.
Cool and decorate with topping around edge of cake.
Yields 12 servings.

title: sunday night supper soup
directions: Make small balls (walnut size) from meat, egg, water, crumbs, salt and 1 tablespoon parsley.
Brown balls in the butter.

Drain. In the same Dutch oven or kettle, combine 2 cups water, beef broth, tomatoes (break up before adding), soup mix, carrots, celery and tops, basil, oregano, pepper and the 1/4 cup fresh or dried parsley.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer covered 20 minutes or more.
Add the meat balls and simmer about 20 minutes more.
I add frozen peas when I add the meat balls.
Very tasty soup and a meal in itself with French bread.

title: joe's heath bar cake
directions: Beat together until stiff the first 6 ingredients.
Add sugar very gradually, continue to beat until all sugar is added.
Pour into greased cake pan.
Do not spread to edge of pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 300°.
Ice with icing recipe.
Refrigerate for 12 hours before serving.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed and add 1/2 can of Eagle Brand milk and 1 stick of melted butter.
Divide the batter in half. Pour 1/2 of batter into pan and bake 20 minutes at 325°.

title: apple stuff
directions: Butter well a dish.
Put in a cup of apples.
Sprinkle 1 cup of granulated sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon over apples.
Mix together the butter, brown sugar, 1 teaspoon of cinnamon and flour.
Sprinkle this over apples and sugar and bake about 30 minutes in moderate (400°) oven.
Serve plain or with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar, brown sugar, eggs and vanilla. Stir in the flour, soda, salt, chopped nuts and chocolate chips. Drop and bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Layer as you would a banana pudding.
Chill.

title: custard ice cream
directions: Bring sweet milk to boil.
Pour eggs, sugar and salt slowly in boiling milk.
Cook until curdles in double boiler.
Add flavorings.
Cook and freeze.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, pepper and 1/2 can tomato sauce.
Form into loaf and put in shallow 7 x 10-inch pan.

title: bean salad
directions: Drain and mix vegetables together in a large bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil.
Pour over the bean mixture.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix together and add salt and pepper. Place in a greased casserole dish. Crumble 1 stack of Ritz crackers and sprinkle over top. Melt 1 stick of margarine and drizzle over. Cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: mexican dip with nachos
directions: Put in large crock-pot. Serve with nachos.

title: spit-barbecued ribs
directions: Place meat in plastic bag or shallow glass dish.
Mix soy sauce, sherry, 2 tablespoons honey and garlic.
Pour over meat. Fasten bag or cover dish securely.
Refrigerate 8 hours, turning meat occasionally.
Remove meat from marinade; reserve marinade. Lace ribs on spit rod; secure with holding forks.
Check balance by rotating spit in palms of hands.
Arrange medium-hot coals at back of firebox; place foil drip pan under spit area.
Cook ribs on rotisserie for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until done, basting with marinade.
Brush ribs with 1/2 cup honey during last 30 minutes of cooking.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Crush graham crackers until crackers are fine.
Melt margarine, milk and marshmallows.
Mix cracker crumbs, marshmallow mixture and all other ingredients well.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients until crumbly.
Press half of crumbs into a greased 9-inch baking pan.
Cover with 4 cups diced rhubarb.
Mix remaining ingredients and cook until thick and clear; pour over rhubarb.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Serve warm, plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken and green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Top with Parmesan or Cheddar cheese. Bake in a 9 x 12-inch casserole at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: old-fashioned beef stew
directions: Coat beef with flour, shaking off excess.
In a large nonstick pot, heat oil over medium-high heat.
Add beef;
saute until browned, about 6 minutes. Place on a plate.

title: microwave norwegian meat balls
directions: Pour cream or milk over bread crumbs and soak 15 minutes. Blend beef, veal, egg, salt, pepper, onion, capers and crumb mixture.
Shape into 1-inch meat balls and arrange on a shallow dish.
Place in microwave oven and cook at Full power for 8 to 10 minutes or bake in conventional oven at 350° for 15 minutes.
Rest 5 minutes and make gravy out of the rest of the ingredients except the parsley which is topping.
The gravy will take 3 to 5 minutes in the microwave; or in pan on the stove, cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Pour gravy over meat balls and top with parsley.

title: three bean salad
directions: Lightly toss beans, onion and green pepper in large bowl.
In jar with tight fitting lid, shake oil, vinegar, Worcestershire, sugar, garlic, salt and pepper until well mixed.
Discard garlic. Pour dressing over bean mixture.
Mix to coat well.
Refrigerate 2 or 3 hours.

title: party punch
directions: In large punch bowl, combine all ingredients, except sherbet. Spoon sherbet in last and serve immediately.
Serves 28 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: crescent chicken
directions: Wrap in crescent roll (Pillsbury); makes 4 to a large package. Spread melted butter on top and brush with seasoned bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: marinated fruit
directions: Combine fruit in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over fruit.
Stir gently.
Chill at least 2 hours before serving. Makes 6 cups.

title: pickled mirliton
directions: Wash mirliton, cut in half to remove seed.
Slice lengthwise. Chop onions and peppers into large pieces.
Combine all ingredients except mirliton in pot large enough to hold everything.
Bring to a boil.
Put mirliton in and leave just long enough to heat all the way through.
Don't boil them.
Sterilize jars and pack mirlitons in jars then pour over vinegar mixture. Seal and put in hot water bath for 10 minutes.
I've doubled, quadrupled or even more.
Still comes out wonderful.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bottom of pan, put pecans and coconut.
Mix cake as directed on box and pour pecans and coconut. Mix the cream cheese, butter (softened) and powdered sugar and spoon over the cake mix.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: fruit lover's pops
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine the fruit flavored gelatin and 1/2 cup of water.
Put the saucepan on a burner.
Turn the burner to high.
Cook and stir with a wooden spoon until the mixture is bubbly.
Turn off the burner.
Remove the saucepan from the burner. Add the frozen fruit juice concentrate.
Stir until the juice concentrate is melted.
Stir in 1/2 cup cold water.
Pour the juice mixture into the liquid measuring cup.
Pour the juice mixture into the paper cups.
Cut foil into 4-inch squares.
Carefully cover each paper cup with a foil square, making a small slit in the center of each foil top.
Push a wooden stick through the hole into the juice mixture.
Put the pops in the freezer and freeze about 6 hours or until firm.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle crushed chips over casserole.
Pour 1/4 cup melted butter over this.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: cheese pineapple casserole
directions: Combine cheese and pineapple.
Mix flour with sugar, then stir into pineapple.
Pour into small casserole dish.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs on top.
Pour margarine on crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fried pie crust
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cut in shortening.
Beat egg with milk and add to dry mixture.
Knead out lightly and wrap tight, chill in refrigerator.
Roll dough thin.
Fill with cooked dry fruit of your choice.
Fry in cooking oil at 375°.

title: rump roast supreme
directions: Double aluminum foil and line a rectangular baking dish, leaving plenty extra to cover the entire roast.
Put the roast in pan and cut onion into small pieces on top of it.
Pour soup over the roast and onion.
Add A.1. sauce on top of soup.
Bring foil together to form a tent, covering the roast.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: cheesy potato casserole
directions: Spread frozen potatoes in a buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add onion (frozen works well) and mix.
Sprinkle cheese over potatoes. In separate bowl, mix chicken soup, sour cream and milk.
Spread over entire casserole.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over mixture, then drizzle melted butter over corn flakes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Goes very well with baked ham.

title: spring salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Cool slightly and add rest of ingredients.
Place in a ring mold and chill until set.
To serve: Unmold and garnish.
Very colorful and crunchy, too!

title: company beef curry
directions: With steel knife in place, process garlic in food processor until finely minced. Place slicing blade in place and process onions. Cut steak into 3 sections, cutting with the grain; place on top of each other and cut into 3-inch lengths, cutting across grain. Place in processor using a slicing blade and cut crosswise against grain.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into greased skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Mix pineapple and apples.
Over this, pour juice of 1 lemon. Mix and add 2 cups miniature marshmallows.

title: creamy delight
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together and boil for 3 minutes, stirring often.
Pour in a bowl and place in refrigerator overnight.
The following day, fold in the Cool Whip and the strawberries.
Easy, but elegant; I hope you like it!

title: baked egg and chili omelet
directions: Butter bread and cut into cubes.
Layer bread cubes, cheese and chilies in buttered casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over bread cubes, cheese and chilies.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, 1 hour in 350° oven. Remove cover and bake 5 minutes more or until puffy and set.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Place
butter in a 2-cup measure or small bowl.
Microwave on High
for
20 to 30 seconds or until melted.
Stir in flour
and salt
until smooth.
Slowly blend in milk.	Microwave,
uncovered, on High for 2 1/2 to 3 1/2 minutes or until thickened.
Stir occasionally.
Tear cheese into small pieces and
stir
into thickened
sauce.
If
cheese
does not melt, microwave on High 15 seconds or until melted.

title: guacamole
directions: Halve avocado, peel, pit and mash in a medium-sized bowl (approximately 1 cup).
Blend in remaining ingredients.
Cover tightly and chill.
(Dip will keep its bright color several hours.)

title: meringue baskets
directions: Beat whites, cream of tartar, salt, vinegar and vanilla until peaks form.
Slowly add sugar.
Bake on greased cookie
sheet at 275° for 1 hour.
Leave in oven until cool with the door closed. Makes 9 big ones or 13 to 14 small ones.

title: raspberry salad
directions: Stir Jell-O in boiling water well.
Cool.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Chill in a sprayed with oil molded container.

title: apple pound cake
directions: Beat sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla until well blended.
Combine dry ingredients and add sugar mixture, beating well.
Stir in apples, nuts and raisins.
Spoon batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: yeast muffins
directions: Cream butter with sugar. Add egg. Add dissolved yeast and water to creamed mixture. Add flour and stir well. Bake in greased muffin pan; fill each cup 2/3 full. Bake for about 20 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and remove meat from bone; save broth.
Boil vermicelli pasta in broth and drain (don't rinse off).
Saute onion and green pepper in a little margarine in a large pot on stove on low.
Cut Velveeta into cubes and melt while stirring constantly.
Makes delicious dish for 8.
Serve with bread and salad.

title: spinach-cheese lasagna rolls
directions: Cook and stir onion and garlic in oil in medium skillet until tender.
Add spinach and cook over medium heat until mixture is very dry.
In medium bowl, combine spinach mixture, cheeses, egg, sugar and pepper.
Spread scant 1/2 cup mixture on each lasagna noodle and roll up lengthwise.
Place lasagna rolls, seam side down in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cover; bake in preheated 350° for about 20 minutes.
Heat tomato sauce, mushrooms and herbs in small saucepan.
Spoon sauce onto serving plate.
Cut lasagna rolls into thirds; place cut side up on sauce.
Sprinkle with green onions.

title: pastry(serves 10)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt. Pour boiling chicken broth over flour mixture. Let stand until cold. Add egg. If dough is too soft, add flour. If too stiff, add some milk. Roll and cut. Drop in boiling chicken broth. Cover and cook 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mountain meat pie
directions: Combine meat, tomato sauce, bread crumbs, onion, bell pepper, salt, pepper, garlic and Worcestershire sauce.
Pat this into the bottom and sides of a greased 9-inch pie pan.
Boil rice in 2 cups water until half-cooked; about 10 minutes.
Combine rice, cooking water, tomato sauce (1 can) and 1/4 cup grated cheese. Place in meat shell.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Pour off excess juices.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and 1/2 can tomato sauce and bake uncovered for 15 minutes longer.

title: chicken roma
directions: Coat chicken with Shake 'n Bake.
Then bake on ungreased pan at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: doctor bird cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add bananas, oil, vanilla, eggs and pineapple with its juice.
Stir to blend but do not beat. Pour into greased 9-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Cool in pan on rack.

title: swedish limpa bread
directions: In large bowl combine sugar, molasses, 1/4 cup butter, salt, anise and orange peel.
Add 1 cup boiling water, stir until sugar dissolves and butter melts.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast over warm water in measuring cup, stir until dissolved.
Add to molasses mixture; mix well.
Gradually add 5 cups flour and 1 cup rye flour; beat vigorously until smooth and dough leaves side of bowl.
Gradually add 3 cups rye flour.
Mix in last of flour with hand until dough leaves side of bowl.
(Dough is stiff.)
Turn out onto lightly floured pastry cloth or board. Knead until smooth and elastic, 10 minutes.
Place in lightly greased large bowl; turn dough to bring up greased side.
Cover with towel; let rise in warm place (85°), free from drafts, until double in bulk, about 1 1/2 hours.
Grease a large cookie sheet and sprinkle lightly with cornmeal.
Punch down dough, and turn out onto lightly floured pastry cloth or board.
Cut in half.
Shape each half into an oval.
With palms of hands, on lightly floured surface, roll each half into a loaf,12 inches long, tapering ends. Place on prepared cookie sheet, 5 inches apart.
With sharp knife, make four diagonal slashes in top of loaf, 1/4 inch deep.
Cover with towel; let rise in warm place, free from drafts, until double in bulk, 1 to 1 1/4 hours. preheat oven to 375°.
Bake on middle shelf for 35 minutes, cover with foil last 10 minutes if necessary. Brush with butter.
Serve warm, or cool on rack.
Makes two.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour boiling water over oatmeal.
Add soda.
Let set for 10 minutes.
Add butter, sugars and eggs; mix.
Then add rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour batter in pan.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together except Ritz crackers and melted butter.
Pour mixture into casserole baking dish.
Crush crackers, melt butter and mix together.
Put crackers on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Great side dish!

title: london broil marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour over steaks.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 24 hours.
Turn once or twice.
Allow meat to stand at room temperature for at least 1 hour before putting on grill.
Baste with the marinade while grilling.

title: apple nut cake
directions: Beat well the oil, eggs and sugar, about 2 1/2 minutes. Gradually add flour.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Pour batter in an ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tests done.

title: hot fudge pudding cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Stir in milk, peanut butter, oil and vanilla until smooth.
Spread mixture into square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Stir together in small bowl brown sugar and 1/4 cup cocoa.
Sprinkle this mixture over batter in pan.
Pour hot water over the top of brown sugar, cocoa mixture but do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
To serve, spoon each serving upside down into dessert dishes.
Spoon sauce over top.
Best served warm.

title: daddy's hash
directions: In a very large pot, cook meat till done.
Let cool.
Pull meat from bone and chop or shred into small pieces.
Put back in pot.
You may have to add more water.
Chop onions and potatoes small and add to pot.
Put in fat back and vinegar.
Mash sausage with hand.
Put in pot and stir till sausage mixes into other ingredients.
Bring all to boil, then turn down between medium and low and cook, stirring often for 4 to 5 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: mrs. fields chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add eggs and vanilla.
Mix the rest. Roll in golf ball size and place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 12 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; cool, skin and debone.
Measure and keep 2 cups chicken broth.
Dice celery and onion; melt oleo and mix the Stove Top stuffing.
Mix together sour cream and chicken soup.

title: sausage and rice casserole
directions: In large skillet, fry sausage and onion; drain. Add celery and simmer for 5 minutes. Add rice, water and mushroom soup. Pour into buttered casserole. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Shredded cheese can be added last 15 minutes if desired.

title: barbecue sauce meat balls
directions: For meat balls, combine egg and milk.
Beat well.
Stir in bread crumbs, onion, salt, sage, garlic powder and meat.
Mix well and shape into 1-inch balls.
Place in shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Combine barbecue sauce, orange marmalade and water.
Stir in drained meat balls after they have been baked.
I use the plain thick original barbecue sauce. Pepper to taste.
These can be frozen also.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Pat crescent rolls into slightly greased jelly roll pan (15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch).
Bake at 350° to 375° until lightly brown, about 10 minutes.
Cool.
Combine salad dressing, cream cheese and seasonings in small bowl.
Beat until creamy.
Spread over cooled crescent rolls.
Top with any combination of chopped vegetables (green pepper, mushrooms, shredded carrots, cauliflower, broccoli and olives).
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese.
Cut into squares and refrigerate.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar and cream with butter.
Add eggs one at a time; beat in mixture well.
Add flour and milk and add the flavoring.
Bake in steeple pan in a 325° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool and remove from pan.

title: piggy pudding
directions: Mix flour and margarine until crumbly. Press into 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 350° until golden brown (15 to 20 minutes). Cool.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together. Beat eggs in milk and cook all until thick.
Pour in a baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites and put on top. Brown in oven at 350°.

title: oyster snack crackers
directions: Mix crackers and dry ingredients, then oil. Use plastic container with lid, turn often.

title: pralines(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Lightly butter a sheet of aluminum foil. Combine sugars, cream and salt in a large saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until 228° on candy thermometer. Stir in butter and pecan halves. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until 236°. Remove from heat and cool 5 minutes. Beat mixture with wooden spoon until slightly thickened. Drop candy by large spoonfuls on buttered foil.

title: broccoli corn bread
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add cornbread mix and pour in well-greased pan.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: pineapple quicky cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: no cook banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding with milk until thick.
Add sour cream;
fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of pan with vanilla wafers, then a layer of bananas, then a layer of pudding mixture.
Alternate layers. Crumble vanilla wafers and put on top.
Will refrigerate for several days.

title: cappuccino coffee mix
directions: Mix everything together.
Put in fancy glass containers for gift or airtight container for own use.

title: mocha coffee mix
directions: Mix.
Spoon 1 1/2 to 2 tablespoons into coffee mug.
Pour boiling water into mug.
Top with whipped cream.
Store mixture in airtight container.

title: spring salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients, then shake.
Makes about 24 ounces. Shake before each use.
(Shake in a 32 ounce jar.)

title: hearty salad
directions: Arrange first 10 ingredients in large salad bowl in order listed.
Spread mayonnaise on top of the salad.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Cover bowl and refrigerate 24 hours.
Toss and serve.
It will look limp; it's supposed to.
Serves 6 as main course or 12 as salad.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook sugar and milk until soft ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat, then add peanut butter and vanilla.
After removing from stove, mix for just a little while.
Pour into a butter greased pan or platter.

title: linda's peach cake
directions: Layer ingredients in order in a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Bake at 350 for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Saute onions and celery. Add all ingredients except cracker crumbs, and margarine.
Mix well and put into greased casserole dish.
Melt margarine and stir the crumbs together.
Put on top of the casserole.
Bake in medium oven (350) for 20 minutes or until light brown.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake about 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Frost or serve with Cool Whip.

title: sausage zucchini boats
directions: Cook whole zucchini in boiling salt water until barely tender (7 to 10 minutes).
Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and scoop squash from shells and put in medium bowl; mash.
Cook sausage and onion; drain off fat.
Stir in mashed zucchini and remaining ingredients; reserve a little of the cheese to sprinkle on top. Spoon mixture back into zucchini shells and sprinkle with reserved cheese.
Place in shallow baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over two cans of Chinese noodles.
Makes about 12 servings.

title: russian tea
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; boil 10 minutes.
Remove cinnamon.
Add fruit juices, and place over low heat.
Pour the boiling water over tea; let stand (steep) 10 minutes or until of strength desired.
Strain into fruit juices.
Serve piping hot. Makes about 5 to 6 servings.

title: tot's rolls
directions: Stir sugar and salt into first 3 ingredients.
Add eggs and stir.
Add yeast.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Cover with foil and set aside in warm place for 2 hours.
Dough should be double in size within 2 hours.
Punch down.
Roll to 1/4-inch thickness and cut rolls.
Dip 1/2 of each roll in melted oleo and fold over like envelope.
Place on baking sheets.
Let rise 2 hours.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Brush with melted oleo.
Takes 3 sticks of oleo.
Rolls can be frozen.
Remove from freezer and wrap in foil and heat.

title: chocolate candy clay
directions: Melt chocolate and add corn syrup; stir until thoroughly mixed. Let stand at room temperature in an airtight plastic bag for at least 24 hours or up to one week.
Candy becomes easier to work with as it sets.
When ready to use, knead a small amount until it reaches a workable consistency.
This candy clay is great for making candy roses or any shape you want.
You can also roll it into thin logs and cut into desired lengths.
Tastes a lot like Tootsie Rolls.
It's very fun and easy!

title: charlie's dip
directions: Drain tuna fish.
Combine with cottage cheese or yogurt in blender.
Process until smooth.
Season to taste.
Use as dip for raw veggies or crackers.

title: cheese soup
directions: Combine and simmer first 5 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Add soup and cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper together.
Add corn, tomato sauce and taco seasoning.
Spread the mixture in a casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and crushed tortilla chips.
Bake at 350°.
Cheese can be Cheddar or Mozzarella.

title: enchiladas de pollo y queso(serving size:  6.  preparation time:  1:00)
directions: Melt two tablespoons butter and cook onions and green pepper in it until softened.
Remove to a bowl and stir in chopped chicken and green chilies.
Melt remaining 3 tablespoons of butter.
Blend in flour and seasonings.
Whisk in chicken broth. Cook, stirring, until sauce boils.
Remove from heat; stir in sour cream and 1/2 cup cheese.
Stir 1/2 cup sauce into chicken mixture.
Dip each tortilla in remaining hot sauce to soften and spoon chicken mixture into center of tortilla.
Roll up and arrange in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; repeat with all tortillas.
Pour remaining sauce over tortillas.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake uncovered at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Saute onion, celery, garlic, bell pepper and parsley in bacon drippings until soft.
Add tomato paste, tomatoes and 1 cup water. Add all other ingredients except shrimp and gumbo file.
Cook slowly, about 1 hour.
Add raw shrimp; cook 15 minutes.
Add gumbo file.
Serve over rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Toss together uncooked rice, celery, onion and broccoli in a 3-quart casserole.
Add water, soup and oleo.
Dot with cheese over top. Bake at 300° for 1 hour. Cover with lid or foil for the last 10 minutes in the oven.

title: skillet pork chops with cabbage
directions: Heat oil in a heavy skillet and brown the chops slowly on both sides.
Combine onion, vinegar, sugar, pepper, tomato juice, soy sauce and salt; pour over the pork chops and bring to a boil.
Turn down the heat and simmer for 30 minutes or until the chops are done.

title: cold platter plate(a sunday afternoon special)
directions: On a platter, cover with lettuce leaves.
Place cottage cheese in the center
of
plate.
Cut
the
meats
in half and place around the
cottage cheese.
Surround the meats with the tomatoes and the
pickles.
French dressing may be poured over the cottage cheese.
Chill and serve.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Mix all ingredients to taste. Stuff the eggs and garnish if desired or try mixing egg yolks with Italian salad dressing.

title: grandma's red beans and rice
directions: Place
all
but rice in large pot and cover with water. Cover and
cook
over
low
flame
for 2 hours.
Fry onion in skillet with
butter
until
soft; add to beans with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve hot over cooked rice.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine, pour into 2 qt. baking dish.

title: spring lemonade salad
directions: Prepare lemonade as directed on can.
Mix gelatin with 1/4 cup lemonade and let stand 5 minutes.
Mix with pudding and add 1 3/4 cups more lemonade.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until pudding boils.
Cool; fold in Cool Whip, nuts, marshmallows and fruit.
Place in mold or 9 x 13-inch pan and chill until set. May be used as salad or dessert.

title: artichoke appetizer
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Place 1/2 tablespoon artichoke on bread; top with mayonnaise mixture.
Place under broiler until bubbly brown.
Serve hot.

title: chicken with mushroom gravy
directions: Wash and soak chicken in bowl of salted water for at least 20 minutes.
Dip chicken pieces in flour seasoned with salt, pepper and spices (oregano, thyme, basil, etc.).
Brown chicken in skillet, but don't cook it.
Place chicken in 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan. Mix soup (2 cans), water, onion and enough of remaining flour mixture so it will thicken.
Pour over chicken and bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheese spread
directions: Whip Philadelphia cream cheese.
Add Roka and Old English. Whip all together.
Add crushed garlic.
If too thick, add a few drops of milk.
Serve with any crackers.
Use Kraft cheese spreads.

title: pot herb soup
directions: Cook the leek and peas in 2 1/2 cups consomme.
Meanwhile, chop the onion, chives, chervil and parsley fine.

title: fried tomatoes(1928)
directions: Wash and dry the tomatoes; slice crosswise to make 3 thick pieces.
Dust with salt, pepper and a little sugar; roll in fine dry bread crumbs.
Beat the egg.
Add the milk.
Dip the slices in this; dip again in crumbs.
Deep fry in Mazola, hot enough to brown a piece of bread in 1 minute (350°).
Drain on crumbled paper; serve plain or with toast with white sauce.

title: apple-cinnamon-bran muffin mix
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients.
Cut in shortening with pastry cutter until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cereal and apples.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all these ingredients.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and beat until creamy.
Pour over hot cake.
Cut into squares and serve warm or cold.

title: sausage balls
directions: Brown sausage; drain well, then mix all ingredients together. Batter will be stiff.
Mix with your hands.
Pinch off in small balls and bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes or until brown.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together. Add eggs and mix.
Add bananas and mix.
In another bowl, mix flour, salt and baking soda.
Add this to the other, mixing well.
Blend in nuts.
Place in greased loaf pan and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour at 375° or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chili beans
directions: Cook pinto beans with salt added for flavor.
Add 2 tablespoons of chili powder to beans.
Brown ground beef; add about 1 teaspoon salt.
Add onion while cooking.
Drain and add 3 tablespoons chili powder and stir well.
Add ground beef mixture to beans.
Mash tomatoes up into small pieces, then add to beans. Let simmer 2 minutes.

title: creamed tomatoes
directions: Simmer together the tomatoes, butter, sugar and salt.
Make thickening by mixing milk, water and flour; add to tomatoes.
Cook until boiled.

title: american beauty cake
directions: Mix food color with cocoa and let stand.
Cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and color mixture.
Beat very well.
Add buttermilk, cake flour, salt and vanilla.
Beat.
Add vinegar and soda and beat by hand.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 8-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Use a thread to cut each layer in half, making 4 layers.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Combine ground beef, onion and garlic powder in a large skillet.
Cook over medium heat until meat is browned, stirring to crumble.
Drain well.
Add next seven ingredients.
Cook mixture 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Tear each tortilla into 8 pieces. Place half of the pieces in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with meat mixture.
Arrange remaining tortilla pieces evenly over meat mixture.
Combine soup and milk in a large bowl.
Mix well and pour over tortillas.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: big batch no-bake cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, milk, cocoa, and salt, and bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Boil for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add remaining ingredients. Stir thoroughly and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper or foil. It makes about 60.

title: chinese plum sauce
directions: In saucepan, cook onion in oil until soft.
Mix cornstarch with vinegar and sugar. Add to onion. Cook, stirring until thickened. Add plums, salt and extract. Continue cooking until fruit is tender.
Spoon some sauce over partially cooked spareribs. Grill, brushing frequently with sauce.
Heat remaining sauce to serve with barbecued spareribs.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.

title: quick and easy punch
directions: Mix orange juice and lemonade according to directions on can. Add pineapple juice.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.
Add apricot nectar, if desired.
Yield:
50 servings.

title: rocky road s'mores bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients; mix well.
Press onto bottom of greased 9-inch square pan.
Sprinkle with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: chicken breasts romano
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt and pepper.
Brown lightly in oil. Remove chicken and set aside.
Add ham, onion, celery and basil; simmer and stir for 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan.
Add stock or water to tomato paste.
Pour over chicken and cover.
Simmer 40 to 60 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add parsley.
Serve with boiled spaghetti.
Serves 6 persons.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Mix
vanilla
pudding and milk.
Add Cool Whip, then put over set Jell-O.

title: pink passion
directions: Put in a bowl and mix well.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Mix crackers and margarine and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over crust.
Top with 1 large Cool Whip and chill.
May be frozen until ready to serve.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine in casserole dish, broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, soup concentrate, 3 ounces of fried onions, and salt and pepper to taste.
Mix evenly together, cover with aluminum foil and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and cover with remaining 3 ounces of fried onions and shredded Swiss cheese.
Bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool for 10 minutes.
Serve.

title: ruth's breakfast casserole
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread stuffing in bottom of pan and sprinkle season packet on top.
Next layer cheese over stuffing. Then put your sausage on top of cheese.
Mix next five ingredients and pour on top of sausage.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.
If gets too brown before baking time is up, put Reynolds Wrap on top loosely.

title: crawfish cornbread
directions: Combine and mix above ingredients.
Prepare skillet or pan for cornbread by greasing and sprinkling with meal and let brown. Pour batter into skillet.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: spicy rice
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in butter until crisp. Stir in seasonings, rice and raisins.
Heat thoroughly.
Stir in apples.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes. Sprinkle with almonds.

title: four bean salad(serves 8 to 10)
directions: Drain beans and combine with green pepper and onion in large bowl.
Mix sugar, vinegar and oil and pour over mixture.
Season with salt and pepper and toss lightly.
Refrigerate overnight. Before serving, toss again.

title: saucy peas and rice
directions: Cook and stir mushrooms in hot margarine in a saucepan until lightly browned.
Add peas, soup, milk and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Stir in rice. Cover, remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork. Makes 6 servings.

title: easy chicken 'n gravy
directions: Will also need a large 14 x 20-inch oven bag.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Cut stems from mushrooms.
Combine bacon, onion, mayonnaise and sour cream.
Stuff mushrooms and broil for 5 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done and brown on top.

title: herb dip
directions: Mix together, making several hours in advance. Serve with chips, vegetables or snack crackers or breads.

title: apple pie no crust
directions: In bowl, stir together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt. With fork stir in egg and vanilla.
Mix until crumbly.
Sprinkle over pie filling.
Pour butter over top and bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until lightly brown.
Pour filling into greased 9-inch pie pan.

title: easy monkey bread(or cinnamon breakfast bread)
directions: Cut biscuits in fourths.
Arrange in single layer in 8 or 9-inch pie plate or pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together and sprinkle over biscuits.
Melt margarine and drizzle over.
Bake at 450° about 10 minutes, until browned.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Wash and slice zucchini.
Saute in butter until barely tender, along with green onions.
Add chicken stock and parsley.
Puree in blender, adding only half the mixture to blender at a time. Return to saucepan; add Worcestershire sauce and cream.
Heat to very hot, but not boiling and serve at once.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pickled red eggs
directions: Pack the eggs in two quart jars.
Combine beet juice, vinegar and spices in a saucepan and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour over eggs; seal.
Let cool and chill.
Refrigerate for a few days to allow flavors to permeate the eggs.
Makes 16 pickled eggs.

title: crunchy topping mix
directions: Heat oven to 325°. Spread crackers & noodles on ungreased jelly roll pan (15 x 10). In small bowl, combine oil, parmesan cheese, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and Worcestershire sauce; blend well. Pour over crackers and noodles; stir to coat. Bake at 325° for 10 - 15 minutes. Cool completely and store in airtight container.

title: broccoli corn bake casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Put in greased casserole and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: hot festival fruit
directions: Mix together.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Brown pork in fat.
Add water and simmer for 1 hour.
Combine sugar, cornstarch, salt, vinegar, pineapple juice and soy sauce. Mix and cook until slightly thick, stirring constantly.
Pour over hot pork; let stand 10 minutes.
Add pepper, onion and pineapple. Cook 2 to 3 minutes.
Vegetables will be crispy.
Serve over rice.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Sift the salt and baking powder with the flour.
Mix all ingredients together and bake in a slow moderate oven.

title: raspberry coconut cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare and bake cake mix as directed on package for two (9-inch) round cake layers adding 2/3 cup of the coconut to batter.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Mix water and yeast and set aside to soften.
In a large bowl, mix sugar, soda, salt and buttermilk.
Add shortening and yeast. Stir in flour.
Turn out dough on a floured surface.
Knead and shape into rolls.
Place rolls in buttered pans, brush tops with melted butter.
Set aside and allow to rise 2 to 3 hours.
Bake at 450° for 15 to 20 minutes or until brown.

title: sunshine carrot salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; stir well.
Chill 2 to 3 hours. Stir in sour cream.
Serve salad on lettuce leaves.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend egg yolks and lemon juice in a blender.
Melt butter on low heat and slowly add to egg mixture.
Add red pepper and blend well.

title: hankie pankies
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Add cheese.
Stir until melted.
Stir in oregano and garlic powder.
Cool for several minutes.
Spread on bread slices.
Arrange slices on rack in broiler pan.
Broil until cheese is bubbly.
Place on serving platter.
Serve hot.

title: oreo cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Reserve 1/2 cup.
Mix remaining Oreo crumbs with melted butter.
Press mixture in bottom of an oblong or rectangular pan.
Place pan in freezer while mixing the next layer.
Mix cream cheese with 12 ounces of Cool Whip.
Spread on top of Oreo mixture and put back into the freezer.
Prepare pudding according to package directions. Spread on top of cream cheese mixture.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and crumbs.
Keep chilled and covered in refrigerator until ready to serve

title: heavenly chocolate cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir cake mix and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat at medium speed with electric mixer until blended.
Pour into ungreased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan or 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool and frost as desired.
Makes 12 servings.

title: jam cake
directions: Sift flour and spices together.
Mix eggs, sugar, oil and buttermilk.
Gradually add flour mixture to this.
Add jam and pecans last.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for about 1 hour.
Frost with favorite frosting.

title: john's famous hot chili
directions: Dice onions and bell peppers.
Saute in a small amount of oil for about 15 minutes or until they begin to tenderize.
Add the ground round and brown thoroughly.
When all the meat is browned, totally drain all the liquid from the pan.
Add the large can of hot salsa, the three cans of El Paso hot sauce and the chili powder.
Cook for about 1 1/2 hours at low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Add can of beer and cook for another 1 hour.
Add kidney beans and cook for 1 hour.
Taste and enjoy!

title: ruby's lemon pecan pie
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients with a fork or whisk.
(Do not beat with a mixer.)
Stir in pecan pieces.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: blue cheese salad dressing--mom's recipe
directions: Place softened cheese in mixer bowl and blend well-serve with paprika on top.
Great on potatoes, wedges of lettuce and as dip for crackers.
tags: bricks of Roquefort cheese from deli

title: low cholesterol breakfast patties
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Shape into 4 patties and place on a rack in a shallow pan.
Broil 2 to 4 inches from heat 10 to 15 minutes.
Turn patties and broil 5 to 10 minutes or until done.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Bring a large pot of water to a boil, place the beans in the pot, stir.
Turn off stove.
Let stand 2 hours.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine stock, tomatoes, water, Worcestershire sauce, bay leaves and salt.
Drain beans and add to mixture.
Add ham or sausage, onion and garlic; bring to a boil.
Place in Dutch oven or covered casserole dish.
Bake 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender.
Serve over rice.
Serves 4.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chicken salad casserole
directions: Mix first 10 ingredients thoroughly.
Put in a baking dish. Sprinkle with Rice Krispies.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
May be frozen.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls flat on cookie sheet (15 x 10 x 1-inch). Press to join edges.
Bake at 400° for approximately 10 minutes. Cool.

title: orange onion salad
directions: Toss mandarin oranges and mild onion. Spoon into lettuce cups. Top with 1 to 2 tablespoons buttermilk dressing.
Makes 4 servings.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Stir together the flour and salt.
Beat eggs thoroughly; mix in potatoes and onions.
Stir into flour mixture; blend well. Lightly grease a large skillet with cooking oil.
Heat over medium heat.
Drop by tablespoon on hot skillet.
Fry slowly, turning to brown evenly.
Serve hot with applesauce or sour cream.
Makes about 16.

title: fruit salad
directions: Thicken pineapple juice with 1 Tablespoon of cornstarch in saucepan over medium heat. Add 1 pack of Equal to sauce when cooled. Pour over fruit and stir.

title: creme de la french
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yields 1-1/2 cups of dressing.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Roll nuts, orange slice pieces and dates in flour.
Mix flour mixture and all other ingredients and add creamed batter.
Pour into large baking pan or Pyrex dish and bake at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: soy-banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together soy and white flour, baking powder, soda, salt, sugar and dry milk.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients.
Add and mix just until moistened the egg, water, mashed bananas and chopped nuts.
Spread in greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes.
Remove loaf from pan to cool. Delicious warm or toasted.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: macaroni and crabmeat
directions: Boil macaroni.
Wash with cold water.
Let it chill before mixing.
Mix macaroni with crabmeat and other ingredients.
Serve.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Place crescent roll dough on pizza pan or cookie sheet and flatten.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes, until golden brown.

title: hot fruit casserole
directions: Drain fruit, saving juice from peaches, pineapple and apple rings to make 2 cups. Add cornstarch, sugar, sherry and butter to juice and cook until thickened. Arrange fruits attractively in a long casserole in layers. Pour thickened sauce over all and bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until heated through. Serve with any meat. Serves 8 to 10.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Put first 7 ingredients in a mixing bowl and mix thoroughly. Add eggs, vanilla, pumpkin and milk.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°. Reduce heat to 350° and bake 45 minutes or until a knife comes out clean when tested.
Makes 3 pies.

title: nutty fingers *
directions: Mix sugar and margarine and add nuts, flour, salt and vanilla. Roll into small balls or little rolls like your finger.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until done.
Allow to cool and roll in 10x sugar.

title: german chocolate caramel squares
directions: Mix cake mix and margarine together with pastry blade.
Mix in milk.
Press half of mixture into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: popcorn candy
directions: Use fresh popcorn and spread out on greased cookie sheet. Combine sugar, molasses, salt and melted butter.
Cook to about 290° or a hard-cracked stage.
Pour over corn and spread thin, making sure all corn is covered.
Break up when cold.

title: deep fried fish batter
directions: Mix in enough milk to other ingredients until smooth.
Dip fish in batter, covering well.
Put fish in hot oil.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes on each side until light brown.
Also good for onion rings.

title: light 'n fruity pie
directions: Completely dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Combine cold water and ice cubes to make 1 1/4 cups.
