Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove any unmelted ice.
Using wire whisk, blend in whipped topping.
Whip until smooth.
Fold in fruit and chill until mixture will mound.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk in heavy 2 1/2 quart saucepan.
Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly to prevent scorching.

title: pumpkin swirl
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Line top and sides with waxed paper.
Beat eggs and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in pumpkin. Stir in dry ingredients.
Pour into pan. Spread evenly. Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake for 13 to 15 minutes. Invert onto towel dusted with powdered sugar.
Peel off wax paper. Roll up cake and towel together from the short side.
Place, seam side down, on wire rack. Cool completely. Unroll cake and spread with filling. Re-roll cake and refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: boiled custard
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, salt and scalded milk.
Cook over boiling water until liquid coats spoon.
Add vanilla.
Chill.

title: delicious eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender on high for 2 minutes. Refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: honey blonde brownies
directions: Preheat oven at 350°.
Mix all ingredients together.
Spread into well-greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes, but only until a slight imprint shows when touched with fingers; don't overbake.
Cut into squares before cooling.

title: corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease iron skillet.
In large bowl, mix corn meal, eggs, milk and hardened bacon grease or all-purpose shortening.
Pour into iron skillet.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Best eaten while hot with butter.

title: salad dressing
directions: Whisk together all ingredients or shake in a covered jar.

title: pound cake with caramel frosting
directions: Beat butter at medium speed until creamy. Gradually, add sugar, beating at medium for about 5 minutes. Add eggs one at a time, beating just until yellows disappear. Add flour to butter mixture, alternately with half and half. Mix until well blended. Add vanilla and stir. Pour batter into greased and floured 10 inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Cool in pan on wire rack 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan and cool completely. Spread with caramel frosting.

title: cinnamon cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and vanilla together.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients; chill at least 1 hour.
Following manufacturers directions for cookie press, mold dough directly on cookie sheets.
Bake at 425° for 7 to 9 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Boil zucchini for 10 minutes in salted water.
Remove from water and cool.
Cut lengthwise and scrape zucchini out, making boat.
Put this extra in blender and puree.
Brown sausage and onion; drain grease off.
Mix zucchini puree, sausage, onion, Parmesan cheese and bread crumbs.
Beat eggs and mix in.

title: pilaf
directions: Melt butter with orzo until golden brown.
Melt cube with hot water.
Bring to boil.
Add onion soup.
Simmer for 1/2 hour until dry.
Stir occasionally.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla.
Mix well and add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix well and add nuts.
Bake in 2 greased loaf pans at 350° for 1 hour.
This bread freezes well.

title: dinner party chicken
directions: Saute chicken until white; cut in half or pieces and place in casserole.
Saute onion and celery in 2 tablespoons butter; add soup and mayonnaise.
Stir until heated.
Pour over chicken. Mix stuffing with beaten egg and melted butter.
Pour over sauce. Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cover if stuffing gets too brown.

title: italian meat loaf
directions: Combine 1/3 cup tomatoes, breadcrumbs and eggs in a large mixing bowl.
Add ground beef; mix well.
Pat mixture into an 8 x 8 x 3/4-inch square on a piece of foil.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt in large bowl. Cut 3/4 cup butter thoroughly with a pastry blender until mixture resembles very fine crumbs. Press mixture evenly into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan, using a piece of plastic wrap to press crumb mixture firmly in pan. Bake at 350° for 17 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: sauteed tomato slices
directions: Wash
tomatoes;
cut
stem
ends
off.	Mix
flour
and seasonings.
Cut tomatoes in 1/2-inch slices; dredge in flour. Saute in salad oil until brown on both sides, turning once.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: In saucepan, combine soup, water, salt, onion and pepper. Bring to a boil, stirring occasionally.
Pour half of mixture into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Make 3 layers in casserole, using Minute rice (right from box), peas and tuna fish.
Add remaining soup.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and paprika.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut through mixture with knife after baking 10 minutes.
Makes about 4 servings.

title: vegetable souffle
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Gently stir flour and seasonings into mayonnaise; do not overmix.
Slowly stir in milk, then vegetables. Beat egg whites until stiff.
Gently fold into mayonnaise mixture until thoroughly blended.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart souffle dish.
Bake in a 325° oven for 40 minutes, or until knife inserted into center comes out clean.
Serve at once.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Peel oranges and discard white part.
Put orange pulp and rind, cranberries and apples through food grinder.
Add sugar and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate.

title: orange rice
directions: Coat a large skillet with vegetable cooking spray and place over medium heat until hot.
Add rice, celery and onion.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until rice is lightly browned.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Pour mixture into a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until done.
Contains about 130 calories per 1/2 cup serving.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni conventionally; drain.
Set aside.
Melt butter in 2-quart casserole dish at High power, 40 to 55 seconds.
Stir in flour and seasonings until smooth.

title: magic cookie bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In 13 x 9-inch dish, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine, top with remaining ingredients.
Pour milk over top.
Bake 25 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Store loosely covered at room temperature.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg well.
Sift flour and baking powder together.
Mix soda in sweet milk and mix alternately with dry ingredients.
Mash bananas and add together.
Grease and flour baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: nut brittle
directions: Mix nuts, sugar and syrup together.
Cook until syrup just starts to turn brown.
Add 1/3 stick of margarine.

title: cherry squares
directions: Mix sugar and butter until smooth and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.
Pour into greased 15 x 10 x 1 pan.
Mark off 20 or more squares and place 1 teaspoon cherry pie filling in middle of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
While warm, sift powdered sugar over cake.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: manna cookies
directions: Combine the oil and honey, then add vanilla and eggs.
Mix thoroughly.
Sift the flour and add it (and the seeds, if you are using them) to the other ingredients.
Oil a baking sheet.
Drop cookie dough on it by tablespoonfuls, leaving about 2-inches of space between each cookie.
Cover a drinking glass with a damp cloth and use it to flatten cookies.
Bake 10 minutes in an oven set at 375°.
Makes about 50 cookies.

title: broccoli - lima casserole
directions: Cook lima beans and broccoli according to directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain well.
Combine sour cream, mushroom soup, onion soup and water chestnuts.
Fold into vegetables.
Spoon into a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
In a skillet, brown cereal in margarine until golden.
Spread over vegetable mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pancakes
directions: Mix ingredients together. Pour onto hot griddle. When bubbles form on top of pancake and edges begin to dry, turn pancake and cook the other side until brown.

title: candy bar pie
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler; cook until melted.
Cool.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into pie shell. Chill.

title: shrimp delightgroves, texas
directions: Saute onions and bell pepper in margarine.
Mix all ingredients and bake in 9 X 13 dish that is tightly covered at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: fruit salad
directions: Cut fruit into 1-inch squares.
Halve the grapes.
Mix together and add
the Cool Whip.

title: baked stuffed onions
directions: Cook onions 10 minutes in enough boiling salted water to cover; drain and cool.
Remove centers of onions, leaving about 1/4-inch shells.
Invert shells to drain.
Chop onion centers.
Cook sausage in skillet over medium heat until done.
Drain.
Combine sausage, 3/4 cup breadcrumbs and chopped onions.
If desired, stir in enough broth or butter to moisten.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Drain sauerkraut and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Place in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Store, covered, in refrigerator for at least 24 hours.
Makes 10 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into Pyrex dish.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Put grated cheese on the last 10 minutes of baking.

title: water chestnut appetizer
directions: Cut bacon strips in half; wrap halves around water chestnuts and secure with wooden toothpicks.
Place in baking dish and generously sprinkle with Worcestershire sauce.
Broil until bacon is brown.

title: jean's vegetable dip
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate. Delicious with raw broccoli, squash, cauliflower, etc.

title: teriyaki grilled chicken
directions: Preheat barbecue grill.
In a shallow dish, combine soy sauce, sherry, oil and ginger.
Place chicken in marinade and let stand 5 minutes.
Grill on barbecue until browned on both sides and cooked through, about 7 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Preheat
oven
Combine all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Mix
well
on medium speed with mixer. Flour chocolate
chips
before adding to cake mixture.
Grease Bundt pan. Bake for
35 to 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.

title: chocolate toffee bars
directions: Mix ingredients.
Press into a 13 x 9 ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool for 5 minutes.

title: layered green salad
directions: Place torn or chopped lettuce as the first layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Layer all ingredients, then add celery, peppers, onions and frozen peas.
Mix mayonnaise and sugar; spread over top of peas.
Sprinkle with cheese and bacon bits (bacon should be fried crisp in order to break up into small pieces or bits).
Refrigerate for 8 to 12 hours.
(You may hold bacon bits until serving time in order to be crisp.)

title: apple chess pie
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together 2/3 cup brown sugar and 1/4 cup butter until light and fluffy.
Stir in 1/3 cup flour.
Beat in evaporated milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in apples.
Pour into pie shell.

title: oklahoma cake
directions: Bake cake according to package directions, using a 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cake is done and still hot, punch holes with a fork all over cake surface.
Mix condensed milk with cream of coconut and pour over cake.
When cake is cooled, frost with Cool Whip, flaked coconut and pecans.
Can decorate with cherries.
Keep refrigerated.

title: scotch-a-roos
directions: Bring to boil sugar and honey, then add peanut butter.
Mix well, then add Rice Krispies.
Put into long baking dish (buttered).
Can be iced if desired.
Cut into squares.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook all together until thick, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Will make 2 pies.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.
In large bowl combine eggs, oil, sugar, vanilla, zucchini and pineapple.
Gradually beat in flour mixture. Stir in raisins and pecans.
Makes 2 large loaves, or 7 small loaves.
Bake at 350°; large loaves for 1 hour, small loaves 30 minutes.

title: congo bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.
Melt margarine in a large saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar and allow to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Add flour mixture, nuts and chocolate chips.
Pour into a greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares. Yield: 50 to 60 squares.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Mix cake
mix, eggs, oil and mandarin oranges. Mix until oranges are
cut
up in small dots.
Pour in pan.
Bake at 325° for 30
minutes.
Drain pineapple and keep juice.
When cake is done and is still hot, pour 1/2 can cream of coconut over cake; pour pineapple juice over cake; let cool.
Mix pudding, pineapple, 1/2
can
cream
of coconut, can of coconut and Cool Whip. Pour over cool cake and top with pecans.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Melt margarine and add enough stuffing mix to take up liquid. Put about 1/3 to 1/2 in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and put in dish.
Sprinkle remaining stuffing mix on top.
Bake in 375° preheated oven for 30 minutes.

title: ground beef stir-fry
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and garlic.
Add vegetables.
Saute just until crisp-tender point.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve over rice.

title: mexican cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger, sausage, green pepper and onion.
Add to 3-quart crock-pot and add picante sauce and chilies.
Add and melt Velveeta cheese.
Serve with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: chocolate pecan pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to directions for filled one-crust pie using 9-inch pie pan.
Flute as desired.

title: arizona mountain soup
directions: Rinse beans.
In a 5-quart kettle, combine beans and 3 cups water.
Cover and let stand overnight.
Do not drain.
Simmer, covered 2 hours or until beans are tender.
Drain, reserving 2 cups liquid.
In kettle, cook bacon until almost crisp.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook and stir in the cooked pinto beans, tomatoes, rice, salt, paprika and pepper.
Add reserved bean liquid and 2 cups water.
Bring mixture to boil.
Cover and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Serve 8. Great with cornbread.

title: asparagus bake
directions: Mix Ritz crackers and 1/2 cup oleo together.
Mix 4 tablespoons oleo, milk and flour.
Add cheese spread.
Layer cracker mix, asparagus, almonds and cheese.
Top with cracker mix leftover.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Slowly add rest of ingredients.
Pour into pastry shell.
Bake at 250° until done.

title: judy's sausage casserole
directions: Lay broken bread pieces in a well-greased casserole dish. Alternate layers of sausage and cheese.
Pour egg, milk, mustard and salt mixture over top.
Let sit in refrigerator overnight. Cover and bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Uncover last 10 minutes to brown on top.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients, add salt and pepper.
Pour into loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together the Crisco, butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and salt, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla and lemon extracts; beat well.
Bake at 300° for 2 hours.
Do not open oven door during baking time.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Add soup (undiluted), salt, egg, mayonnaise, onion flakes and cheese.
Top with crushed cheese crackers.
Cook at 325° until bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour loaf pan.
Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add milk and lemon extract; blend.
Sift dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture. Beat until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat entire mixture well before pouring into well-greased loaf pan.
Bake for 75 to 80 minutes.
Makes 1 pound cake.
Frost or sprinkle with powdered sugar or serve plain.

title: billi bi(a creamy french mussel soup)
directions: Clean and debeard the mussels.
Place all the ingredients except cream and egg yolks in a large soup pot.
Cover tightly and bring to a boil.
Lower the heat and simmer for 8 minutes or until the mussels have opened.
Remove the mussels and shell them; reserve in a bowl.
Strain the broth and return to the pot.
Add the cream and bring to a boil again.

title: pfeffernuse
directions: Mix in order given.
Pinch off and roll with hands about the size of an English walnut. Bake at 350° for approximately 10 to 12 minutes.
Better when kept for several weeks in an airtight container before eating.

title: zesty carrots
directions: Mix water, horseradish, chopped onion, mayonnaise, salt and pepper; pour mixture over carrots.
Mix crumbs, butter and paprika and sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes. Yields 6 servings.

title: burritos
directions: Brown and drain the ground beef. Add the taco seasoning and 2 teaspoons chili powder.
Cover meat mixture with water. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Drain liquid and set meat aside.
Add to liquid the tomato juice and 1 1/2 teaspoons chili powder.
Bring to a boil. Thicken with the cornstarch mixture.
Remove from heat and add the cheese.
Stir until melted. Pour enough of this gravy mixture into lightly greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish to cover bottom.
Fill medium size flour tortilla (soft) shells with meat mixture, some shredded cheese and 1 to 2 tablespoons gravy.
Place folded side down, in pan.
Put remaining gravy on top when all 12 tortillas are in pan.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.

title: orange nut mini balls
directions: Combined 1 1/2 cups nuts or Krispies with other ingredients and mix well. Shape into balls, roll in remaining 1/2 cup of nuts or Krispies.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Pinch broccoli into flowerets.
Add all ingredients together. Add mayo last.
Add enough to make it as creamy as you want it.

title: apple brownies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and
egg together.
Add apples.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: oatmeal butter quik
directions: Add oatmeal to salted boiling water, cook until done.
Add butter; dissolve Nestle Quik in the 3 tablespoons of hot water and add to oatmeal.

title: westport shrimp(from a taste of aloha)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease a 3-quart casserole.
In a saucepan, bring butter and cream to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Mix cornstarch and curry with the sherry and add to the cream. Cook until thickened, stirring constantly. Add shrimp or chicken, rice and raisins.
Blend in seasonings and pour mixture into the casserole.
Sprinkle cheese over the top and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly browned.

title: cocoa peanut butter mounds
directions: Mix sugar and cocoa in saucepan.
Add butter and milk.
Bring to a boil 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool thoroughly.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Combine everything (except flour and water).
Pour over meat in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on low 9 hours or until meat is very tender.
Lift meat from cooker.
Cool slightly and slice against the grain.
Skim off fat in cooker and turn on high when mixture is bubbling; stir in flour blended with 1/4 cup water.
Return meat to cooker and cook covered 15 minutes.
Serve on buns.

title: cranberry-orange salad
directions: Add boiling water to gelatin.
Mix in salt, cinnamon and cloves.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce and orange rind.
Chill until mixture starts to thicken.
Fold in orange and apple.
Chill until firm.

title: tater-tot casserole
directions: Press ground beef in bottom of dish.
Put chopped onion on top of meat; add Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper, cream of chicken soup and then cheese.
Cover with Tater Tots and bake 1 hour or until brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Test for doneness in middle like a cake.

title: broiled shrimp boats
directions: Place raw shrimp in saucepan.
Add white wine, salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Cut into bite-size pieces. Melt butter and blend in flour.
Gradually stir in reserved liquid.
Add milk and bring to boil.
Stir mixture until thickened.
Add shrimp, mushrooms and cheese and chives.
Cook 2 minutes longer.
Fill shells or ramekins.
Cover with buttered bread crumbs.
Broil until tops are lightly browned.

title: polish pineapple pudding
directions: Mix and let sit for an hour.

title: beef rouladen
directions: Separate rouladen steaks.
Season each steak lightly with salt.
Spread mustard to cover steak.
Saute onion in butter.
Add 1/2 of the onion to the steak.
Place 1 slice of bacon on top of onion.
Roll steak and fixings into an oblong shape and secure with toothpicks.
Brown rouladen steaks in 2 tablespoons of oil and place in a casserole dish and cover.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Add your favorite gravy.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Cool slightly.
Add sugar, brown sugar and eggs.
Sift and add flour and baking powder.
Add nuts. Bake in 8 x 8-inch greased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon pie
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add beaten eggs, lemon juice and flour.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add powdered sugar and beat together.
Add flour, salt, vanilla and nuts.
(Mixture is stiff.) Break into small pieces and roll in hand to make small balls.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 to 20 min.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm.

title: apple-raisin chutney
directions: Reduce sugar and vinegar by half and add raisins.
Add apples and cook for about 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add tomatoes. Cook for another couple minutes.
Strain juice off of apple/tomato mixture, reserve.
Put juice back into saucepan and reduce until it is a light syrup.
Allow syrup to cool.
Add tomato/apple mixture and combine with fresh mint.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook pasta shells as directed.
Let cool.
Mix all cheeses, except Mozzarella slices.
Fill each shell with cheese mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
Pour spaghetti sauce over shells; top with sliced Mozzarella and put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda and spices.
Combine vanilla, oil, sugar, egg and pumpkin and beat well.
Add flour mixture. Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls on a buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple and white grape salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in a bowl and set aside.
Add remaining ingredients with drained pineapple juice in a saucepan. Heat until mixture thickens; stir while heating.
Remove from heat and cool.
Pour over fruit.
Cover and chill.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add other ingredients and mix well.
Let stand and rise to double in size.
Knead and shape into rolls.
Let stand again and double in size.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: quick chips
directions: Wash potatoes.
Thinly slice potatoes and place on a greased platter in a single layer.
Sprinkle potatoes with salt. Microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Turn potatoes over and microwave for 1 minute or until chips are crispy and start to brown.

title: easy peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter.
Mix flour, baking powder, sugar and milk until smooth.
Pour melted butter into baking dish.
Add flour mixture. Add peaches.
Bake 45 minutes in 350° oven.
When almost done, sprinkle with cinnamon/sugar mixture.

title: haystacks
directions: Chop noodles lightly.
Melt butterscotch morsels over low heat, stirring constantly.
Pour in noodles and peanuts.
Drop by teaspoons onto wax paper.

title: diabetic chicken
directions: Wash chicken and skin it.
Place chicken in a 3-inch deep pan. Sprinkle chicken with seasoned salt.
Put margarine on chicken and sprinkle with parsley flakes.

title: parsley potato salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine all ingredients, except mayonnaise. Toss lightly.
Cover and refrigerate several hours.
A few hours before serving, add mayonnaise and stir to mix well.
Cover and keep salad chilled until served.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to buttermilk.
Mix dry ingredients well.
Add Crisco to dry ingredients, pinching with fingers until all the shortening is in tiny pieces.
Add liquids to dry ingredients; mix well.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator; use as needed.
Take out amount of dough needed; use enough flour to roll and cut out dough.
Melt oleo in large size 2-inch deep casserole dish.
Flop each biscuit on both sides in the oleo; place in dish.
Let rise at least 20 minutes and bake in a 425° oven until brown.

title: dried peaches
directions: Mix all together and let stand overnight.
Cook slowly until thick. Can in hot jars.
This is good for fried pies.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain pineapple chunks, reserving 1/4 cup of syrup.
Combine pineapple chunks, reserved pineapple syrup or orange sections and maraschino cherries.
Cover; chill thoroughly.
Just before serving fold in coconut.
Garnish with fresh mint leaves, if desired. Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate sheath cake
directions: Put cocoa and oil in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boil and pour over sugar and flour.
Stir; add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Bake in a 12 x 15-inch pan in a 400° oven for 25 minutes.
Pour following frosting over hot cake.

title: pantry casserole
directions: Drain all vegetables well.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan and put a layer of peas, asparagus, water chestnuts and mushrooms and pour mushroom soup over all.
If you like
a lot of seasoning, sprinkle with cayenne pepper.
Cover with grated cheese.
Melt butter and marinate bread in it.
Spread bread over cheese.
Bake at 350° until slightly browned, 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: taco-filled peppers
directions: In large skillet, brown the ground beef; drain.
Stir in the taco seasoning, kidney beans and salsa.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer for 5 minutes.
Cut peppers in half lengthwise; remove and discard seeds and stems.
Immerse peppers in boiling water for 3 minutes; drain.
Spoon about 1/2 cup meat mixture into each pepper half.
Place in an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Cover; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, or until peppers are crisp-tender and filling is heated through.
Top each with tomato, cheese and a dollop of sour cream.
Yields 4 servings.

title: smoked oyster and corn casserole
directions: In casserole to be used for baking, beat egg lightly with fork.
Add milk, corn and seasonings.
When mixed, scatter drained oysters over the top.
Sprinkle with 4 soda crackers, crushed. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: microwave apples
directions: Mix first four ingredients together. Mix with the sliced apples and put in a pyrex dish. Sprinkle red hots on top. Microwave on high for 8 minutes. Let cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: jiffy joes
directions: Crumble meat into casserole dish.
Stir in peppers and onion. Microwave on High for 5 to 6 minutes or until meat loses pink color when stirred.
Drain meat mixture well.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread in 9 x 13 greased pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 40 minutes, at 350°.
Cut into pieces about 1 x 2-inch.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat.
Add onion and garlic.
Cook until translucent. Blend into taco seasoning and olives.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Layer half of chips over bottom.
Add all meat mixture, then Mozzarella and sour cream.
Top with remaining chips.
Bake until heated through, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese and bake until melted.
Let stand 5 minutes before serving.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Line pie pan with pastry and sprinkle it with pecans.
Combine flour, salt and sugar in top of double boiler.
Add sour cream and cook until slightly thickened.
Add eggs, beat.
Remove from heat and add lemon rind, then pour mixture over pecans in pastry shell. Place in a 425° oven and cook about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake until filling is firm.

title: baked zucchini and rice
directions: Combine zucchini, rice, onion, garlic, salt and parsley in pan.
Add water, lower heat and cook 15 minutes.
Add eggs, cheese and
milk.
Bake
at
350° for 40 minutes or until set. Serves 6.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix water, sugar and cornstarch in saucepan.
Cook until thick; remove from heat, add gelatin and cool.
Place sliced strawberries in baked pie shell.
Pour cooled mixture over strawberries.
Place 4 tablespoons strawberries on top.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: soy sauce marinade for tri tip
directions: Can substitute powdered ginger for root (1/2 teaspoon).

title: oyster crackers snack
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients; add oyster crackers (11 to 14 ounces).
Stir every 15 minutes for 2 hours until oil is absorbed. Seal in Tupperware.

title: mushroom soup
directions: Cook scallions, garlic and sliced mushrooms in butter or oil until soft.
Add chicken broth, cream, sage and pepper.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: german chocolate pie
directions: Melt chocolate with butter over low heat, stirring until blended.
Remove from heat; gradually blend in milk.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt thoroughly.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in chocolate mixture.
Pour into pie shell.
Combine coconut and nuts; sprinkle over filling.
Bake at 375° for 45 to 50 minutes or until puffed and brown.
Cool 4 hours.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs one at a time, mixing well.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add cocoa and instant coffee.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, alternating with milk mixed with vanilla.
Beat well and pour batter into a greased tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broiled grapefruit
directions: Preheat broiler.
Cut grapefruit in half.
Section and remove seeds.
Sprinkle each half with a little brown sugar; dot with butter.
Broil for 10 minutes until golden brown and heated through.

title: hamburger-vegetable soup(yield: 8 servings)
directions: Brown meat in large skillet. Pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients. Bring mixture to a boil. Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 hour or until vegetables are tender. Stir occasionally. Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Combine crushed Oreos and melted butter and press into the bottom of an 8 1/2 x 11-inch pan.
Freeze in freezer.
Spoon 1/2 gallon softened ice cream over crust and refreeze.
Combine Eagle Brand milk, chocolate syrup and butter.
Bring to boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Let cool and pour over ice cream.
Freeze.
Top with Cool Whip and nuts, if desired, and keep frozen.

title: chicken salad ball
directions: In
electric
mixer,
combine first 6 ingredients; then add the
chicken, chopped eggs and onions. Mix well and chill; then shape
into a ball and roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serve with crackers, toast fingers or raw veggies.

title: peppermint icebox pudding
directions: *Use National Biscuit Company of Nabisco famous chocolate wafers.

title: mexican cheese chilli dip
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender, about 5 minutes. Stir in tomatoes, chillies, salt and pepper. Simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes. Cut cheese into 1/2-inch cubes. Stir in half and half when cheese begins to melt. Cook until cheese is melted. Cook, uncovered, 10 minutes. Serve in chafing dish with Fritos.
Makes 3 cups.

title: clam chowder
directions: Drain clams, reserve liquor.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
Fry bacon in saucepan.
Remove.
Saute onion in bacon drippings until tender.
Add clams, liquid, potatoes, celery salt, salt and pepper.
Cover.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat to low and simmer until potatoes are tender, 12 to 15 minutes.
Add milk and butter.
Heat until hot.
Stir in cracker crumbs.
Crumble bacon over individual servings.
Makes 6 servings.

title: codfish appetizers
directions: Saute cod in butter in medium saucepan.
Add parsley, ketchup and salt and pepper (as needed).
Remove cod and shred.
Mix flour and milk; add to saucepan.
Bring flour mixture to simmer over low heat; boil and stir 1 minute.
Add cod; heat through.
Remove from heat; stir in egg yolks.
Let cool, then refrigerate 30 minutes. Beat egg whites until stiff peaks form.
Add baking powder to cod mixture; stir well, then fold in egg whites.
Drop by spoonfuls into hot oil.
Remove when golden; drain well on paper towels. Serve warm.

title: luscious lamb
directions: Wash lamb in lemon juice and discard juice.
Cut 1/2-inch slits in lamb, one inch apart and insert garlic.
Mix dry ingredients and rub onto lamb.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes per pound.

title: easy beef and noodles
directions: Cook bacon in large skillet until crisp; remove bacon, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cut chicken in pieces.
Add seasonings and teriyaki sauce; let sit.
In baking dish, combine soups and rice.
Put soaked chicken on top of soups and rice.
Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover and cook 20 more minutes.

title: ice cream
directions: Beat eggs thoroughly.
Add milk, sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix all together thoroughly.
Pour in ice cream freezer and freeze until firm.

title: hasty fruit cobbler
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking powders and milk or cream.
(It will be the thickness of pancake batter.)
Dot a pan with butter. Pour mixture into pan.
Pour some juicy fruit on top of the batter.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: red christmas punch
directions: Stir together Jell-O, juices and water; just before serving, add sherbet.

title: 4-layer dessert
directions: Mix together and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: "spanakopita" - spinach pie
directions: Thaw frozen spinach and drain thoroughly.
Except for filo and melted butter, combine ingredients.
Leave egg whites for last, then fold them in.

title: mallow sauce
directions: Combine marshmallow cream and cream cheese in blender.
Process until smooth.
Serve over chocolate, lemon or pound cake. Also can be used as dip with assorted bite sized fresh fruit.
Yields 10 servings.

title: grandma shield's sugar cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together and drop by spoonful.
Sprinkle with sugar before you bake.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: texas-style chili
directions: Brown hamburger, drain.
Then add salt and pepper.
In blender, place tomatoes, tomato sauce and Ranch Style beans.
Blend.
Add this mixture to meat and simmer.
(Recipe may be doubled to accommodate a larger family.)
Serve with fresh chopped onions and grated Cheddar cheese on top.

title: coconut chicken bites
directions: These can be made the day before and just baked at serving time.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add pumpkin puree, vegetable oil, eggs and water.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into a well buttered 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: mayonnaise
directions: In small mixer bowl, beat egg yolk, mustard, sugar, salt, pepper and 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice on medium speed until blended.
Continue beating, adding salad oil drop by drop.
As mixture thickens, increase rate of addition.
Slowly stir in remaining lemon juice.
Beat thoroughly.
Chill.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage in
ungreased
skillet,
pour
off excess fat. Mix together sausage, rice, onions and celery.
Place in 2-quart casserole.	Can be	refrigerated.
When ready to bake, mix soy sauce and
water
together; pour over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use 9 x 13 pan.
Melt butter and brown sugar in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices and cherries in any pattern in pan and cover with walnuts.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks, add sugar and pineapple juice.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in beaten egg whites and pour on top of pineapple mixture in pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and invert on serving plate.
Cool completely.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Combine peas, onion, celery, cheese, pimento and eggs.
Season with salt and pepper.

title: crispy corn bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and mix well.
Beat egg and buttermilk and add to cornmeal mixture.
Stir well.
Do not beat. Melt shortening in a 425° skillet.
Pour hot shortening into batter and pour batter immediately into hot skillet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Put 1 cup of sugar over 2 coarsely cut, medium apples.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add margarine or butter (melted) and unbeaten egg.
Sift together the flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir well. Add raisins and nuts, if desired.
Bake in 8-inch square pan at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: fruit bowl
directions: Peel oranges and bananas; mix all together.
Dice apples very small with peel on.
Mix all and let set for 1 hour or more before eating.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix mashed sweet potatoes, sugar, eggs, vanilla, milk and butter together.
Add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Pour in a casserole dish.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease Bundt pan.
Mix ingredients together until well blended.
Pour into prepared pan.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: apricot banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar in a large mixer bowl.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Blend in lemon juice.
Mash bananas with fork; mix in.
Add dry ingredients; blend.
Stir in nuts and apricots.
Pour batter into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan, well-greased. Bake at 325° for 70 to 80 minutes, or until loaf tests done. Makes 1 loaf.

title: mama's tuna casserole
directions: Make macaroni and cheese according to box directions. Add tuna and mushroom soup. Mix and pour in a 9 x 13 baking dish. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: key lime pie
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix with condensed milk and 1/2 tub Cool Whip until smooth.
Add lime juice until it is as tart as you like, then put in pie shell.
Top with remaining Cool Whip. Garnish with lime slices.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: chocolate chip pancakes
directions: Blend Bisquick, milk and eggs until smooth.
Add sugar, vanilla and salt.
Mix well.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Bake on hot greased griddle.
Serve with butter and maple syrup.
Yields 12 to 15 pancakes.

title: coconut-black walnut pound cake
directions: Combine sugar, salad oil, and egg; beat well.
Combine dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture alternately with buttermilk beating well after each addition.
Stir in nuts, coconut, and flavoring.

title: christmas mince bars(makes approximately 4 dozen)
directions: With electric mixer at low speed, blend gingerbread mix, mincemeat and egg.
Increase speed and beat 1 minute.
Pour batter into a lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Spread mixture evenly.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly pressed with fingers.
Let cake cool completely in pan or wire rack.
Using sharp knife, cut into 1 x 3-inch bars.
Sift confectioners sugar over cake before serving, if desired.

title: ground beef-corn casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add tomato sauce, corn, soup, chili powder, salt and pepper; mix well.
Simmer for 10 minutes. Add macaroni.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is melted.

title: sour cream cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix meal, oil, eggs and corn together. Fold in sour cream and cheese.
Bake in greased 9
x 13-inch pan for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: butter-mint jello salad
directions: In a pan, bring pineapple and juice to a boil.
Add gelatin. Stir to dissolve.
Stir in marshmallows into cooled gelatin. Refrigerate 1 hour.
Fold into gelatin along with crushed mints. Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream.
Makes 12 servings.

title: vegetable turkey pot pie
directions: Put peas and carrots, water and butter in saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Cook gently for 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in onions in cream sauce.
Add turkey.
Pour into a 2-quart casserole dish and bake for 15 minutes at 350°.
Prepare stuffing mix as directed on package.
Spoon around edge and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat. Add flour, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sauce is thickened and bubbly; stir in salt.
Set aside.

title: fudge pie
directions: Blend oleo and chocolate.
Melt these together.
Add sugar, eggs (beat in one at a time), flour and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into a well-greased 9-inch pie plate and bake at 325° for 25 minutes.
Cut before it cools completely.

title: mocha walnut brownies
directions: In a saucepan over low heat, melt the chocolate and butter; stir until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar and mix well. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt; add to the chocolate mixture just until combined.
Stir in walnuts.

title: gayla's nappa cabbage salad
directions: Crunch Ramen noodles into small pieces.
Saute noodles, sunflower seeds and almonds in a little bit of oil on low (the noodles burn easily).
Stir.
Mix together with cabbage and onions.

title: shrimp cheese spread
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate at least 2 to 4 hours and serve.

title: poor man's lobster
directions: Cover fish with cold water and vinegar.
Bring to boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Drain and serve with hot butter and paprika.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pecans.
Chill and roll into ball, then roll in chopped pecans.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken thighs in yogurt
directions: Heat a large frying pan; add 2 tablespoons oil.
Add garlic and onion; saute until onion is tender.
Do not brown.
Heat second frying pan; add 1 tablespoon oil.
Brown chicken on both sides.
Remove to 13 x 9-inch glass baking dish.
When onions are tender, stir in yogurt and parsley off the heat.
Pour yogurt mixture over chicken thighs and bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: pizza dip
directions: Cover bottom of serving dish with cream cheese.
Top with chili sauce.
Separately layer green pepper, red onion, mushrooms and Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with thinly sliced bread rounds. Serves 12.

title: cutout cookies
directions: Cream together and refrigerate overnight.
Cut out and bake at 325°.
Frost with Betty Crocker frosting.

title: lorna's cranberry salad
directions: Bring gingerale to boil, add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: fried okra
directions: Beat egg.
Add milk, flour, salt, pepper and enough corn meal to make thick dip.
Pour this over okra and mix well with fork. Fry in oleo in skillet over medium heat until brown and done, about 25 minutes.
Stir often.

title: walnut apple crisp
directions: Set oven to 350°.
In shallow, 2-quart baking dish, combine apples, water and lemon juice.
In large bowl, combine brown sugar, flour, cinnamon and salt; mix well.
Cut in butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Stir in walnuts and oats. Sprinkle evenly over apples.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill for several hours or overnight.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 1/2 cup juice; set pineapple aside.
In small bowl or cup, combine reserved
juice, the soy sauce, vinegar, and cornstarch, stirring until cornstarch is dissolved; set aside.
Heat oil over high heat.
Add pork; stir-fry until well browned, 5-10 minutes.
Stir in peppers and reserved pineapple.
Add reserved juice mixture; bring to a boil. Reduce heat to low; simmer, stirring occasionally, until pork is cooked through, 5-10 minutes.
Serve immediately.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Add remaining ingredients.
Heat oven to 300°.
Place formed cookies in oven, cut oven off, and leave cookies in overnight.

title: french onion bread
directions: Soften yeast
in
water.
Combine
shortening
and
hot water in large bowl.
Stir
in sugar, salt and dry onion soup. Add yeast.
Gradually add flour to form stiff dough.
Knead on floured board until smooth and satiny, about 5 minutes.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together (cut cream cheese in tiny pieces when mixing).
Pour in greased iron skillet.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: yummy cheese soup
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in large saucepan.
Simmer, loosely covered, for 15 minutes.
Blend margarine and flour in saucepan. Whisk in milk gradually until smooth.
Add cheese.
Cook over low heat until melted, stirring constantly.
Add salt and pepper.

title: chicken breast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in casserole dish.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° in preheated oven 45 minutes to 1 hour or until bubbling.
Cook, uncovered.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in a shallow heat-proof casserole dish. Add shrimp and toss to coat. Spread shrimp in a single layer. Broil shrimp 4-inches from heat 3 to 4 minutes. Turn shrimp and broil an additional 3 to 4 minutes or until lightly browned. Sprinkle with parsley.

title: peanut butter jumbos
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease cookie sheets.
Cream butter, sugar, peanut butter and eggs in a large bowl.
Blend in soda, vanilla and oats until well mixed.
Stir in chocolate chips and candy.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Mix in cheese, soup, corn, onion and milk.
Put into 9 x 13-inch pan (greased).
Put Tater Tots on top. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients together.
Add dressing and refrigerate overnight.

title: corn casserole
directions: Drain Mexicorn and mix all ingredients together in a large bowl.
The red pepper really adds to the taste, so use enough to enhance the flavor.
Pour into a buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° until it is slightly brown.
Enjoy!

title: ice cream cookies
directions: Cream the butter and sugar together; add the egg and extracts. Beat until the mixture is thoroughly blended.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Divide the dough in half.
Add melted chocolate to one part.
Add a little more flour to the white part of the dough if necessary.
Roll the white part into a thin rectangular sheet; spread with the chocolate mixture; and roll it as if it were a jelly roll.
Chill.
Cut into thin slices.
Place on a greased baking sheet and bake in a hot oven (400°) for 7 minutes.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Dice and cook chicken.
Dip tortillas (10 to 12) in hot chicken broth and line bottom of casserole pan.
Add other ingredients in order.
Sprinkle top with cheese.
Bake for 55 minutes at 375°.

title: lime pie
directions: Melt butter in large skillet; stir in coconut, flour, sugar, pecans and salt.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is golden.
Place immediately in 9-inch pan, using back of spoon to press onto sides and bottom.
Completely thaw a small can of frozen limeade.
Completely thaw a large carton of Cool Whip. Combine limeade and Cool Whip with Eagle Brand milk.
Pour into pie crust and chill until set.

title: cream of tomato soup
directions: Combine tomato sauce and milk; bring to a boil.
Add salt, sugar, butter and soda, which will cause quick foaming, so be sure to have a vessel big enough to contain the volume.
Last add 1 small can condensed cream with enough water to make 1 1/2 cups.

title: rhubarb-jello-jam
directions: Let rhubarb and sugar stand overnight.
Cook 15 minutes or until done.
Add jello and stir until dissolved. Pour in glasses and seal.

title: winter slaw
directions: Pour over vegetables hot.
Let stand 12 hours.
Cold pack just until jars are hot and sealed.
Boil about 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice
directions: Add Velveeta cheese to broccoli while warm.
Add the can of mushroom soup to the rice.
Saute one small onion in butter and mix all ingredients together and bake at 350° until hot and bubbling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: brenda's famous banana split pie(no cooking)
directions: First Layer:
Mix melted butter with Oreos.
Press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Combine cucumbers, onions and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then wash off salt.
Combine remaining ingredients and let it come to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions.
Let it come to a boil, then pack in hot jars.
Makes 10 pints.

title: homemade burritos
directions: Sort, wash and cook brown beans in crock-pot until tender. Add taco powder and mix well.
Drain off juice and mash beans or can leave whole.
Spoon bean mixture onto flour tortilla according to how much you want, then add ingredients listed or according to your taste.

title: red beet soup
directions: Brown shank or neck pieces in a large pot with the oil.
Turn over and add onions.
Lower heat and cook until onions soften (10 minutes).
Add salt and spices.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Lower heat and simmer uncovered until meat is tender (about 1 1/2 hours).
Wash beets.
Peel and cut roots and add to soup. Clean leaves and stems discarding tough or damaged leaves.
Cut stems in 1-inch pieces.
When beets are almost tender, add stems. Continue cooking until beets and stems are tender.
The meat should almost fall off bones.

title: impossible zucchini tomato pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate 1 1/2 inches deep.
Sprinkle zucchini, tomato, onion and cheese into the pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, about 15 seconds in a blender on high or for about 1 minute with mixer.
Pour into pie plate.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean, about 30 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 6 servings.

title: baked chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken until tender.
Cut into bite size pieces and place in casserole.
Dilute soups with the milk.
Pour over chicken.
Mix stuffing, melted margarine and chicken broth.
Pour over chicken and soup mixture.
Bake for about 30 minutes in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: raisin pie
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients, stirring constantly over medium heat until thick.
Pour into pastry-lined 9-inch pie plate. Moisten edge; adjust top crust or lattice crust.
Flute edge. Bake in hot oven at 400° about 35 or 40 minutes.

title: maple syrup
directions: Combine corn syrup, brown sugar and water.
Heat until sugar dissolves, stirring as needed.
Remove from heat and add maple flavoring.
Butter may be added at this time if desired.

title: sunny banana pie
directions: Place sliced bananas in pie crust.
Add 1/2 cup milk to cream cheese; mix well.
Add pudding mix and rest of milk and beat with mixer for 1 minute.
Pour into crust and chill.

title: bake rice pork chops
directions: Season chops; salt and pepper.	Brown them in frypan.
Place in baking dish and cover with rice.
Mix soup and milk together. Pour over chops and rice; be sure to cover rice with liquid. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Can also do with chicken.

title: cabbage with cheese
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling salted water until tender, about 6 to 9 minutes.
Drain; add cream and cheese.
Place over low heat; stir until cheese melts and coats cabbage.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate chip banana cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, salt and sour cream.
Add bananas and vanilla.
Mix well.
Combine flour, baking soda and baking powder.
Add to butter mixture and mix until well combined. Add chocolate chips.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.

title: warm spinach salad
directions: Cut bacon into 1/2 inch pieces, pan fry, drain and save drippings.
In a bowl add egg, salt, vinegar, and water and cornstarch, stir well.
Add this mixture to pan drippings and heat slowly until mixture is smooth and thick.

title: curry chicken stars
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Unroll dough and shape into 2 1/2-inch squares. Make 1-inch cuts diagonally from the corners toward center.
Place 1 heaping teaspoonful filling into center of each square.
To form stars, fold in every other dough tip toward center.
Bake on greased baking sheet in 350° oven for 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 appetizers.

title: barbecued ribs
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour over ribs.
Bake at 350° until done.
Baste if necessary.
I never measure, just pinch and dump so use your own judgment and enjoy!

title: chicken and ham
directions: Wrap each piece chicken with a ham slice and then to that add a cheese slice.
Place in a large baking dish.
Mix together mushrooms, mushroom soup and wine.
Pour over chicken.
Put almonds on top.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with wild rice, sauteed, mushrooms and onions.
(Or can serve with noodles and potatoes.)

title: five-cup salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill several hours or overnight before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Line pie plate with pastry.
Set in refrigerator until ready to be filled.
Combine sugar, 2 tablespoons of the flour and salt. Add slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add rhubarb.
Sprinkle 1 tablespoon flour over bottom of crust; fill crust with rhubarb mixture.
Set in preheated oven and bake.
Beat 2 egg whites until stiff and add 4 tablespoons of sugar for meringue.
Spread on pie when done and brown in oven at 325°.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Coarsely crush cookies.
Save 1/4 cup of crumbs for topping. To remaining crumbs, add melted butter and mix well.
Press into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on raw vegetables or potato chips.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix together.
Add handful of shredded cheese into batter. Grease muffin pan.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes about 6 biscuits.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook and debone 1 large fryer.
In a large bowl, dice chicken and add the celery, onion, English peas, eggs, pimento, broth and soup; add salt and pepper to taste.
Mix all together and place in 1 large or 2 medium casserole dishes and top with the following: 1 stick oleo (melted), 1 1/2 cups milk and 1 1/2 cups self-rising flour.
Pour over chicken mixture and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until light brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Cream together shortening, peanut butter and eggs until fluffy.
Combine flour and butter mixtures with milk and vanilla.
Form dough into balls; roll in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and place candy kiss in each cookie. Return to oven for 2 to 5 minutes.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown ground meat and drain fat.
Stir in 1/2 cup salsa. Spread 1/4 cup salsa in a 10-inch pie plate; top with tostadas or halved taco shells.
Top with half of each of the beans, meat mixture, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat layers; cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with lettuce, remaining salsa and additional sour cream.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chow mein casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
Add rice and remaining ingredients.
Turn into a 3-quart covered casserole and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve over chow mein noodles.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Cut the chicken into small pieces.
Season with garlic powder and seasoning.
Dip into egg and milk batter.
Then bread the chicken with the bread crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown. Serve immediately.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole(quick and easy!)
directions: Brown sausage and crumble into small pieces.
Prepare wild rice according to package directions.
Mix the sausage, rice and sour cream together and pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: surprise puffs
directions: Mix ingredients into a good thick batter.
Dip wieners into batter and fry in deep fat until golden brown.

title: polish dogs
directions: Bake sausage in oven at 350° for 10 minutes.
Mix on top of stove bell peppers, onions, butter or margarine, soy sauce, salt and black pepper to taste.
Mix well together until tender.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Prepare chocolate cake in two 9-inch pans.
Prepare chocolate pudding in two separate bowls and chill, preferably for a few hours prior to making cake.

title: outdoor burgers
directions: Add all ingredients; mix lightly.
Shape in 4 patties, 1/2-inch thick.
Broil over hot coals, 5 to 6 minutes.
Turn and broil 5 minutes or desired doneness.
Makes 4 patties, 1/2-inch thick.

title: poppy seed filling for kolaches
directions: Mix flour in sugar.
Heat milk in pot and when it boils add remaining
ingredients and cook slowly until it thickens. Cool well.
When making poppy seed kolaches, instead of making balls, spread
the
golf ball size dough out flat and oblong. Place about 1 heaping teaspoonful of filling in center.
Bring the
dough
up to enclose the filling and pinch dough together making
an
oblong roll.
Put
pinched side of kolache to the greased
pan.
Brush lightly with melted margarine.
Let rise in a
warm place.
Bake at 350° about 15 or 20 minutes.
While warm, brush with melted margarine.
Sprinkle with some sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased 9 x 13 pan. Refrigerate at least 2 hours or overnight. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set and brown.

title: creole shrimp and okra
directions: Combine bacon, onion, green pepper, garlic, seafood seasoning and red pepper.
Cover with plastic wrap; cook in a microwave-safe dish for 5 minutes, stirring once after 3 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes with juice, tomato paste and water.
Cover; heat in microwave on High for 8 minutes.
Add okra; stir in and heat for 5 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cover; let stand.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: no-bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, milk, butter and cocoa.
Bring to a full boil. Boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter, oats and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: stuffed boneless chicken breasts
directions: Split the breasts and stuff with broccoli and shredded cheese. Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 400° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat after each addition.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add alternately with buttermilk.
Add extract and juice; beat until satin texture.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 325°.
Very good.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Marinate shrimp in Italian dressing for 15 to 30 minutes. Shake in fish fry.
Cook in hot oil until golden brown.

title: beet salad(rodbetsalat)
directions: Combine beets and apples.
Stir in mayonnaise.
Chill well. Serve with cold meat or fish.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: sweet meatballs
directions: Combine bread crumbs, onion, milk, egg and ground beef.
Roll into meatballs and brown.
In saucepan, combine sauce, water, brown sugar, mustard and vinegar.
When sugar is melted, add cooked meatballs and let simmer.

title: italian dip
directions: Combine cottage cheese with next 3 ingredients.
Mix well. Add dry dressing and mayonnaise.
Mix.
Serve at room temperature.

title: fish fillets au gratin
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
In small bowl, combine all ingredients except fish.
Place fish on individual squares of greased foil. Spoon crumb mixture over fish.
Seal securely and bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chips and nuts.
Fold these in last.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 65 minutes.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes, and remove.

title: taco meat
directions: Fry the ground beef and water in skillet until meat is half-cooked. Sprinkle flour over meat and stir until well mixed. Add the onion, tomato sauce, garlic, chili powder, cumin and pepper. Add salt to taste.

title: savory pepper steak
directions: Cut beef round steak in 1/2-inch strips.
Coat with mixture of all-purpose flour, salt and pepper.
In large skillet brown strips in 1/4 cup hot shortening.

title: smooth 'n creamy frosting
directions: Combine pudding mix and sugar in bowl.
Beat slowly with rotary mixer or at lowest speed on electric mixer until well blended, about 1 minute.
Fold in whipped topping.
Spread on cake at once.
Makes enough for two 9-inch layers.

title: easy chicken ala king
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a heavy saucepan; cook over low heat for 10 minutes, stirring often.
Serve over rice.
Yields 2 servings.

title: cousin patti's salad
directions: Break up noodles (save seasoning).

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Boil onions for 1 minute; drain.
Prepare in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Combine eggs, cream, salt and pepper.
Pour over onions. Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Serves 6.

title: white bean soup and sausage
directions: Brown sausage in oil. When brown, remove and cool, then slice. Add ham, onions, carrots and celery to pan. Cook and brown for 8 to 10 minutes. Mash 1 can of beans with fork; add broth and all beans and sausage. Cover and simmer 20 minutes. Let it rest for 10 minutes or so, then serve with cornbread.

title: creamy broccoli-raisin salad
directions: Remove broccoli leaves and cut off tough ends of stalks; discard.
Wash broccoli thoroughly and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Combine broccoli, raisins, onion and half of bacon; toss gently. Set aside.
Combine cream cheese and remaining ingredients in a blender or food processor; process until smooth.
Pour over broccoli mixture, stirring well.
Chill 3 hours.
Sprinkle with remaining bacon.

title: jam bars
directions: Mix sugar and nuts well.
Add margarine and flour.
Turn onto board.
Make a well and add yolks; mix.
Use about 2/3 of this dough to make bottom layer in jelly roll pan.
Roll to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Spread with jam.
Use remaining dough to make cross bars on top by making thin rolls of dough and place these crisscross to each other on top of the jam layer.
Bake in moderate oven until light brown.
Slice into rectangles.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Butter 9 x 13 baking dish. Mix flour, dry mustard, and melted butter. Layer 1/3 bread, ham, cheese and then sprinkle with the flour, mustard, butter mixture. Repeat layers. Beat eggs and milk and pour over casserole. Cover and refrigerate overnight. Bake uncovered at 350 for one hour.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs and sugar. Add flour, baking powder and salt; mix well. Stir in nuts and chips. Line a 9 x 13 cake pan with wax paper. Pour into pan (you may have to add a little hot water to make it pour). Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: herb cheese crescents
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Unroll dough.
Separate dough at perforations to make 8 triangles.
Halve each triangle lengthwise. Spread 1 teaspoon cheese on each triangle.
Roll up from wide end of triangle.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix peanut butter, cracker crumbs, margarine and confectioners sugar.
Put into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spread melted chocolate on top.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into bars.

title: boston brown bread
directions: Soak bread crumbs in milk for one hour.
Rub the crumbs through a sieve and reserve milk.
Sift dry ingredients together; add crumbs and molasses.
Stir in raisins and milk.
Stir well and pour into a well-greased mold.
Fill 2/3 full.
Cover top tightly. Steam on trivet in deep kettle with boiling water.
The water should be 2/3 the way up on molds and more added as needed.
Cover the kettle to boil and do this for 3 hours.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients except cream cheese.
(I add either red or
green food coloring.) Spread over cream cheese block. Serve with crackers.

title: low-fat chicken salad
directions: Skin, debone and shred chicken breast.
Combine all ingredients.
Use as salad or in sandwiches.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Cream cheese and butter together.
Work in flour with red pepper.
Roll thin; cut into strips of desired size.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: strawberry clouds
directions: Cube cake in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix in Cool Whip.
Layer over cake. Slice strawberries, mix with glaze.
Pour over cake mixture.

title: cases tortilla casserole
directions: First Layer:
Line 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with corn tortillas.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on.
When cool, put in a large bowl. Splash potatoes with vinegar.
Chop eggs and add.
Add both types of olives, garlic salt, onions, celery seed, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix all with hands.

title: harvest muffins
directions: *Made with 2 1/3 cups rolled oats processed in blender 2 to 3 minutes.

title: scottish trifle
directions: Break sponge cake in large bowl.
May be soaked in sherry. Cover with fruit and Jell-O (mix according to package). Refrigerate.
When set, mix custard according to package.
Let cool.
Pour over cold cake mixture.
Refrigerate.
When set, whip the cream and pour over cake mixture.
Decorate with 100's and 1,000's or chocolate chips/flakes.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Sprinkle rice in a large buttered casserole.
Place chicken over rice.
Sprinkle soup mix over chicken.
Pour chicken broth over entire mixture; cover.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: stew
directions: Mix soup, water and flour until smooth.
Add remaining ingredients; cover.
Bake at 275° for 4 to 5 hours.

title: cinnamon popcorn
directions: Place popped corn in oiled 9 x 13-inch pan.
In heavy pan, melt margarine.
Stir in sugar, cinnamon and salt.
Stir and beat until sugar melts and is dissolved.
Pour over the popcorn; toss to coat.
Bake in preheated oven at 300° for 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: william's peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together well.
Shape dough into balls. Flatten dough with a fork, making a crisscross design.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes, or until done.
Watch these cookies carefully; they burn easily.

title: breakfast pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray pie plate with non-stick cooking spray.
Cook and stir sausage and onion in skillet, until sausage is brown.
Drain.
Spread in a pie plate.
In a mixing bowl, beat milk, Bisquick, eggs, salt and pepper on high for 1 minute.
Pour into pie plate over top of sausage.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake until a knife inserted in the center comes out clean and cheese is melted (about 5 minutes).

title: applesauce cake
directions: Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: almond flavored cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into balls.
Cover with powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: golden pound cake
directions: Mix sugar and softened butter until creamy.
Add 2 eggs and 1 cup flour until all flour is mixed.
Add flavorings and beat until well mixed.
Bake in Bundt pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in baking dish.
Cover with topping and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in 1/2 cup water for 7 minutes.
Drain well. Place croutons in 8 x 8 inch square pan. Mix butter with 1/2 cup warm water and pour over croutons.
Blend until moist.
Arrange broccoli on top of croutons.
Blend soup with 1/2 cup water and pour over broccoli.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 300 for 30 minutes.

title: chile con carne:  charles kromas
directions: Braise suet in pan (or put oil in pan).
Add garlic, chile pepper and minced beef; simmer for 1 hour.
Add salt and pepper. Add beans and cook (simmer) until beans are heated through.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Thinly slice lettuce and place into a large bowl.
Chop celery, green pepper and onions.
Place in layers on lettuce.
Add peas.
Mix mayo and sugar together.
Cover salad completely with this mixture.
Sprinkle on shredded cheese.
Add bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 8 hours.
Serve cold.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread browned ground beef into a 9 x 13 baking dish.
Cover with tater tots.
Pour soups over the top or tater tots.
Bake 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: tapioca
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients, then add the remaining ingredients.
When cold, add whipped topping to suit your taste.

title: grape hull pie
directions: Pour grape hulls into pie shells.
Cover with sugar.
Dot with butter.
Cover with pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy it plain or with whipped cream.

title: chocolate gravy
directions: Ham meat doesn't fry much, so put grease in with it when you fry it.
Take the meat out and pour the grease in a bowl. Sprinkle sugar on the hot frying pan.
Pour about 1/2 cup of water on skillet.
It will fry like lightning, so just cook it until it is hot, about 1 minute.
Pour it over the grease in the bowl and that is where you get "red eye."

title: beef pepper steak
directions: Preheat oil in electric skillet, uncovered, at 325°.
Add meat and brown.
Remove to serving dish.
Add onion and pepper slices to skillet; cook until just tender.

title: coconut bread
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and stir well.	Combine egg, milk and vanilla; stir well.
Stir into flour mixture.
Cover and let stand for 15 minutes.
Pour into a greased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes.	Test with pick.
Let cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool on rack.	Makes 1 loaf.

title: lutzen raisin rye bread
directions: Combine water, salt, brown sugar, molasses, shortening and yeast.
Stir together and let stand 5 minutes or until yeast is working well.
Stir in flours, adding and working in enough flour to form a dough that leaves the sides of the bowl.
Knead it working in raisins until dough is smooth and elastic.
Cover and let rise overnight in cool place.
Knead dough and shape into 3 loaves.
Let rise in warm place until dough rises about 1-inch above edge of pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool pans 10 minutes.

title: quick pudding
directions: Beat together butter, flour and egg.
Add milk.
Pour mixture over apples which are placed in a baking dish.
Bake for about one hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Beat together thoroughly the eggs, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in peanut butter and Karo syrup.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 225° and bake 30 minutes more.

title: nuddy buddy pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in large bowl.
Beat well.
Pour in crusts.
Drizzle syrup and sprinkle with nuts.
Freeze.
Makes 3 pies.

title: black walnut oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together the Crisco, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Mix together and add the remaining ingredients. Shape into rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper.
Chill thoroughly in refrigerator overnight or for several hours.
Slice 1/2 inch thick.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: sour cream dressing
directions: Mix all together and let come to a good boil. When cold, add salt to taste.
Can be doubled to keep.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Mix ingredients (except chips and cheese); bring to boil. Crush tortilla chips in bottom of each bowl; add soup.
Top with crushed tortilla chips and shredded cheese.

title: quickie peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in a deep baking dish (12 x 12 x 2-inch).
Mix flour, sugar, milk and baking powder together.
Pour over (evenly) melted margarine (do not stir).
Place peaches all around evenly. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
(Can use any kind of fruit.)

title: spinach casserole
directions: Mix spinach, sour cream and soup mix.
Put in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with stuffing mix, then butter.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes (until browned).
Add artichoke hearts, if desired, to garnish.

title: fresh butter beans
directions: Put fatback in pot and cover with water.
Boil for 30 minutes. Add beans, salt to taste and sugar.
Cook until beans are tender. Don't overcook!

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil jumbo shells in water; drain.
Mix Ricotta cheese, broccoli or spinach, bread crumbs, parsley, egg, Mozzarella cheese, 1 tablespoon tomato sauce, oregano, black pepper and basil to stuff shells.
In a casserole dish make a layer of sauce.
Stuff the shells and line up in dish.
Make another layer (or not).
Top with lots of sauce and thin slices of Mozzarella cheese.
(You can put the Mozzarella cheese on top 40 minutes later, if you want.)
Tent with tinfoil.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Use something under it if glass casserole, so bottom doesn't cook too much.
Voila.

title: easy sugar jumbles
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Sift in remaining ingredients and stir.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
You may add nuts, raisins, chocolate chips, gum drops, etc.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: dianne's corn pudding
directions: Blend sugar, cornstarch, salt and eggs.
Add corn and evaporated milk.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into shallow, buttered casserole dish and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until well set.
Can be reheated if covered with foil.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Brown meat with salt and pepper, garlic and spices.
Line bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish with flour tortillas (broken into small pieces).
Drain meat and place on top.
Add chopped onions, beans and 1 cup Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Cover with 1/2 of cheese.
Add another layer of tortillas.

title: broiled cheese and bacon fingers
directions: Place cheese, bacon and onion in food processor and process. Add Worcestershire sauce.
Spread on thick slices of Italian bread, crackers or English muffins.
Broil until cheese is melted and bacon is cooked.

title: lila's bran muffins
directions: Mix cereal and boiling water and set aside to cool.
Mix sugar, oil, eggs, buttermilk, soda, flour and salt together with cooled cereal mixture.
Add all-bran cereal and raisins.
Pour into muffin cups and bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Snipped dried apricots, chopped fresh apple or chopped cranberries may be added for half the raisins.
Chopped nuts are a good addition. This keeps in the refrigerator for 4 weeks, or bake all at once and freeze.

title: healthy crockpot soup
directions: Combine all the above ingredients in a large crock pot.
Cook on slow heat all day.
Serve hot.

title: sausage balls
directions: In mixing bowl, combine uncooked sausage with cheese.
Mix until well blended.
Add Bisquick and blend well.
Shape into 1 inch balls.
Place 1 inch apart on a baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes, or until nicely brown.
Serve hot.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Heat oven to 300° to 350°.
Bake about 1 hour.
Top with whipping cream, warm or cool cake or with ice cream.

title: pineapple surprise
directions: Bake cake until done.
While cake is still hot, pour crushed pineapple on top with juice, then cook vanilla pudding and pour on top.
Chill 1 hour or until cool.
Then put Cool Whip, coconut and cherries on top and put in refrigerator for 30 minutes.
Any leftover cake should be kept in refrigerator.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together white sugar, brown sugar and butter.
Add eggs, vanilla, oats and flour.
Mix these ingredients with creamed mixture.
Add chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: pastor bill's peanut butter and jelly sandwich
directions: Apply a large amount of peanut butter to bottom slice of bread. Top with preserves.
Place top slice of bread on top and cut in half diagonally.

title: sweet zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Cream with sugar, oil and vanilla. Mix and sift all dry ingredients; add to sugar mixture.
Beat. Add zucchini and nuts; mix.
Pour into two loaf pans that have been greased and floured.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes. Let cool for 5 minutes on wire rack and dump from pans.
Mmmm, good.

title: zucchini chinese style
directions: Cook bacon until crisp; remove from skillet.
Add sliced zucchini to bacon drippings in skillet; toss to coat.
Pour chicken broth over zucchini.
Cover and steam 4 to 5 minutes until squash is almost tender.
Blend cornstarch, m.s.g. and salt with cold water; stir into zucchini mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Turn into serving dish; garnish with crumbled bacon.
Serves 4 to 5.
(Note:
have made without bacon, just using chicken broth.)

title: hot chocolate mix
directions: In a large pan, mix dry ingredients thoroughly.
Store in airtight container.
Use 1/3 to 1/2 cup mix for each cup and fill with boiling water.
Yields 16 to 20 cups.

title: lo-cal rice pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in 2 lightly greased custard cups.
Bake, uncovered, at 325°, stirring every 15 minutes for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 2 servings.
One serving equals 115 calories.

title: cheese ball
directions: I add garlic salt, black pepper and Tabasco sauce.
Mix together and roll in chopped pecans.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix all together in large bowl.
Spread into large greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost with Betty Crocker cream cheese frosting.

title: homemade sausage
directions: *Or use enough for personal taste.

title: vegeburgers
directions: Mix all ingredients; make into patties.
Brown slowly in a nonstick frypan until done.
Serve hot on a bun with a slice of tomato, onion and lettuce.
Makes 8 to 10 patties.

title: cheddar soup
directions: Saute carrots, celery, onion and pepper for about 5 minutes in butter.
Stir in flour until pasty.
Add chicken broth while stirring constantly.
Add cheese slowly until melted.
Add evaporated milk, salt and pepper.
If you want a smooth creamy soup, puree first 4 ingredients before mixing with flour, etc. Add 1/8 cup sherry just before serving.

title: yogurt pie
directions: Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Fold into pie shell.
Freeze until set (about 3 hours).
Allow to thaw slightly before serving.
Keep leftovers refrigerated or refreeze.
This dessert is easy, light and fast.

title: fresh apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.

Mix sugar, flour, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt.	Stir in apples. Turn into pastry-lined plate; dot with margarine.	Bake until crust is brown and juice begins to bubble through slits in crust, 40 to 50 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine rice, soups and water.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Top with the chicken breasts (skinned).
Salt, pepper and butter the chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: layered cookies
