directions: Combine melted butter and graham cracker crumbs.
Pat evenly into bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan coated with Pam.
Over the graham cracker mixture, layer the coconut, chocolate pieces and nuts or substituted ingredients.
Pour the sweetened condensed milk over everything and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until done.

title: corn-on-the-cob(microwave)
directions: Hush corn and remove silk.
Wrap each ear in waxed paper; twist ends.
Arrange 2-inches apart in microwave.
Microwave on High (100%) 5 minutes; turn corn over and rearrange ears. Microwave until tender, 4 to 6 minutes.
Let stand 3 minutes. Serve with margarine or butter, salt and pepper.

title: pink cloud
directions: Mix together and refrigerate.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; chop and place in casserole dish.
Mix together the soups and sour cream.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cracker crumbs and cover with butter.
Bake at 350° until casserole bubbles.

title: salad dressing
directions: Mix all together in blender or shaker.

title: very easy casserole
directions: Brown hamburger in ovenproof dish.
Season as desired.
I use salt, pepper, garlic powder, onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Stir in vegetables, including liquid.
Simmer until most liquid is gone.
Place biscuits on top of meat and vegetables.
Bake in oven at 425° until biscuits are browned, approximately 10 to 15 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6 people.

title: peasant bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in one cup of warm water.
Combine flour, salt, sugar and yeast mixture in a large bowl.
Add the remaining 1 cup of water and stir well.
(Optional:
Add 1 cup washed and drained raisins.)
Let rise until doubled (about 1 hour).

title: cleo's pumpkin cake
directions: Sift together, flour, salt, soda, and cinnamon.
Add oil, eggs sugar, and pumpkin to flour mixture.
Mix well.
Bake in sheet pan 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chinese meatballs(6 servings)
directions: Mix all together.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Saute until brown. Serve with sweet/sour sauce and white rice.

title: icebox rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
In a large bowl, add sugar, salt and almost 1/2 flour.
Beat.
Add eggs and shortening.
Beat.
Add rest of the flour.
Knead and put in a large greased bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough and cut out for rolls. Place in greased (oil or shortening) pans.
Cook at 350°.
Brush tops with butter or margarine when you take them out of the oven.

title: foxy franks appetizers
directions: In a skillet, combine preserves, vinegar, tomato sauce and cooking sherry. Cut franks into 1-inch pieces and add to sauce. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve hot with wooden picks.

title: wilton buttercream icing
directions: Cream the butter and shortening with electric mixer.
Add vanilla.
Gradually add sugar, one cup at a time, beating well on medium speed.
Scrape sides and bottom of bowl often.
When all sugar has been mixed in, icing will appear dry.
Add milk and beat at high speed until light and fluffy.
Keep covered with damp cloth until ready to use.
Refrigerate when not in use.
Keeps for up to 2 weeks in airtight container.
Rewhip before using.
I double this for large cakes.

title: cheese strata
directions: *Velveeta cheese, diced onions, green peppers, tomatoes, mushrooms, cooked bacon (5 to 7 strips), cooked sausage (6 to 10 pieces), etc.

title: dirt pie
directions: Cream together cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Mix pudding as directed on package.
Add to the cream cheese mixture. Fold in cool whip.
Crush oreo cookies in blender. Alternate layers of cream cheese mixture and crushed Oreos in a new flower pot.
Top layer should be Oreos.
Decorate with artificial flowers and gummy worms if desired.

title: hot baked cheese dip
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish, layer softened cream cheese, chili (drain off fat), Monterey Jack cheese and jalapeno cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Serve with taco chips, corn chips, etc.

title: sunday roast
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place roast in dish.
Pour ingredients over roast and cover.
Marinate 24 hours in refrigerator.
Turn once.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours. Serve with drippings.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, nuts and salt in 1 1/2 quart glass casserole and mix well.
Microwave on high 6 to 9 minutes until light brown.
Add butter and vanilla.
Mix well.
Microwave on high 1 to 2 minutes more.
Add soda and stir well until light and foamy. Pour onto buttered cookie sheet.
Let cool 1 hour.
Break into pieces and store.

title: alice rettke's christmas fudge
directions: In saucepan, add sugar, butter, milk and salt; stir until all the sugar is dissolved.
Set aside.
Heavily butter a cookie sheet; evenly spread coconut, pressing it in a little.
Chill in refrigerator while the candy is cooking.
In a large mixing bowl, put the milk chocolate, marshmallow cream, vanilla, semi-sweet chocolate and unsweetened chocolate.
Coarsely chop all fruits and nuts; add to bowl.

title: fruit punch
directions: Boil water and sugar together and set aside to cool.
Mix juices and combine with cooled water and sugar mixture.
Pour into 1/2-gallon containers; freeze.
(One-half gallon milk cartons work well.)
Set containers out of freezer 3 hours before serving.
Add 1 quart of ginger ale to each 1/2 gallon of punch mixture.

title: easy onion chicken
directions: Combine the onion salad dressing mix, butter and paprika. Spread mixture over chicken. Roll pieces in the bread crumbs to coat.
Sprinkle with additional paprika for added color.
Place chicken pieces in greased shallow baking pan, skin side up. Bake in a 375° oven for about 1 hour or until tender (do not turn). Serves 4.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt together over low heat; caramels, milk and margarine. Try not to let it boil.
When heated, stir smooth and set aside. Prepare cake mix, using directions on box.
Pour 1/4 of the batter into a greased 9 x 13 inch pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and pour caramel mixture over hot cake, keeping as much as possible from going down sides of pan as cake shrinks.
Pour remaining batter evenly over caramel layer. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans.
Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer, or until done.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix cornstarch and sugar.
Add milk and water.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly.
Add egg yolks, one at a time until thick.
Add butter and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Put on pie and bake at 350° until brown.

title: easy harvest helper
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine all ingredients except cheese. Simmer, covered, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Serve with cheese.
Makes about 10 cups vegetables.

title: turkey tetrazzini
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly spray 11 x 7-inch baking dish with cooking oil.
Cook noodles according to package directions. Combine broth, turkey, mushrooms, onion, parsley and bay leaf in saucepan.
Heat to boiling and cook for 5 minutes.
Mix milk and cornstarch and stir mixture into boiling saucepan contents until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove bay leaf and add cooked noodles.
Transfer to baking dish.
Mix breadcrumbs, oil, cheese and sprinkle over mixture.
Bake 20 minutes or until crumbs are golden brown and edges are bubbling.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients; add sifted flour with soda and spices.
Add vanilla last.
Grease and flour 4 loaf pans; fill to 1/2 full and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add 1 c.
raisins, nuts or prunes after adding the vanilla.

title: braised barbecued short ribs
directions: Season short ribs with salt and pepper.
Brown under a broiler or on a hot grill.
Meanwhile, in a pressure cooker, over moderate heat, cook the onion until tender.
Add the garlic and stir to combine.
Add the remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Add the browned ribs and seal pressure cooker.
Cook over high heat until steam flows steadily.
Turn heat down so that steam keeps a constant stream.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Turn off heat and allow pressure cooker to cool naturally for 10 minutes.
After 10 minutes, release pressure and open cooker carefully.
Place meat on platter.
If sauce is too thin, boil for a minute, until thickened. Serves 4.

title: ranger cookies
directions: Cream sugar into shortening until light and fluffy.
Stir in eggs and vanilla.
Sift baking powder, soda and salt with flour. Add to creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal, flakes, coconut and nuts. Stir well; drop by teaspoon onto a greased baking sheet.
Press flat with fork.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Mix cheese and flour.
Combine rest of ingredients in bowl. Mix in cheese mixture.
Pour into crust.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: thumbprint cookies-pecan
directions: Mix all ingredients together except nuts and egg whites.
Roll dough in balls (sz walnuts).
Whip egg whites slightly with a fork. Dip dough balls in whites and roll in pecans.
Bake on lightly greased cookie sheet at 375° for 5 minutes; remove from oven and press center of cookie with melon baller, return to oven and bake 5 to 8 minutes more or until done.
Cool and ice with powdered sugar icing.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Chill overnight.
Roll into walnut sized balls.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Do not wait for cookies to turn brown as they will be overdone.
Remove when faintly tan.

title: sweet fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients in electric blender.
Blend until smooth, stopping to scrape down sides.
Chill at least 1 hour. Serve with assorted fruits.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: mom's coconut eggs
directions: Mix together.
Make small eggs.
Coat in dark dipping chocolate.

title: nut cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake at 250° for 3 hours.

title: indiana cream pie
directions: Combine dry ingredients; add coffee cream, then unwhipped whipping cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour mix into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
During the first half hour, stir every 10 minutes, being careful not to stir into the crust on bottom. At the end of the first half hour, dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon.
Continue baking for remainder of hour.

title: spanish rice
directions: Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat.
Add beef, onion and green pepper, cooking until there is no more pink to the meat; drain liquid.
Stir in remaining ingredients; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Yields 6 servings.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes.
Fold in first five ingredients
to drained potatoes.
Put cheese on top.
Sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients and place tablespoon of mixture on cracker.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 10 minutes.

title: peppermint stick candy layer cake
directions: Sift flour and measure.
Sift again with baking powder and salt.
Cream shortening.
Continue creaming, gradually adding 4/5 cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons milk.
Add egg yolk and vanilla to remaining milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients with milk to cream mixture.
Beat egg whites stiff, but not dry.
Beat in remaining sugar.
Fold into cake batter.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) layer pans with wax paper in bottom.
Sprinkle with the finely ground peppermint candy.
Bake in hot oven (375°) for 25 minutes.
Ice it in pink and sprinkle remaining ground peppermint candy over top and sides of cake.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Place margarine in 9 x 13-inch aluminum pan; let melt in oven.
Put cornbread mix, eggs, cottage cheese and broccoli in bowl; mix well.

After margarine is melted take pan out of oven; pour margarine into cornbread mixture; mix well. Leave a little margarine in bread pan, just enough so the bread won't stick (not enough so you see any standing in pan).
Cook at 450° for 45 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot or cold.

title: decent meringue
directions: Mix cornstarch and cold water. Add boiling water and
cook over medium heat until smooth and clear.
Cool. Beat egg whites with sugar and vanilla. Beat in the starch mixture, mixing well. Spread over pie filling.
Bake in oven until brown.

title: rancho casserole
directions: Brown hamburg and onion.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients. Simmer for 30 to 35 minutes on top of stove.

title: apricot nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 1 large or 2 small loaf pans.
Measure all ingredients into a large mixing bowl; beat on medium speed for 1/2 minute.
Pour into pan(s).
Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until toothpick in center comes out clean.
Remove from pan(s) and cool thoroughly before slicing.

title: peach pie
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients for 2 minutes.
Pour into 9-inch greased pie pan.
Drain peaches and arrange over mixed ingredients in pie pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese and 3 tablespoons peach juice (or more - make it so it can pour over peaches - not too thin). Pour over peaches.
Mix 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle on cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: deans casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Cook spaghetti until almost done.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a saucepan.
Add water, oil and food coloring.
Cook until mixture pulls away from side of pan.
Knead slightly, almost immediately.
Store in an airtight container.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Combine milk, sugar and Bisquick.
Mix eggs, butter and vanilla in electric blender container.
Cover and blend on low speed for
minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie pan.
Let stand
about
minutes, then sprinkle with coconut.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serve warm or cool.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a medium mixing bowl.
Add eggs, beating well.
Stir in corn, milk and salt.
Melt butter in a lightly greased casserole dish.
Pour in corn mixture.
Bake at 400° for an hour or until firm.
Serve hot.

title: country stew
directions: Brown ground chuck and onions in oil.
Place in slow cooker along with spaghetti sauce, tomato juice, salt and pepper.
Stir until smooth.
Add vegetables (all but beans).
Cook on medium heat until vegetables are tender.
Add beans and simmer on low heat about 1 1/2 hours.
Serve with warm rolls for a complete meal.

title: mussels normandy
directions: Put all in pot and steam until opened.
Top with 2 tablespoons minced chervil.

title: bagel pizza
directions: Slice the bagels, then spread sauce on top.
Slice the cheese into little squares, then place it on top of the sauce.
Add diced onion and pepper if you wish, then place in microwave for 3 minutes.
Cool, then serve.

title: zimmermann boy's grapefruit juice
directions: Pick 4 big grapefruit off of tree in the front yard; juice (try to keep juice off Mom's kitchen floor).
Put juice in 2-quart pitcher and add sugar, then fill with water to the 2-quart line on the pitcher.
Give a big glass of this to Mom cuz she loves it.
When we have nothing else to do we pick a whole bunch of grapefruit and juice them and freeze the juice in Ziploc bags so we can take out a bag, mix it up in our pitcher and serve it to our friends.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly in baking dish.
Drizzle butter on top and sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve with chips or crackers.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Combine cucumbers and onions.
Sprinkle with salt and mix well.
Let stand in refrigerator for 2 hours; drain well, but do not rinse.
One hour before removing from refrigerator, combine sugar and vinegar in a saucepan and heat to mix and dissolve sugar.
Cool completely and pour over cucumbers.
Put into freezer containers and freeze.

title: ambrosious salad
directions: Mix and toss together.
Set in refrigerator.
A good make ahead salad.
Serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 10.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt margarine and peanut butter.
Mix well into confectioners sugar (use hands to mix well).
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Then melt chocolate chips and paraffin wax in a double boiler.
Dip balls in mixture (use toothpick to hold and dip in chocolate).
Set on wax paper to harden.
Makes about 100.

title: cheesy broccoli pie
directions: Prepare pie crusts to line 2 pie pans.
Add garlic salt instead of regular salt to crusts.
Prick bottoms of crusts in pans.
Bake crusts at 450° for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and reduce heat to 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Refrigerate the cranberries until cold. Open can and push cranberries out onto a plate. Cut into slices. In a clear bowl, layer cranberries, Cool Whip, crushed soda crackers, cranberries, Cool Whip and crushed soda crackers. I make 3 layers.

title: sausage lasagna wraps
directions: Cut meat in 3 to 4-inch pieces.
Put slit in middle; fill with cheese.
Cook 1 noodle per piece of sausage.
Lay 3 to 4 noodles over top of mixture.
Wrap each piece of sausage with one noodle that has been cooked nearly done.
Lay in casserole.
Put rest of cheese over top.
Pour spaghetti sauce over top and put in oven. Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: southwestern chili dip
directions: Combine cheese, mayonnaise, 1/2 olives, green chilies, garlic powder and hot sauce.
Top with 1/2 olives, tomato and green onions.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Serve with tortilla chips for dipping.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Beat together Cool Whip, cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on crust.
Top with globs of cherry or blueberry pie mix.

title: ambrosia mold
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve juice.
Add cold water to juice to make 1 cup.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in a large bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in measured juice.
Refrigerate until slightly thickened.
Stir in Cool Whip with whisk until smooth. Chill 15 minutes.
Stir in pineapple, oranges, marshmallows and coconut.
Spoon into a 6-cup mold.
You may use sugar-free Jell-O and Cool Whip for a lower calorie count.

title: hot crusty biscuits
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Cut in the shortening. Add the milk and egg; mix until it flows around bowl.
Knead 5 to 6 times.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Place on ungreased baking sheet. Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: crisp mixed pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in 2-inch long thin sticks.
Cover with a brine of 1 cup salt to 2 cups water.
Let stand overnight.
Rinse and drain.
Pare carrots, cut in sticks like cucumbers.
Cook in a small amount of boiling salt water for 5 minutes.
Remove seeds from peppers and cut into sticks.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over vegetables.
Heat just to boiling point.
Seal in hot, sterile jars.
Makes 8 pints.

title: easy brunswick stew
directions: Put all ingredients in a pan of at least 6 quart capacity. Cook on medium heat for 30 minutes.
May be simmered for longer. Stir fairly constantly.
May be cooked in crock-pot with great results.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw spinach, squeeze and pat dry.
Mix all ingredients together and stir well. Refrigerate. Serve dip with rye bread.

title: oatmeal coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Stir all ingredients in large bowl until blended.
Pour in pie shell and bake 50 to 60 minutes, until top and crust are golden.

title: microwave pizza topper
directions: Spread each muffin half with pizza sauce.
Top each with 3 slices of pepperoni and then with cheese.
Place halves on microwave-proof plate.
Cook on 60 for 45 to 60 seconds, or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 2 minutes before serving.
Makes 1 to 2 servings.

title: artichoke-and-pasta salad
directions: Combine 2 artichoke hearts, olive oil and the next 6 ingredients (olive oil through garlic) in a blender or food processor and process until mixture is smooth.

title: caramel corn
directions: Place brown sugar, margarine, syrup and salt in 2-quart saucepan. Boil 5 minutes, then add vanilla and soda; stir, then pour over popcorn.
Place on cookie sheet and bake in oven at 250° for 45 minutes.
Stir often.
Peanuts can be added.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook the squash in small amount of water 5 to 10 minutes; drain.
Combine sour cream, butter, onions, salt and pepper. Place in buttered 1-quart casserole.
Top with crumbs and cheese. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cheese krispies
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Roll into balls the size of a walnut.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and press with tines of fork in a crisscross pattern.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350° or until lightly browned.
Cool on cake rack.
May be frozen.

title: pink salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all of the remaining ingredients together, mixing well.
This salad goes well with a meal, not just as a dessert.

title: freezer sandwich cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients except peanut butter in bowl with fork. Shape dough into roll about 1 1/2 inches in diameter.
Wrap in plastic wrap.
Freeze until firm, at least 2 hours; no longer than 1 week.
Cut roll into 1/8-inch slices with serrated knife.
Bake until set about 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool 1 minute.
Remove from sheet, cool completely.
Put 2 cookies together with 2 teaspoons peanut butter between each.

title: five flavors pound cake
directions: Mix together. Bring
to a boil and pour over cake while warm. Allow to partially cool in pan before removing.

title: millionaire salad
directions: Mix oranges, coconut, marshmallows and pineapple.
Moisten with sour cream and chill.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: sausage and cheese chowder
directions: In medium saucepan cook sausage, celery, onion and green pepper until vegetables are tender and meat is browned.
Drain excess fat.
Blend in both soups, milk and water.
Cook and stir over medium heat to high heat until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and serve at once.
Yields 6 servings.
Serve with cornbread and fresh apple slices.

title: temptations
directions: Combine butter, brown sugar, sugar, egg, peanut butter and vanilla.
Beat.
Combine flour, salt and baking soda in separate bowl.
Add to cream mixture.
Cover dough and refrigerate.
Roll into balls and place in greased muffin tin.
Bake at 375° for about 9 minutes.
Take out of oven and press peanut butter cup into cookie.
Cool.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken breasts in a greased baking pan and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Place the sauerkraut over the chicken and top with slices of cheese.
Pour dressing evenly over all.
Cover with foil and bake in a 325° oven for 90 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: vicki's favorite potato soup
directions: Saute everything chopped.
Add chicken broth.
Boil until all is soft; add milk and potatoes until soft.
Shut off heat; let cool.
Add the sour cream.
Stir well and serve.

title: fancy chicken dinner
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix soy sauce and soda. Pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour uncovered.

title: sour potato noodle soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until golden brown.
Add flour and brown well, stirring constantly.
Add water a little at a time, stirring constantly.
Then add as much water as desired or at least two quarts.
Add paprika, salt and pepper to taste.
Add bay leaf.
Cut potatoes in small chunks and add.
Cook until potatoes are tender.

title: ground beef with sour cream and dill
directions: Brown ground beef and onions in skillet. Drain. Transfer to crock-pot. Add carrots, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Cover and cook on low for 3 to 4 hours. Stir in sour cream and dill. Cook 5 minutes. Serve on hot cooked noodles.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix together.
Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet 2 inches apart.
Press with fork to make crisscross on top of each cookie.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Let stand on cookie sheet for about 1 minute before removing to rack to cool.

title: *chili beans
directions: Brown hamburger.
Mix in chili powder and ketchup.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add beans; cook, covered, over low heat for 30 minutes.
Serve with hot rolls and slaw. Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: brazos baked beans
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Fry bacon in a large skillet.
Add onion and bell pepper and cook until tender.
Drain excess bacon grease and add all remaining ingredients.
Pour in a baking dish and bake for about 2 hours.
Yields 12 servings.

title: bird nest cookies
directions: Melt chocolate chips over double boiler.
Add peanut butter and melt.
Add marshmallows and melt.
Put both cans of noodles in a very large bowl.
Pour over melted mixture very quickly.
Mix together with spatula until all noodles are covered.
Spoon large cluster onto cookie sheet and cool.
When solidified, ready to serve.

title: sausage and wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Meanwhile, brown sausage in skillet; drain excess fat.
Combine rice, sausage and remaining ingredients in a greased, 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for one hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: round steak
directions: Flour and brown round steak.
Place a slice of onion on top of steak.
Sprinkle chili powder, salt and pepper on steak.
Spread ketchup on steak and top with sliced potatoes.
Add water to almost top of skillet.
Put a lid on skillet; cook on low heat for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: kathy's cheese ball
directions: Mix onions and half of beef with softened cream cheese.
Form into 2 balls, roll each in remaining chopped dried beef to coat.

title: trim-a-tree cookies
directions: Will also need wire for hooks, water colors (tempera or acrylic paints) and clear fixative.

title: fish batter
directions: Stir until smooth.
Dip meat or fish in batter and cook in oil until golden brown.
Batter cannot be saved.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, cinnamon, soda and salt and set aside.
In another bowl, beat together oil, eggs and sugar.
Gradually add dry ingredients to creamed mixture, mixing just until all ingredients are moistened.
Stir in strawberries and pecans.
Pour batter into a greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Mix Tang into dry pudding mix before adding liquid.
Drain fruit and use juice and water to make pudding as per directions. Add chopped fruit and chill until ready to serve.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Put cooked peeled potatoes and all other ingredients in a bowl and mix with an electric mixer at medium speed.
Put ingredients into a greased ovenproof glass dish and top with marshmallows. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Add nuts if desired.

title: german potato salad(microwave)
directions: Cook the first 3 ingredients in 2-quart microwave casserole 10 to 14 minutes. Place the bacon on microwave rack.
Cover with towel and microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until crisp.
Pour bacon fat into 1-quart microwave dish.
Add onion.
Microwave 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in sugar, flour, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Microwave 60 seconds or until it starts to bubble.
Stir in water and vinegar.
Microwave 4 to 6 minutes or until it thickens.
Crumble in bacon and slice potatoes into mixture. Stir gently. Heat again, 1 to 2 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute the oil and onion 10 minutes. Add the rest of the ingredients. Bring to a boil and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients well in a batter.
Melt stick of butter in dish.
Pour batter over butter; do not stir.
Pour fruit in.
Do not stir.
Bake slowly at 425° until done.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Blend cake mix, sour cream, oil, 1/4 cup sugar, water and eggs.
Beat at high speed for 2 minutes. Pour 2/3 batter in a greased and floured tube or Bundt pan.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Cook
chicken until done.
Debone.
Layer in casserole. Mix soup
and milk with garlic powder.	Add mushrooms.	Put on top of chicken.
Add stuffing and cheese.	Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Put chicken in 9 x 13 pan.
Mix celery soup, chicken soup and cream cheese with mixer until well mixed.
Pour over chicken. Mix stuffing with herb packet (dry) and sprinkle over top of soup. Mix broth and melted margarine and pour over stuffing. Bake uncovered at 375 for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: hot vegetable and ham salad
directions: Cook and quarter potatoes in 3 quarts of salted water 12 to 15 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and ham.
Then add cabbage. Cover and cook 5 minutes more.
Drain.
Stir in buttermilk dressing. Serve warm.
Cubed chicken breast may be used instead of ham.

title: easy fruit cobbler
directions: Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and cinnamon.
Then stir in butter well.
Add milk and fruit.
I like fresh strawberries or peaches.
Bake at 325° until center is not doughy.

title: angel pie
directions: Beat egg whites stiff.
Sift cream of tartar and sugar together; add gradually to beaten egg whites.
Beat until smooth.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Divide the ingredients in half and process in the blender on high speed.
Pour mixture into a greased, uncovered, 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes. This can be prepared a day ahead.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Serve hot.

title: quick low-fat pasta sauce(for two)
directions: Saute garlic in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, parsley, sugar and seasonings.
Cook slowly for 5 minutes on low heat.
Pour over angel hair pasta or any other pasta.
Sprinkle top with freshly grated Parmesan cheese.

title: fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix sour cream and mayonnaise until smooth.
Add syrup and blend well.
Use over fresh fruit, fruit salads or canned fruit.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Wash and slice green tomatoes in 1/2-inch thick slices. Sprinkle with salt.
Roll each slice in flour until coated on each side.
Place oil in skillet and heat.
Place floured tomato slices in skillet.
Fry over low heat until browned on both sides.
Serve hot.
Makes 4 servings.

title: butterscotch coconut cookies
directions: Measure sifted flour; add baking powder and salt and sift together.
Cream shortening; add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. Add vanilla.
Then add flour, a little at a time, mixing well. Stir in cereal and coconut.
Drop from teaspoon on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes about 4 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In 3 quart saucepan, heat together sugar, corn syrup and water stirring until sugar dissolves.
When syrup boils, blend in butter. Stir frequently after temperature reaches 230° on candy thermometer; add peanuts when temperature reaches 280°; stirring constantly to crack stage 305°.
Remove from heat, stir in soda mixing well.
Pour onto 2 buttered cookie sheets.
Spread, then loosen when candy hardens.
Break into pieces and store in plastic bags.

title: cookie salad
directions: Drain fruit and cut into small pieces.
Set aside.
Mix together milk and pudding.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip, mixing well.
Add fruit and crumbled cookies into mixture; stir.
Chill well before serving.

title: spanish rice and beef
directions: Lay bacon together and cut into small pieces.
Saute bacon in skillet until done;
remove bacon from skillet and pour off about half the fat.
brown onion in remaining bacon fat.
Add beef and salt and cook until beef is just grey in color.
Add tomatoes, cooked bacon, well-washed rice, and paprika.
Turn into a greased casserole dish.
Cover and bake in a 350°F. oven for 1 1/2 hours or until rice is tender.
Add HOT water if needed during cooking time in the oven.

title: diet soup(equals enough for 1 week)
directions: Cook all ingredients for 1 hour.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: Boil cubed potatoes till tender no more. Cook sausage, drain well.
Mix together sausage and potatoes. Add soup and mix well. Add cheese whiz and mix well. Pour into a pan and top with shredded cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 325°.

title: monterey jack salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.	Serve with tortilla chips or corn chips.

title: tomato maranaro
directions: Lightly brown butter, oil and garlic, then add basil, oregano, parsley and tomatoes.
Simmer.
Add to noodles.
Top with cheese.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into a greased and floured pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: walt's vegetable soup
directions: Put meat and 3 cups water in pressure cooker.

title: bean soup
directions: Wash beans and soak overnight in cold water.
Cook cleaned ham hock in 2 cups water in a pressure cooker at 10 pounds for 30 minutes or cook in a large cooker pan.
Add more water.
Remove ham, clean and peel vegetables.
Chop all vegetables very fine. Pour vegetables in cooker.
Add beans.
Cook until beans and vegetables are done.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: dry jello salad
directions: Mix together jello and cottage cheese; fold in pecans, pears and marshmallows.
Add Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: corn spoon bread
directions: Mix ingredients together, except Swiss cheese.
Spread in 11 x 7 x 1 3/4-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with shredded Swiss cheese.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until knife inserted comes out clean.
Serves 8.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook in large kettle until apples are done.
Stir often to keep from sticking.
Store in freezer or can.

title: teriyaki shish kebabs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Reserve some for a marinade. Combine the rest with beef; toss and refrigerate overnight.

title: baked catfish
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; set aside.
Whisk together egg white and milk.
Dip fillets into milk mixture and dredge in cornmeal mixture.
Place on a foil lined baking sheet coated with cooking spray.
Sprinkle fillets with sesame seed and coat each fillet with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until fish flakes easily when tested with a fork.
Serve with lemon wedges.
Makes 4 servings, 196 calories and 5.9 g fat.

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil bouillon cubes, water and celery, carrots, potatoes and onion for 20 minutes.
Add frozen vegetables and cook until tender.
Add soup, water and cheese.
Serve with salad, bread and simple dessert.
Serves 8.

title: lemon cheesecake torte
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and line oblong pan.
Be sure to save about 2 cups of crumbs to sprinkle on top later.
Cream the cream cheese; beat in sugar.
Mix well.
Add lemon jello after it has jelled and cooled.
Add vanilla and fold in whipped cream.
Pour over crumbs and sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill.

title: brown sugar - bourbon peaches with vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine
first	5
ingredients	in heavy medium skillet over medium-low	 heat.	Stir
until
sugar
dissolves.	Add peaches and
stir until heated through.
Scoop ice cream into bowls
or parfait
glasses.
Top
with
peaches and sauce and serve.	Time of	preparation:
minutes.
Serves 2; can be doubled or tripled but don't triple the amount of bourbon.

title: spinach italienne
directions: Clean spinach and discard stems.
Soak cleaned spinach in hot tap water for 10 minutes; drain.
Place spinach in a greased 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Lay Mozzarella slices on top of spinach. Spread tomato sauce evenly over cheese.
Mix the oregano with the melted butter; brush bread slices on one side.
Cut bread slices into 1-inch strips.
Arrange, buttered side up, on mixture.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: watermelon slush
directions: Place watermelon in a blender.
Process until smooth.

In glass container, combine watermelon puree, fruit punch, water and vodka. Stir. Cover and freeze overnight or 8 hours, minimum. Prior to serving, let stand at room temperature 30 to 45 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Spoon 1/2 cup slush mixture into each serving glass. Stir 1/4 cup ginger ale into each.
Makes 13 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: ground beef grand style
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Drain and set aside.
Combine remaining ingredients except biscuits.
Mix well with beef and onions.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 10 minutes more or until biscuits are golden brown.

title: super meatballs
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in bowl, mixing well.
Shape into balls.
Brown in skillet; drain.
Place in casserole.
Mix chili sauce and jelly in bowl.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: ham pinwheels
directions: Mix cream cheese, chives and horseradish.
Spread 1 tablespoon cream cheese mix on slice of ham.
Put cheese on top, then another tablespoon of mix.
Roll tightly with rolled side down.
Chill in refrigerator overnight.
Slice in 4 or 5 pieces.

title: sausage pie
directions: *Can use dried parsley that has been soaked for awhile.

title: apple crisp
directions: Slice apples into pan.
Sprinkle sugar, nutmeg and water over apples.
Mix together brown sugar, flour and butter until crumbly. Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: poor man's loaf
directions: Mix together.
Shape into loaf and place in roaster.
Cover with cream of mushroom soup and 1 can of water mixed.
Bake at 300° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: turketti
directions: Cook
spaghetti, drain.
Place	turkey,
pimento,
green pepper
and onion in 1 1/2 quart casserole.
Pour
in
mushroom soup and turkey broth.
Add salt, pepper, 1
cup
grated cheese and spaghetti.
With 2 forks, lightly toss until
all
is
well mixed and coated with sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top. Bake until bubbly throughout.

title: chicken
directions: Pour soups in bottom of roasting pan.
Pour rice over soup evenly.
Roll chicken in onion soup and lay on top of rice.
Do not put on top of each other. Pour wine over chicken.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: russian tea mix
directions: Mix well and use 2 heaping teaspoonfuls to a cup of boiling water.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 2 minutes
with mixer.
Pour into 3 greased and floured round pans.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: glazed pecans
directions: Mix sugar, cinnamon, vanilla and butter flavoring together. Add milk and bring to a boil.
Add pecans and stir continually until pecans take up all the liquid.
Pour on wax paper and separate.
A family favorite.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast in the lukewarm water.
Let set 3 minutes. Add the cake mix, 1 cup flour, eggs, oil and salt.
Beat until bubbles appear.
Add 6 cups flour slowly.
This makes a soft dough. Knead in a bowl 5 minutes.
Oil top, cover and let raise until double.
Put
on floured board.
Roll out. Spread with oleo, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Roll as for jelly roll. Cut into 1-inch slices.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 400° until brown.
Ice if you like with powdered sugar icing.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine pineapple juice with 1 cup water; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat; stir in 2 (3 ounce) packages strawberry jello until dissolved.
Add cranberry sauce, 3 tablespoons lemon juice and lemon peel.
Chill until slightly thickened; stir in sour cream and pineapple.
Chill until firm, at least 2 to 3 hours.

title: gold cake
directions: Cream butter until light and fluffy.
Add the sugar gradually and continue creaming.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add to the butter and sugar mixture.
Sift the flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add them alternately with milk. Add flavoring and beat well.
Bake in 2 (9-inch) layers at 350° for 35 minutes, 1 loaf pan at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes or 22 to 24 cupcakes at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Can also bake in angel food pan.

title: peanut butter candy cups("buckeye balls")
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients together.
If too dry, add a little milk. Roll into balls and refrigerate until firm.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Cook mixed vegetables until tender; drain.
In bowl, add beans, celery, onion and pepper.
In saucepan over medium heat, bring sugar, vinegar and cornstarch to a boil.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour over vegetables.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: healthy vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan sprayed with cooking spray, saute carrots, onion and garlic over low heat until softened, about 5 minutes. Add broth, cabbage, beans, tomato paste, basil, oregano and salt and bring to a boil. Lower heat and simmer, covered, about 15 minutes or until beans are tender. Stir in zucchini and heat 3 to 4 minutes. Serve hot. Makes 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: stuffed cabbage leaves
directions: Wash and blanch cabbage leaves.
Drain and dry.
Saute onion, parsley, green pepper, thyme and garlic.
Toss brown rice, wild rice and sauteed vegetables together.
Divide into 8 equal portions and fill each cabbage leaf.
Wrap leaf around and fasten with a toothpick.
Place, seam side down, in a nonstick casserole.
Top with tomato sauce.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: macaroni hamburger casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown meat and onions in frying pan.
Add tomato sauce, chili powder and salt; simmer for about 20 minutes. Add drained macaroni to mixture.
Put into casserole; top with mushroom soup and grated cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate cake bars(hershey syrup brownies)
directions: Cream sugar and butter together; add eggs; mix well.
Add syrup, flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix together and put in 10 x 15-inch pan.

title: lentil soup
directions: Cover lentils with water and let soak overnight.
In morning, pour off and measure water, adding enough to make 6 cups if necessary.
Combine all ingredients in kettle.
Cover and simmer 2 hours or until lentils are soft.
Remove ham bone.
Add additional seasonings if desired.
Serve with croutons, crackers.
If soup is too thick, thin with milk, bouillon cube dissolved in water, or vegetable stock. If too thin, thicken slightly with flour and water paste.

title: sand tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients together and form by hand in relaxed "U" shape.
Cook very slowly 225° to 275° until lightly browned.
Roll in powdered sugar if desired.
Makes approximately 50.

title: pork saute
directions: In shallow glass dish, combine all ingredients except pork. Add pork coating with marinade, cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours stirring occasionally.
Drain pork; reserve marinade.
Thread pork on skewers, grill 5 to 6 minutes or until done basting with marinade.

title: honey pumpkin bread(one loaf)
directions: Stir together honey, milk and sugar over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cool 10 minutes, then beat in butter.
Cool 10 minutes more and beat in egg yolks and pumpkin.
Sift dry ingredients together, then sift them again into the batter.
Mix thoroughly. Fold in fruit and nuts.
Turn batter into greased and floured bread pan. Bake at 350° 1 1/4 hours or until bread tests done.
Cool in pan 15 minutes and then turn out on rack. Serve warm with butter or cream cheese.

title: seafood scampi
directions: Melt margarine in skillet on medium-high; saute onion, green pepper and garlic for 3 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and stir 3 minutes.
Add noodles; toss and heat through.

title: rhubarb dessert
directions: In a square baking pan, cover the bottom of pan with rhubarb. Sprinkle with sugar.
Sprinkle package of dry jello on top. Sprinkle dry cake mix on top of jello.
Pour 1 1/2 cups water over all.
Break up your butter and drop it here and there on mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with whipped topping!
Enjoy!

title: persimmon date loaf
directions: Sift flour and measure and sift again with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in bread crumbs.

title: brown rice
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Stir together so well blended.
Bake uncovered.	Quick, easy and especially good with beef and barbecue chicken.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice vegetables.
Place in enamelware or glass bowl. Sprinkle with salt and add water.
Cover and let stand 2 to 4 hours or overnight.
Turn into colander and drain for 10 to 15 minutes. Put into kettle.
Add some sliced onion, then vinegar, sugar and spices.
Heat to boiling.
Simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Pack, seal 3 to 5 pints for 5 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: chicken salad sandwich
directions: Grind the chicken, celery and pickles; add the almonds.
Add the eggs, pimientos, dressing and mayonnaise.
Season with remaining ingredients.
Spread on thin sliced sandwich bread. Trim crust from edges.
Cut in fancy shapes.
Garnish with sliced olives or parsley, pimento or cress.
Serve either closed or open-faced sandwiches.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Melt oleo; dip strips of bread in oleo, both sides, and set aside.
Arrange asparagus in 8 x 11-inch baking dish.
Mix peas, soup and cheese and pour over asparagus.
Arrange the bread strips on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: make-ahead mashed potatoes
directions: Combine all ingredients and whip with an electric mixer until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Turn into
a large casserole dish. Refrigerate until ready to heat for serving.
When ready
to serve,
bake
at 350° for 1 hour
or
until
heated through. Serve hot.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix flour and
cinnamon.
Beat sugar, shortening, eggs, pumpkin and
water;
then add flour mix.
Mix in mincemeat and nuts.
Bake in 2 loaf pans at 350° for 60 minutes.	Cool.

title: peach crinkle
directions: Place peaches in a lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with lemon rind.
Combine pie crust mix and brown sugar. Sprinkle over rind.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve with ice cream.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: mother's molasses cookies
directions: Roll out on floured board. Sprinkle with sugar before baking. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fried pies
directions: Sift
together dry ingredients; cut in shortening.
Add egg beaten in milk to dry ingredients.	Knead lightly and wrap tightly in	plastic
bag.
Chill
in
refrigerator	at least 2 hours. Roll
dough
thin;	fill
with
cold
fruit (canned or dried). Fry in cooking oil on medium heat until brown on both sides. (Pies should be a half-moon shape.)

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn in a large roaster pan.
Boil all ingredients, except popped corn and baking soda, for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add soda; stir quickly and pour over popped corn while foamy.
Mix well.
Place in a 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes while baking.

title: oriental rice pilaf
directions: Saute onions in margarine about 5 minutes.
Add rice and stir, about 5 minutes.
Pour into 1 1/2 or 2-quart casserole dish and add all other ingredients.
Cover.
Cook in preheated oven at 350° for about 40 minutes or until all liquid is absorbed.

title: aunt pat's baked apples
directions: Rinse apples.
Cut in halves.
Core.
Do not peel.
Place apples in cold water with a little lemon juice.
Prepare filling. Melt butter in a saucepan.
Add sugar, flour, cinnamon and cloves. Heat.
Add chopped nuts and coconut.
Mix to blend.
Remove apples and pat dry.
Place apple halves in an ovenproof dish. Fill holes with nut mixture and mound filling on top of each apple.
Bake apples at 350° for about 35 minutes or until tender and filling is golden brown.
Serve warm with whipped cream or vanilla ice cream.

title: baked enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain well.
Add taco sauce, enchilada sauce, chiles, creamed soups, chili powder and milk.
Quarter tortillas.
Layer in casserole dish:
tortillas, sauce and Cheddar cheese several times.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: mrs. c's pumpkin bread
directions: Blend together sugar, eggs, oil and pumpkin.
Add dry ingredients that have been sifted together.
Stir water into mixture.
Grease and flour bread pans.
Pour mixture into pans and bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: quick salsa chicken
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Prepare chicken.
Sprinkle both sides of chicken with taco seasoning mix.
Place in baking dish.
Pour salsa over chicken.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is fork tender.
Sprinkle evenly with cheese.
Bake additional 3 to 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Serve with sour cream.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cheese fudge
directions: Melt cheese and oleo.
Add vanilla.
Sift sugar and cocoa together thoroughly.
Add nuts and mix.
Pour in melted cheese, oleo and vanilla and stir.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pans to cut. Makes 10 pounds.

title: hungry family goulash
directions: Go to IGA (Fairway).
Go to aisle Number 6. Look on the left side in the canned goods department.
Get one (1) can of Beenie Weenies.
Take them home, wherever that happens to be.
Get a can opener and open them.
Pour them into a small bowl.
Eat!
Eat! Eat!

title: judy's fudge
directions: Cook first 5 ingredients for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, chocolate bits and nuts.
Pour into greased pan.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Melt butter.
Cook broccoli according to package.
Mix other ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Boil chicken and pick off meat.
Set aside.
Skim fat from broth.
Using broth, cook until done.
Add onions, celery, sprouts and chicken.
Bring to boil and thicken with flour and water paste.
Add Kitchen Bouquet to color.
Serve over Chinese noodles. Pass the soy sauce.

title: angela's buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Pour into tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: southern-style chili macaroni
directions: Cook ground beef in skillet, stirring frequently until brown. Drain.
Stir in macaroni, sauce mix and remaining ingredients. Heat to boiling, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes, stirring frequently.
Uncover and simmer until desired consistency.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Grease and flour 2 (9-inch) pie pans.
Beat eggs well and add sugar, flour and milk.
Add vanilla and melted butter.
Stir in coconut.
Divide mixture to full two pie pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown. Makes its own crust.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce on bottom.
Add layer of frozen peas.
Layer mixed celery, onion and green pepper.

title: oven chicken
directions: Lightly flour the chicken and then brown in a small amount of oil. Drain.
Place in a large baking pan.
Mix the sour cream and the soup together and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fruit "slurpee"
directions: Fill blender 3/4 full of strawberries. Cut up and toss in 1 banana. Cover with orange juice and blend until smooth.
Serves 4.

title: grilled quesadilla
directions: Flatten each roll into 8-inch circle on outdoor grill or on the stove top using a grilling pan. Grill one circle about 1 minute on each side. Grill another circle on one side. Turn over and top with 1/2 cup cheese. Put already grilled circle on top and allow bottom circle to grill. Repeat with each set of rolls. Serve warm with salsa, if desired. Makes 6 Quesadillas.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Combine all ingredients in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling. Pour into a 9 x 14-inch casserole.
Top with biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until biscuits are lightly browned.

title: chicken ala roma
directions: Saute onion in 2 tablespoons butter until tender; add tomatoes, undrained mushrooms, tarragon, basil, sugar and 1/4 teaspoon salt. Simmer until sauce thickens.
Stir in chicken.
Melt remaining butter.
Blend flour and remaining salt.
Add cream and cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Stir in wine.
Pour 1/3 of tomatoes over bottom of 2-quart shallow casserole.
Spoon 1/3 of wine sauce over tomatoes.
Top with 1/3 of shredded cheese.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook sausage until done, breaking into bits as you cook it. Drain and set aside.
Beat eggs; add milk, salt and mustard.
Into a greased baking dish layer the bread, sausage and cheese.
Pour egg mixture over these ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Brown stew beef in oil, along with onion.
Add 1 quart water to the meat.
Chop cabbage up into small pieces and add.
Add mixed vegetables and tomatoes.
Let simmer for 2 hours.

title: elwin's birthday cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add egg yolks.
Combine flour and soda and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Stir in vanilla.
Add coconut and nuts.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into cake pans and bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Ice with Elwin's Birthday Cake Icing.

title: cherry winks
directions: 1. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Set aside.

title: macaroni and raisins
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain. Meanwhile, plump the raisins by barely covering them in hot water. Let stand.

title: mini kabobs
directions: Arrange fruit, vegetables, cheese and folded salami slices on long frilled wooden toothpicks.
Make your own creations (cheese, fruit, salami), (veggie, cheese, fruit), (cheese, veggie, salami).

title: crock-pot cube steak
directions: Wash meat and break into pieces and put in the crock-pot with 1 can of French onion soup, 1 can of mushroom soup and 2 cans of water.
Simmer for 3 to 4 hours on high (checking once).
Mix 2 tablespoons of flour with dry onion soup mix, then 1 cup of water or milk (this will thicken gravy).

title: beacon hill cookies
directions: Melt chocolate over hot water.
Beat egg whites and salt until foamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating well.
Keep beating until peaks form.
Beat in vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in chocolate and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfull onto greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Decorate with nuts.

title: lessie roseman's chicken pie
directions: Place chicken in bottom of a greased 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Bring soup and broth to a boil; pour over chicken.
Combine flour, margarine and buttermilk and pour over mixture.
Do not stir.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: wonderful waffles
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into combined egg yolks, milk and butter.
Fold in egg whites, beaten stiff.
Bake in hot waffle iron.

title: 30 minute chili
directions: Brown 1 pound ground beef with 1 cup chopped onion in skillet. Drain off fat.
Stir in tomatoes and juice, tomato sauce, kidney beans, salt, pepper, chili powder and sugar.
Break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, for 30 minutes to blend flavors.

title: casserole of vegetables au gratin
directions: Melt margarine in saucepan.
Add green pepper and garlic.
Cook gently until green pepper is slightly tender.
Stir in flour until well moistened with butter.
Add milk, salt, pepper, basil, oregano and sugar.
Heat and stir in 1/2 cup grated cheese until cheese is melted.
Add drained tomatoes.
Heat gently until the mixture is thickened again and turn into a 2-quart casserole dish . Add corn and whole onions.
Mix. Sprinkle with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese on top.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, about 50 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Place drained asparagus in flat baking dish.
Sprinkle with crumbs and half of pimento.
Dot with butter. Pour on mushroom soup, cover with eggs and press into soup.
Dot with pimento bits and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes. Serves 8.

title: simple lemon icebox pie
directions: Add lemonade to Cool Whip in small amounts. Taste frequently for tartness. Pour into pie crust and put in freezer until firm.

title: 1-2-3 pie crust
directions: Cut Crisco into flour until small pieces.
Add water to flour mixture, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mix.
Knead several times and press into pie pan.
Flute edges.

title: chicken with port wine sauce
directions: Wash and slice mushrooms.
Melt butter and saute green onions 5 minutes without burning.
Add mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Saute over medium heat 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Add chicken broth, Port and cream to mushrooms and simmer for five minutes.
Put mixture into baking dish.
Arrange chicken breasts in a single layer on top of the mixture.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover dish tightly with tinfoil.
Bake in center of oven for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve immediately.

title: cherry delights
directions: Mix butter and sugar.
Stir in Karo, eggs and flour.
Chill for an hour.
Roll into balls and dip in egg whites and nuts.
Put cherries on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: play dough(makes large batch)
directions: Place all ingredients in large saucepan.
Cook and stir constantly over medium heat until a soft dough forms; dough will begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Knead until smooth. Store in a covered container.
Enjoy!

title: penne a la vodka sauce
directions: Put olive oil in pan over low heat.
Saute garlic to a golden brown color.
Add cans of Contadina tomato sauce, salt and pepper to taste.
Also add 1/4 teaspoon dried basil.
Stir to a boil on high heat.
Then lower to medium heat.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Add 1/2 pint light cream.
Stir occasionally for 5 minutes.
Last add 2 ounces of vodka.
Bring to a boil.
Serve over cooked macaroni.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix well and pour over browned beef, pork, chicken or venison. I usually need to double this.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix melted margarine and sugar; let cool to room temperature. Beat eggs slightly and add to margarine.
Mix.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into pie shell and bake 30 to 40 minutes in 375° oven.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Place milk and sugar in large saucepan.
Heat to boiling, cooking 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; add marshmallows, nuts, chocolate chips and vanilla.
Stir until melted.
Pour into buttered 8-inch square pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: rocks
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs.
Stir in dry ingredients; mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoon onto cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: amaretto cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add sour cream; beat.
Add extracts, baking soda and salt.
Gradually beat in flour.
Add Amaretto and beat well.
Pour into greased Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes or until done.
Cool for about 15 minutes and remove from pan to finish cooling.

title: pork chops and apples
directions: Brown pork chops and drain
off
fat.
Slice
peeled apples in bottom of baking dish.
Add
cup
of	celery	and dried onion.
Mix brown sugar and
mustard.
Add 1/2 cup water to sugar mixture and stir.
Pour
half of mustard over celery. Add pork chops and remainder of mustard mix.
Cover and bake 1 hour at 400°.
Uncover and bake another 15 minutes.

title: how to can squash and okra
directions: Loosen the skins of 15 pounds ripe tomatoes.
Dip tomatoes, one at a time, in boiling water for 1/2 minute.
Then dip them quickly in cold water.
Peel the tomatoes.
Remove stem ends and cores of tomatoes.
Pack small or medium tomatoes whole.
Cut large tomatoes in quarters or eighths.
Use a spoon to remove excess seeds, if desired.
Drain in colander.
Before starting the canning procedure, heat the canning jars and rings in boiling water to make sure they are sterile.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef, oregano and onion; drain.
Cook noodles. Layer in dish the meat sauce, cheese and noodles.
Bake until bubbly.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Bake pastry shells according to package directions.
In a medium saucepan, cook shrimp and garlic in butter until lightly browned.
Add sauce mix; blend in milk, green onions, tomatoes and basil.
Bring to a boil, stirring.
Reduce heat and simmer 5 minutes until shrimp is thoroughly cooked.
Spoon mixture into warm pastry shells.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; place in a single layer in a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan.
Set aside.
Combine next 8 ingredients; pour over shrimp.
Bake at 450° for 5 minutes.
Take out of oven and turn shrimp over and bake until shrimp are done (8 to 10 minutes longer).
Serve over rice.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion, celery and bell pepper in olive oil until tender.
Mix with chicken, mushroom soup, cheese and pimento. Cook spaghetti in chicken stock; drain.
Mix all together and pour into large casserole.
Sprinkle with parmesan cheese.
Cover and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: pork and green chile stew
directions: Brown pork and onion in hot oil in a large pot, stirring frequently, for about 5 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and stir well. Bring mixture to a boil over high heat; reduce to low and simmer, covered, for 45 minutes. Remove cover and simmer for about 10 minutes more or until stew is slightly thickened. Makes 4 servings.

title: scotch-o-roos
directions: Combine sugar and Karo.
Bring to boil and add peanut butter. Mix in Rice Krispies.
Press into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: summer fruit with cream brown sugar
directions: Mix sour cream and brown sugar in a bowl.
Divide melon chunks and raspberries among individual dessert dishes.
Top with sour cream mixture and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Simmer chicken with onion and bay leaf in salted water to cover.
Remove chicken bone and cut in bite-size bits.
Reserve chicken broth.
Melt 1/2 cup of butter in skillet and saute mushrooms 2 or 3 minutes.
Add chicken, cream, sherry, white wine, salt and pepper.
Heat almost to boiling.
Blend flour and 2 tablespoons butter together to make a smooth paste and stir into chicken mixture, continuing to stir until smooth and somewhat thickened.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook noodles in chicken broth until tender, 7 or 10 minutes.
Drain; rinse in cold water and place in buttered shallow casserole.
Gently pour chicken and mushroom mixture over noodles.
Fold in sour cream and add pimento and ripe olives.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and brown lightly under broiler oven at 375° for about 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemon colored.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Stir in oil, then zucchini and vanilla.
Stir baking soda and baking powder.
Add to egg mixture, mixing only until all ingredients are moistened.
Pour into 2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) baking pans.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350°, then 1/2 hour at 325°.
Makes two loaves.

title: quick mix pudding cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Roll into balls and put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake.

title: georgia pecan pie(two pies)
directions: Brown pecans, coconut and butter.
Set aside.
Mix together cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Pour cream cheese mixture into 2 baked pie shells.
Top with nut mixture.
Drizzle warm caramel ice cream topping over pies.
Freeze.
Has to be frozen.
Thirty to thirty-five minutes before serving, remove from freezer.
Keeps up to 6 months.

title: turkey salad
directions: Cut chunks of turkey breast and process in food processor. Onion and celery can also be processed.
Mix together.
Each ingredient can be adjusted to taste.
Salt and pepper to taste. This is good on crackers or stuffed in mini pita pockets.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: saturday night special
directions: When done, using spatula cut into small pieces and set aside. Fry at least 1/2 pkg. bacon until crisp.
Discard 3/4 of grease and break into pieces.
Peel and thinly slice 4 medium sized potatoes and cook in hot skillet.
Peel, slice and break into rounds 1 large onion and add to potatoes.

title: sugar coated nuts
directions: Combine all ingredients together in saucepan.
Cook over medium heat 10 to 15 minutes or until peanuts are coated with syrup.
Spread mixture on greased baking sheet.
Bake at 325° for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir well.
Return to oven; bake 15 minutes more.
Makes 3 cups.

title: cole slaw
directions: Bring to boil the vinegar, celery seed, salt, pepper, mustard and salad oil.
Pour over uncooked, shredded cabbage while hot. Mix together and add sugar.
Let stand overnight.
Tastes better each day.

title: spicy ham sauce
directions: In saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over moderate heat until thickened, about 10 minutes. Good with ham or smoked pork.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place ingredients in large casserole dish in order.
Cover and bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: leftover breakfast
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cook sausage until done.
Drain sausage.
Tear bread up and put in bottom of pan.
Then layer sausage, cheese, sausage and cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard and pour over sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: green "stuff"
directions: Mix it all together and chill.
Can be made into a mold.

title: no cook freezer strawberry jam
directions: Wash and cap strawberries.
Take hands and crush real good, then measure 2 cups crushed strawberries in one pan.
Measure sugar; have sugar ready to pour in.
Stir in real good.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Melt the sugar in an iron frying pan over low heat.
Stir it with a wooden spoon as it melts.
When it has melted to a light brown syrup, stir in the nuts.
Pour the mixture carefully into a greased pan.
While it is warm, mark it into squares.
When it has cooled, break the candy into pieces.
This brittle may be made with any kind of nuts or your favorite dry cereal.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease muffin tins.
Mix all ingredients and fill muffin tins half full.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes, until browned.

title: christmas breakfast(make ahead breakfast)
directions: Trim crusts from bread. Crumble bread. Mix bread and cheese and spread in bottom of greased 7 1/2 x 12-inch flat baking dish. Beat eggs and milk together and stir in salt, pepper and mustard. Pour over bread and cheese. Lay bacon on top. Refrigerate overnight. Next morning, bake uncovered, at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes. Serves 6. Make this the day before.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place soup, water, onion, celery and rice in baking dish.
Lay chicken in, skin side up.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients well. Pour into greased loaf pan.
Melt 1/4 stick butter and pour over loaf in pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: frozen banana salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir well; pour into square glass baking dish.
Freeze until firm.
Serve on lettuce.
Makes 9 servings.

title: fuzzy navel(non-alcoholic)
directions: Combine ingredients in blender until smooth and creamy. Serves 2.

title: shrimp fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook noodles as directed but put 2 tablespoons of butter in them so they will not stick.
Place about 8 shrimp in a cup and add black pepper, salt, butter and garlic powder.
Place Saran Wrap over cup and place in microwave for approximately 2 minutes. (Shrimp must be pink when cooked.)

title: italiano main dish soup
directions: Shape beef into meatballs.
In large saucepan, brown meatballs and cook with onion, garlic and oregano in shortening until tender.
Add cabbage and bean and bacon soup.
Gradually stir in water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until well heated.

title: paula tripp's acorn squash soup
directions: Cut squash in half lengthwise and remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in broiler pan.
Add hot water to pan to a depth of 1 inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Spoon pulp from squash to create a serving bowl, reserving pulp.
Set aside squash bowls. Place carrots and onion in a saucepan and cover with water.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain and combine vegetables with reserved squash pulp and 1/3 cup water in the container of blender or food processor.
Process 30 seconds or until mixture is smooth.
Set aside.
Melt butter in large Dutch oven over low heat.
Add flour, salt and pepper, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Gradually add pureed vegetable mixture, chicken broth, sherry, spices and red pepper and bring to boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Stir in half and half and if desired 1 1/2 tablespoons sherry.
Cook until soup is heated through, but do not boil.
Serve in squash shells on bed of kale.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Serves 8.

title: molasses softies
directions: Add
beaten
egg,
brown
sugar,
salt	and molasses to melted shortening and mix well.
Sift flour, spices and soda; add to mix alternately with boiling water.
Add vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful
on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Bring 1/2 cup water to a boil in heavy saucepan.
Add sugar and syrup. Boil until 300° on candy thermometer or mixture spins a thread.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook until golden brown and peanuts begin to pop.
Add butter, vanilla and soda.
Stir down quickly. Pour onto greased cookie sheet, spreading thin.
Cool.
Break into small pieces.

title: potato garlic vichyssoise
directions: In a large, heavy saucepan, cook the onion in the oil until soft, about 3 minutes.
Add the garlic and potatoes and toss with the onion.
Add the broth, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Simmer for 15 minutes until the potatoes are tender.
With a potato masher or back of a large cooking spoon, mash the potatoes coarsely.
Don't worry if the results are uneven.
Continue until the soup thickens slightly.
Add the cream and milk (or all milk) and heat slowly to a simmer.
Adjust seasoning, chill and serve.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Place rhubarb in 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Cover with sugar and butter.
Cream egg, sugar and shortening.
Add flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Any kind of fruit may be used but adjust sugar on fruit accordingly.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook tomatoes and onions together and put through food mill (as tomato juice).
Add rest of ingredients to tomato juice and cook until thick.
Can like tomato juice.
Good for spaghetti sauce, plain or with ground beef added.

title: pineapple delicious
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar and eggs, one at a time, and beat well.
Crush graham crackers.
Whip the cream and add sugar.
Add flavoring.
Put in 9-inch square casserole in the following order:

title: sitting bull
directions: Make the amount to fit the serving needed.
Sandwich the jelly between the wafers and dip in milk.
Make a layer of these.
Top with whipped topping. Make 2 to 3 layers, depending on depth of dish.
Garnish with nuts of your choice.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the flour, baking powder and sugar.
Add milk.
Pour into hot melted butter.
Add peaches, including all liquid.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix sour cream, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Add remaining ingredients; blend.
Pour into muffin tins which have been lined with paper cups.
Freeze until firm.
Remove the paper liners and serve.
Salads keep indefinitely in freezer in plastic bags.

title: yogurt wheat bread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, baking powder and baking soda in a mixing bowl.
Add sugar (if used instead of honey).
Cut margarine into flour mixture.
Mix together the milk and yogurt (and honey, if using in place of sugar).
Add to flour mixture and stir until ingredients are blended.
Remove dough from bowl and roll out on floured surface.
Shape into a ball.
Cut ball in half and shape each half into an oval.
Slit center of each oval. Place on greased cookie sheet several inches apart.
Bake 30 minutes.
Loaves should be golden brown and sound hollow when tapped with fingertips.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Put in refrigerator, covered.
Stir every day for 3 days.
Put in clean jars.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Combine pudding, eggs and milk.
Cook just until boiling. Strain into 4-quart ice cream freezer can.
Add cream, sugar and vanilla.
Add enough milk to fill freezer can 3/4 full. Refrigerate 2 to 5 hours.
Freeze in ice cream freezer as directed with freezer.

title: pasta with chicken and broccoli
directions: In a large skillet, heat oil on medium heat.
Saute garlic about 1 minute, till golden.
Add chicken strips and saute till almost completely cooked-about 7-10 minutes.
Add broccoli and cook till crisp-tender.
Add sun-dried tomatoes,
basil, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Add the wine, then add chicken broth and butter or margarine.
Cook 3-5 minutes or until heated thoroughly stirring occasionally.

title: garfield lasagne
directions: Brown meat; drain fat.
Add salt, garlic and pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Add crushed tomatoes and tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly and simmer 30 minutes.
Boil noodles until almost tender.
Rinse.
Pour 1/4 meat sauce into casserole dish.
Top with noodles, then Mozzarella.
In separate bowl, mix cottage cheese and Ricotta together.
Put 1/3 mixture in casserole next. Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand before cutting.
If refrigerated, bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scampi salad platter
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine the spinach, garbanzo beans, water chestnuts or jicama, mushrooms and green onion.
Add the 1/4 cup Italian dressing; toss to mix.
Cover and chill.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in a little warm water.
Finish filling cup with buttermilk.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt until light and springy, then roll out like biscuits and cut.
Let rise 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake.

title: ritz cracker chicken
directions: Melt butter in pan you are to use in oven at 350°.
Crush crackers in bowl.
After dipping chicken in butter, put chicken in cracker crumbs.
Lay chicken back in the melted butter dish.
Bake for 45 minutes to 1 hour until tender, covered.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Combine ground beef, onion, garlic, salt and pepper in 3-quart Dutch oven.
Cook until brown and drain.
Add flour and mix well. Add mushrooms and liquid and soup; stir and bring to boil.
Lower heat; add sour cream and noodles.
Mix well.
Serves 6.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Whip milk and lemon juice together until thick; drain pineapple and oranges.
Fold into milk, lemon juice and Cool Whip. Add nuts.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
This makes 2 pies. Keep refrigerated.

title: salsa dip 2
directions: Chop pepper and onion finely and cook in oil until tender. Mix well with other ingredients and cook until thick. Add sugar and salt and pepper to taste.

title: witches brew
directions: Pour iced Seven-Up over orange sherbet for a delicious Halloween party drink.

title: creamy salad
directions: Shred lettuce coarsely into salad bowl.
Spread diced celery over lettuce.
Drizzle onion rings over top.
Mix vinegar, salad dressing, sugar and sour cream.
Pour over mixture.
Cover with crisp bacon pieces.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top.
Chill at least 3 hours.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Mix by hand.
Spray muffin pans with Pam.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen.

title: panzanella
directions: Dunk bread into bowl of cold water.
Squeeze well and tear into bite size pieces.
In a serving bowl, toss bread and remaining ingredients.
Serves 4 to 6 as an appetizer.

title: cool whip salad
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil, then set aside to cool. Add the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and refrigerate until set.
Can be made the day before.

title: braised pork and vegetables
directions: Cook and stir pork in oil in 10-inch skillet over medium heat until brown; drain on paper towels.
Cook and stir onion and garlic in same skillet until onion is tender.
Stir in pork, carrots, 1 cup water, bouillon, salt, basil, thyme and pepper. Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion.
Drain.
Pour in bottom of (flat) rectangular casserole dish.
Cover generously with frozen mixed vegetables.
Put cream of mushroom soup on top of vegetables; add layer of shredded cheese.
Top with frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: golden beef quiche
directions: About 1 1/4 hours before serving, prepare pie crust mix as directed.
Shape mixture into a ball.
On lightly floured surface with lightly floured rolling pin, roll ball into a circle 2 inches larger all around than a 9-inch pie dish.
Line pie plate with pastry; trim pastry edge, leaving a 1-inch overhang.
Fold overhang under; pinch to form a high fluted edge.
Spread pie crust with butter or margarine.
Preheat oven to 375°.
In 12-inch skillet over medium heat, cook ground beef and onion until meat is lightly brown and onion is tender, stirring often.
Spoon into pie crust. In large bowl with wire whisk or fork, mix undiluted soup and remaining ingredients; pour soup mixture into pie crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.

title: mrs. groover's marshmallow nut roll
directions: Thoroughly mix ingredients together and form into a roll.
Let stand overnight.
Slice and serve with whipped cream.

title: granny's grape jelly
directions: Add Sure-Jell to juice.
Bring to a boil.
Add sugar; bring to a boil. Boil one minute.
Put in jars and seal.

title: seafood casserole
directions: Saute onion (white or green), 1 stalk celery and mushrooms (if desired) in 3 tablespoons of butter.
Add green pepper, shrimp and cooked lobster meat.
Set aside.

title: three rivers chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown chicken in oil; sprinkle with pepper.
Remove from pan and blot with paper towel.
In a lightly greased casserole dish, spread asparagus spears and place chicken on top of spears.
Mix next 4 ingredients together in a small bowl and pour over chicken-asparagus.
Bake, covered, for 30 minutes. Uncover and sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake for 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: refrigerator slaw
directions: Heat to boiling the vinegar, salt, mustard, celery seed, sugar and oil. Remove from heat. Mix with cabbage, onion and pepper. Cool to room temperature and refrigerate. Will keep 2 weeks in refrigerator.

title: uncooked cookies
directions: Boil butter, sugar, milk and cocoa for 1 minute.
While hot, add peanut butter, rolled oats and vanilla.
Drop on wax paper until cool.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Combine oats
with
buttermilk	in a bowl and let stand while you
prepare
the
rest.
Measure
and sift together dry ingredients.
To oatmeal mixture add oil, sugar and egg.
Stir in dry
ingredients.
Mix
only long enough to moisten.
Spoon into greased muffin
tins
and
bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: italian dinner rolls
directions: Combine dressing mix and cheese.
Thaw bread dough.
When thawed, cut into roll size pieces.
(You can make big ones or small ones.)
Brush dough with olive oil.
Roll in dry mixture.
Let rise as instructed on bread package.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Cream cheese, add other ingredients and mix.

title: hamentashen(purim fruit-filled cookie)
directions: Mix all ingredients except flour and slowly add the flour. Knead dough until smooth.
Roll out on a floured board and cut circles using a large glass or round cookie cutter.
