Put a small amount of jam or pie filling in center of circle.
Fold the edges of dough toward the center to form a triangle, leaving a bit of the filling visible in the center.
Pinch the edges to seal them. Place the hamentashen on a lightly greased foil-lined baking sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: yummy kool-aid
directions: Mix up Kool-Aid with water and sugar as directed.
Then mix in both juices.
Chill.
Serve.

title: spanish potato salad
directions: Boil cubed potatoes with peas and carrots.
Add tuna fish, hard-boiled eggs, olives, beets and shrimp.
Combine all ingredients and add enough mayonnaise to blend.
Decorate salad with remaining half can of shrimp, 1 hard-boiled egg (thinly sliced) and 2 tomatoes (sliced).

title: pinto bean cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add beaten egg.
Add beans.
Sift all dry ingredients together and add to sugar mixture.
Add apples, raisins, nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased 10-inch tube or loaf pan.
Bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: In ice cream freezer container, combine ingredients; mix well. Freeze according to manufacturer's instructions.
Return leftovers to freezer.

title: apricot coffee cake
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients. Pat out on piece of foil (dough is soft). Put apricot preserves in center of crust, then fold dough over each side to center. Place foil with dough on it on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 420° for 15 minutes (until brown).

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, sour cream and vanilla.
Sift flour with baking powder, baking soda and salt. Chill overnight.
Next day, roll into balls and then in powdered sugar.
Put on ungreased pans 2 inches apart.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from pans and roll in powdered sugar again.

title: lime float punch
directions: Stir all the ingredients together, except the sherbet, until the sugar is dissolved.
Chill.
At serving time, pour the mixture into punch bowl.
Add large spoonfuls of sherbet and stir lightly so little of sherbet melts.
Serves 12.

title: peach champagne sorbet(yields 2 quarts)
directions: Soften gelatin in water in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until gelatin is dissolved.
Combine peaches, sugar and lemon juice in large bowl.
Mix well to combine.
Place half the mixture into an electric blender and blend smooth.
Repeat with remaining 1/2 of peach mixture.
Combine gelatin mixture, champagne and all peach puree.
Turn into a metal pan.
Freeze until mushy, overnight if necessary.
Remove from freezer and beat smooth.
Refreeze until firm.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain.
Mix all ingredients together.
Fold in broccoli and put in buttered casserole.
Put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: best ever chocolate chip cookies(chewy)
directions: Cream butter and shortening; gradually add sugars, beating well at medium speed with electric mixer.
Add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to creamed mixture, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate morsels.

title: sourdough food
directions: Stir all ingredients into remaining sourdough starter and refrigerate.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour and sugar in bowl.
Beat eggs and add with oil and buttermilk.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a lightly greased "hot" bread pan.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes or until golden brown.
Bread will be soft after cooking.

title: ham and cheese muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine flour, baking powder and baking soda.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Stir into dry ingredients until just moistened.
Fill greased or paper lined muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake at 425° for 16 to 18 minutes or until done.

title: meal pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 325° for approximately 30 to 35 minutes or until set around edges.

title: tropical cooler(punch)
directions: Combine juice and ginger ale in large bowl.

title: prosphoron(bread of offering)
directions: "Prosphoron" means offering or gift.

title: sausage appetizers
directions: Drain pineapple, keeping 2 tablespoons syrup.
Combine pineapple, 2 tablespoons syrup, brown sugar, lemon juice and mustard.
Cut sausage into bite size pieces and put into mixture or marinate for 1 hour.
String several on skewers.
Broil over a few hot coals until heated.

title: flan neopolitan(mexican national dessert)
directions: You will need one 2-quart Pyrex loaf dish.

title: open-faced apple pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake in pie shell at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Quick and delicious.

title: jello salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 3/4 cups hot water.
In top of double boiler, melt marshmallows, cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Cool and mix with lime jello.
Add pineapple.
Whip cream and fold into jello mixture.
Let set until firm (overnight).
Dissolve orange jello in 2 cups hot water and pour over firm jello.
Serve.

title: white icing
directions: Put the water in medium saucepan.
Add the sugar; cook on medium heat until forms a ball in cup of cold water.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Pour water and sugar mixture into beaten egg whites.
Beat until thick.

title: pecan pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs, 1 at a time, and beat after each one. Add other ingredients and blend well. Pour in tube pan; bake 1 1/2 hours at 275°.

title: easy pork chops
directions: In 9 x 13 dish sprayed with cooking spray, arrange pork chops. In separate bowl, combine soup with water. Mix together. Pour over top of chops. Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serve with steamed rice or mashed potatoes.

title: broiled maryland crab cakes
directions: Preheat broiler to medium.
Remove shell and cartilage from crabmeat.
Blend mayonnaise, egg white, seasoning and cracker crumbs in bowl.
Add crab and fold gently.
Divide mixture into 8 equal portions.
Shape into patties.
Coat them with crumbs and refrigerate.
Heat butter and turn cakes in it to coat top and bottom.
Broil about 4 inches from flame, about 5 minutes, turning once.
Serve with additional melted butter with crackers on hamburger rolls.
This makes 2 per
person.

title: lemon gelatin pound cake
directions: Mix gelatin and cake mix well. Add oil, water and extracts; blend. Add eggs, one at a time, and mix well. Pour into a greased and floured tube pan. Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350°. Let cake cool in pan 15 minutes. Turn out and while still warm, pour on Lemon Glaze.

title: broccoli with almonds
directions: In a large saucepot, bring broccoli, water and bouillon to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 5 to 8 minutes or until broccoli is crisp-tender.
Drain and place in a serving dish; keep warm.
In a skillet, saute almonds in margarine until browned. Add onion and salt; saute until onion is tender.
Pour over broccoli; toss to coat.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: fudge krispies
directions: Melt chocolate, margarine and corn syrup.
Remove from heat. Add vanilla and sugar.
Add Rice Krispies.
Pat down in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill; cut into squares and serve.

title: bonnie's fudge
directions: Mix
sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and syrup and cook over medium heat
in
a medium saucepan until thick, about 8 to 10 minutes. Add
butter,
vanilla and nuts.
Pour into a 6 1/2 x 10 1/4-inch pan sprayed with Pam.
Cool for 4 to 5 hours.
Cut in small pieces.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries and apples through food chopper.
Add pineapple and sugar to this and stir well.
Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add cranberry mixture to Jell-O and let thicken. You can freeze this.

title: angel cornbread
directions: Combine
dry
ingredients
and mix well.
Mix eggs, oil and buttermilk and pour over dry ingredients; mix well.
Spray muffin tins
with
Pam.
Fill
each cup 3/4 full with batter. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Mix molasses with sugar and shortening.
Stir in egg.
Mix and sift flour, cream of tartar, spices and salt. Dissolve soda in boiling water and add to molasses mixture.
Stir in vanilla.
Add sifted dry ingredients all at once and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough for several hours or overnight.
Roll 1/4 inch thick and place on greased cookie sheet.
Cook in 400° oven for 10 minutes.

title: blueberry zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until light and foamy. Add oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.

Mix lightly but well. Add flour, salt, soda, spices and baking powder (all sifted). Blend well. Add nuts and berries. Use 2 (9 x 5 x 2) loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour. Makes 2 breads. Very delicious!

title: chocolate delight
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix flour, melted butter and nuts.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan or baking dish.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 minutes. Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese with confectioners sugar.
Blend and fold in 1 cup of the Cool Whip.
Spread carefully on the crust. Mix pudding according to directions on box and spread on top of Cool Whip mixture on the crust.
Spread remaining Cool Whip on top and sprinkle with rest of nuts.
Chill, cut into squares and serve.

title: chicken - no peek
directions: Sprinkle rice mix in large buttered 12 x 7 1/2-inch dish.
Mix cream soups and water.
Pour over rice mix.
Arrange chicken in dish.
Sprinkle with dry onion soup mix.
Cover dish tightly with foil.
Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Cook the box of macaroni; drain.
Brown and drain hamburger. Mix together tomato sauce, pizza sauce, tomato paste, Parmesan cheese, macaroni and hamburger.
May also add other pizza toppings, such as onions, peppers, mushrooms, etc., if desired. Put 1/2 in pan.
Cover with 1/2 the Mozzarella cheese and pepperoni.
Repeat until all is used.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: sweet dream bars
directions: Melt butter in baking pan.
Mix pecans, brown sugar, flour and soda.
Beat eggs.
Add to sugar mixture.
Pour into pan over butter.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and cool.
Cut into bars.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook chicken, cool and grate in food processor or blender. Grate all cheeses and mix together, set aside.
Heat enchilada sauce over stove.
Dip flour tortillas, one at a time, in sauce; lay in 9 x 13 glass dish.
Fill tortilla with grated chicken and cheese mix.
Roll up and place in dish.
Top enchiladas with one cup of leftover sauce. Spread rest of cheese mixture on top, top with onions.
Bake at 350 degrees for 20 minutes.
Top with salsa before serving.

title: great potato rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast and 1/4 cup sugar in 1/4 cup lukewarm water. Stir well.
Scald milk and add margarine to melt.
Stir in 1/4 cup sugar and 1 teaspoon salt.
While hot, add potato flakes.
Stir well, then add 1/2 cup cold water and beaten eggs.
When milk mixture is lukewarm, add yeast mixture.
Stir in flour until dough is fairly stiff.
Cover.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour. Knead dough on floured surface.
Roll out to about 1/2-inch thick. Cut with cutter.
Let rise until double, about 1 hour.
Bake at 450° for about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce for pork chops
directions: Dip pork chops in beaten egg, then in flour.
Quick-fry both sides.
Mix remaining ingredients together and cook for 10 minutes.
Pour sauce over pork chops in electric skillet and simmer for 30 to 45 minutes.
Messy, but good!

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix together.
Makes two 5 x 9 pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350° in greased pans.

title: zucchini squares(40 appetizer pieces)
directions: Mix well and pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cut into small squares and serve.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed, except bacon, into a 4 quart bowl. Cover and refrigerator overnight.
Just before serving, top of with bacon and toss.

title: mexican quiche
directions: Grease 9 x 13 dish.
Spread out crescent rolls in greased dish to make the bottom crust.
Pour well-beaten eggs over dough.
Top with sausage.
Sprinkle green chilies over the sausage and top with grated cheese.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 375°.

title: potato salad
directions: Cut potatoes in rather large squares.
Boil until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Mix all ingredients together and add the salad dressing.
Be careful not to overcook or mash the potatoes while mixing.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: ole south muffins
directions: Add together all dry ingredients.
Work in butter, eggs and milk.
Mix well.
Pour into greased muffin pan.
Bake at 350° to 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add vanilla coloring.
Add eggs and cream well.
Sift and measure flour and cocoa.
Sift 3 times.
Add to mixture alternately with milk.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch cake pan; bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Ice with following icing when cool.

title: italian dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients in a jar with a tight fitting lid. Shake and chill.
Shake well before each use.

title: sue meacham's fruity popcorn
directions: Pop corn and drizzle butter over corn.
Toss to coat.
Mix with gelatin or Kool-Aid mix.
Spread in 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake in preheated 350° oven, stirring twice, for 3 to 5 minutes to set coating.
Cool thoroughly; pack in airtight containers.

title: fammie's apple pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spoon applesauce in buttered baking dish.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add the beaten egg.
Add milk and vanilla.

title: turtles(excellent gift for chocolate lovers!)
directions: Melt the caramels in a heavy pan while stirring constantly. Add milk and stir thoroughly.
Add pecans and stir thoroughly. Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Chill well (15 to 30 minutes). Melt Hershey bar, chocolate square and paraffin together.
Dip chilled caramel spoonfuls into melted chocolate mixture.
Place on waxed paper.
Chill.
Store in airtight container.

title: rotel soup
directions: Heat slowly and serve.

title: cajun duck
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine the flour, paprika, creole seasoning, sugar and accent.
Add chicken broth; stir until blended.
Salt and pepper ducks to taste.
Place four bay leaves in each cavity.
Place ducks breast down in a dutch oven; cover with broth mixture.
Bake covered for 2 1/2 hours or until tender.
Debone ducks and serve with gravy over rice.

title: homemade double crust pastry
directions: Put flour and salt in a medium bowl. Cut shortening into small pieces and add to flour and salt. Sprinkle water over the mixture and gently toss with a fork. Form into 2 balls.

title: mexicali skillet
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook onion until tender, but not brown. Cut up tomatoes.
Add undrained tomatoes, undrained beans, chili peppers, water and uncooked rice to skillet.
Stir in chili powder.

title: chicken and dressing casserole
directions: Use 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: berry granita
directions: In a small saucepan, combine the water and sugar.
Bring to a simmer over medium heat; cook until the sugar is dissolved.
Let cool slightly, then refrigerate until cold.
In a food processor, puree the berries.
Add the sugar syrup and orange and lemon slices; pulse to blend.
Pour the mixture into a chilled 12 x 2-inch metal pan.
Freeze for 30 minutes, or until ice crystals form around the edges.
Stir the ice crystals into the center of the mixture.
Return the pan to the freezer; stir every 30 minutes until all of the liquid is frozen, approximately 2 to 2 1/2 hours. Put in fruit cups; garnish with fresh berries.

title: hillbilly stew
directions: Season all meat with spices of your choice.
Cook until done. While meat is cooking, get vegetables ready.
When cleaned and cut, put them in a large pan and cook them until almost done. Then put in your meat.
Cook about 30 minutes more.
Then you have your stew.

title: chunky italian appetizer
directions: About 1 hour before serving, cube cheese and quarter tomatoes. Put cheese and tomatoes in large salad bowl and toss with dressing.
Cover and refrigerate about 1 hour.
Serve with crackers.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together sugar and flour. Beat in eggs, milk, vanilla and butter. Fold in nuts. Pour into 9 inch deep pastry shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta, salt, oil and garlic in boiling water until pasta is done.
Dice bell pepper, onion, olives and tomatoes in large bowl.
When pasta is done, drain.
Remove garlic bud and add pasta to bowl.
Pour in dressing and mix well.
Chill before serving. Enjoy.

title: banana pudding cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend well.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes, then remove from pan.

title: jello salad
directions: Add jello and tapioca to water.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add oranges, pineapple and whipped Dream Whip.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours before serving.

title: mustard-pepper chicken with herb sauce
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon butter in heavy large skillet over medium heat.
Add shallots, mushrooms and 1 teaspoon pepper and saute until vegetables brown, about 8 minutes.
Add wine and bring to boil.
Add rosemary and thyme sprigs and simmer 5 minutes.
Add stock; increase heat to medium-high and boil until liquid is reduced to 3/4 cup, about 20 minutes.
Strain into saucepan. (Sauce can be made 1 day ahead.
Cover and refrigerate.)
Prepare barbecue (medium-high heat) or preheat broiler.
Sprinkle remaining 4 teaspoons pepper over both sides of chicken.
Grill chicken until cooked through, about 5 minutes per side.
Transfer to baking sheet.
Preheat broiler.
Brush mustard over chicken. Sprinkle with mustard seed.
Broil until brown, about 2 minutes.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese and dry jello.
Fold in whipped cream or Cool Whip, nuts, coconut and crushed pineapple.
Chill at least 2 hours until firm.
Can use low-fat cottage cheese.

title: rainbow salad(patience salad)
directions: Use 1 1/4 cups water and bring to boiling for each flavor of jello.
Save 1/3 cup jello and put into a small bowl.
When cool, add 1/3 cup sour cream and beat.
Put clear cherry jello in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Harden and add sour cream mixture. Harden and continue until all flavors are finished.
Finish with the strawberry flavor that has no sour cream added to it. You will end up with 11 very thin layers of jello.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Mix water, oil, salt, vinegar, sugar and pepper.
Heat to boiling, then set aside to cool.
Mix all vegetables.
Pour liquid mixture over.
Put in covered container and refrigerate at least 12 hours.
Keeps well.

title: poor boy steak
directions: Sprinkle 1/4 cup flour and 1/2 teaspoon salt in an 8-inch baking pan.
Place raw ground beef over the flour and salt. Flatten the meat by patting or with rolling pin.
Sprinkle the remaining flour and salt on top of the meat.
Roll or pat lightly until the meat covers the pan evenly and the flour and salt have been absorbed.
Cut the meat into 6 steaks.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Drain steaks and place in a baking pan.
Prepare brown gravy.
Pour gravy over steaks, cover pan and bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Drain green beans, place in casserole dish.
Add cream of mushroom soup.
Mix together.
Slightly toast almonds and add. Spread onion rings on top and heat in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: easy key lime pie
directions: Combine the milk, whipped topping and Key lime juice.
Pour mixture into pie crust.
Refrigerate 1 hour.

title: dirty rice
directions: Mix all together and
bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or 1 hour.

title: ham and three cheeses egg puffs
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs.
Beat in flour and baking powder. Add milk, beating until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Turn in 2-quart greased baking dish or 9 x 9-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: three bean salad
directions: Rinse and drain all beans.
Mix
vegetables in large plastic container; add salt and pepper.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly; pour over all vegetables.
Do not stir.
Put tight lid on container. Refrigerate and toss occasionally (much better after 3 days of refrigeration).

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixing bowl.
When mixed well, put into salad bowl.
Sprinkle with a few pecans; let set overnight in refrigerator to chill.

title: hidden valley ranch potato salad
directions: Cut slightly cooled potatoes into cubes.
Combine potatoes, onions and salad dressing; toss gently.
Dust with paprika. Garnish with chives.
Serve warm or at room temperature.

title: stavanger lefsa
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients together and cook, stirring constantly.
Pour immediately over the 4 1/2 cups flour in a bowl. Mix well and place single fold of a towel over bowl while it is cooling.

When cool, put 1/3 of the dough on floured board and add more flour as it is kneaded into a rather large hard dough and can be rolled out. Break off into 8 pieces and roll out very thin. Keep flipping it over as you roll and keep it floured on both sides.
Use a lefsa stick to turn them.
Place on a 400° griddle and dry one side but do not brown.
After they are all dried on one side, take each one and put Goop on and rub by hand round and round until smooth.
(Keep off edges or they will stick to your grill.) This is all done on the floured side.
Now put the "ungooped" side on the grill and dry it and then turn and "brown spot" the gooped side.
These will become hard when stored so run water over them before serving.
Place between cloth or towel until soft; spread the "unspotted" side with butter and sugar. Fold over and cut each into 4 pieces, folding once more.

title: tangy french bread
directions: Brush both sides of bread with dressing.
Top with cheese and basil.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes or until cheese melts.
Cut into 2-inch slices.
Serve hot. Makes 16 servings.

title: rice cream gravy for chicken
directions: Pour drippings into a 4 cup measure.
Microwave on High for 1 to 2 minutes or until hot.
Stir in flour, poultry seasoning, salt and pepper until well blended.
Slowly blend in milk and cream. Microwave on High for 5 to 8 minutes until thickened.
Serve with Oven-Baked Chicken.
Yield:
2 cups gravy.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on box; drain.
Add soup and mayonnaise; mix well.
Add eggs, onion and cheese; mix well.
Pour into a 2 or 2 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with bread or cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered chip dip
directions: First Layer:
Mix beans with 1/2 package of taco seasoning.

title: pumpkin nut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Mix pumpkin, sugar, milk and eggs.
Add the dry ingredients and butter.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour in well-greased pan (9 x 9 x 3-inch) loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: stuffed hard rolls
directions: Slice hard rolls in half, scoop out centers.
Spoon mixture into rolls.
Wrap individually in foil. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields about 12.

title: chicken cashew casserole
directions: Saute the onion and celery in the butter.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Simmer the mixture for a few minutes, then pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Before browning in the oven, add 1 can chow mein noodles and 1/2 cup cashews.
Bake in a 350° oven about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: punch
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and sugar with 6 cups of boiling water.
In blender, add bananas and juices.
Mix all ingredients together and pour into two separate plastic bags to freeze.
Mix 1/2 batch frozen juice with a 2 liter of 7-Up and pour into large punch bowl.

title: beef stew
directions: In a large pot or Dutch oven, cook bacon until light brown. Combine flour and pepper in a bowl.
Dip meat in this mixture to coat.
Brown in the bacon fat, turning often.
Add a little vegetable oil, if necessary.
Add onion and garlic; cook until brown.
Add tomato sauce, broth, bay leaf and thyme.
Cover and cook slowly for about 1 1/2 hours.
Add carrots, celery and potatoes; cook, covered, another 1/2 hour or until vegetables are tender.

title: sausage stuffed french bread
directions: Cook sausage until pink is gone.
Add onion and celery. Cook until tender
and
sausage is brown.
Slice bread lengthwise and remove
insides
to
form
a
shell.
Combine
pulled bread, seasonings	and
cooked
sausage mixture.
Add eggs and milk; toss with
stuffing
to	mix well.
Mound onto halves of bread shell and
brush	with melted butter.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake in	a 400° oven for 20 minutes.
Remove and add grated cheese; return
to	oven for 5 minutes, or until cheese is	melted. Remove
and
place	halves	together.
Slice
and serve.

title: chicken lasagna roll-ups(great for little helping hands!)
directions: Bake chicken breasts 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and shred. Combine Ricotta cheese, egg and parsley flakes; mix well.
Stir in shredded chicken.
Cut noodles in half, crosswise.
Spread about 1/4 cup of chicken mixture on each noodle.
Roll gently.
Place rolls, seams down, in lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with spaghetti sauce.
Bake, covered, 30 minutes at 350°.
Uncover, sprinkle with cheese and bake 5 minutes more until melted.

title: hamburger cheese bake
directions: Cook noodles by package directions and drain.
Brown beef with salt, pepper, onion, green pepper and garlic salt.
Stir in tomato sauce and oregano.
Set aside.

title: poor man's chocolate cake
directions: Sift the first 5 ingredients together in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch greased cake pan.
Add the oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Pour in the water; mix thoroughly with fork.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: 6 weeks slaw
directions: Combine cabbage, green pepper, celery, carrots and onion and cover with 2 cups water and salt.
Let stand 1 hour.

title: microwave potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes and onion in casserole.
Add bouillon.
If desired, dot with butter. Cook on high 10 minutes, covered. Stir.
Cook 7 minutes on high, covered.
Uncover and sprinkle with cheese and parsley.
Cook 1/2 minute or until cheese melts.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients. Add apples and mix. Combine flour, spice and soda. Mix with other. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms and remove stems.
Chop up stems and saute in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Stir in stuffing, chicken broth and garlic salt.
Stuff mushrooms with mixture and place in a Pyrex pie plate with 2 tablespoons margarine.

title: baked chicken
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Dip chicken breasts in butter and coat with dry mixture well.
Place chicken on rimmed cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until juices run clear when pierced with a fork.
Do not overcook chicken or it will become dry.

title: good basic corn bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients into mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat until fairly smooth, about 1 minute. Bake in greased 8-inch square pan.
Bake in preheated oven at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: low-fat potato chicken casserole
directions: Cook potatoes until 2/3 done; barely cover with water to cook. Saute chicken in nonstick frypan sprayed lightly with Pam.
Cook until done, adding onion and celery last stage of cooking.
Add to potatoes; add also spices and cheese.
Mix milk and cornstarch together; add to rest of mixture.
Bring slowly to a boil.
Place in casserole dish; sprinkle with turmeric.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream butter flavor Crisco and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each egg.
Add sour cream and mix.
Add salt and baking powder to flour, then mix with cream mixture.
Add vanilla.
Pour batter into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: texas beef loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Pack in a baking dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let set for several minutes before slicing.

title: sausage skillet
directions: Cut sausage into bite-size pieces.
Saute sausage and onion in skillet until onion is tender.
Add vegetables, cover and simmer, stirring frequently until vegetables are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: spinach salad dressing
directions: Put ingredients in jar and shake.
Pour over spinach, water chestnuts, bean sprouts and onions.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Line 9 x 13-inch pan with graham cracker squares.
Beat pudding with 2 to 2 1/2 cups of milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour over crackers.
Over pudding, lay a layer of graham cracker squares.
Chill overnight.
Next morning, frost with chocolate frosting.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Mix the above, using enough juice to mix all ingredients together.
Run hot tap water over cabbage to soften, then roll meat mixture and wrap in cabbage leaves.
Pour rest of the juice over cabbage rolls and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Baste occasionally.

title: chocolate squares
directions: In saucepan on stove top, empty cake mix, pudding mix and 2 cups milk; heat and stir until boiling starts.
Pour at once into 9 x 12-inch baking pan. Sprinkle with chocolate chips and walnuts. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool on wire rack and cut into squares.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, lemon juice and salt in blender.
Blend well.
Pour melted butter in blender.
Blend well, at least 5 to 7 minutes.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, then at 375° until done.
This makes one deep dish pie or 2 smaller ones.

title: diabetic's candy
directions: Blend the first 4 ingredients, then add the other ingredients. Form into balls or in 1 bar shaped piece.
Has 147 calories.

title: sherried beef
directions: Heat soup.
Add sherry and dry soup mix.
Pour over beef cubes in a large casserole.
Cover.
Bake 3 hours at 325°.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: apple pie
directions: Put in crust.
Dot with butter and add top crust.
Bake 20 minutes at 425° and 40 minutes at 400°.
It will be done when bubbles in the center.

title: country southern fried chicken
directions: Wash chicken; pat dry.
Then add your seasoning which is one tablespoon seasoning salt, 1 tablespoon black pepper and 1 teaspoon Accent.
Then use sweet milk and eggs; beat it together and let it drip for a few minutes.
Then batter with flour.
Let your grease get hot, then after it begins frying, turn the stove down to medium heat and don't turn until one side is completely brown.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Combine soups, tomatoes and broth.
Add onion and blend well. Layer tortillas and chicken pieces, pouring soup mixture and cheese over each layer.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheese soup
directions: Cook carrots and onions in butter until tender.
Add flour and blend in smoothly.
Stir in milk and beer.
Cook, stirring over medium heat until liquid comes to boiling and is thickened.
Add cheese and seasonings, stirring until melted.
Best if doubled.

title: lasagna(easy)
directions: Cook meat, onion and garlic.
Drain.
Add spices, tomatoes and paste.
Cover and simmer 40 minutes.
Cook noodles and drain. Alternate - start with sauce, then noodles and layer, end with sauce.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: no cook pink champagne frosting
directions: Beat salt and egg whites until mixture forms soft peaks.
Add sugar slowly, beating until smooth and glossy.
Add Karo syrup while beating.
Add syrup a little at a time.
Beat after each addition of syrup until frosting peaks.
Fold in vanilla and coloring.
Frosts top and sides of two 9-inch layers.

title: sticky buns
directions: Cover the bottom of a greased Bundt pan with nuts.
Place the frozen rolls over the nuts in the pan.
Sprinkle the pudding over the rolls.
Cover with plastic wrap and let stand overnight.
(If refrigerated, leave out at room temperature about 1 hour before baking.)
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chicken frittata
directions: Fry chicken breasts in heavy skillet with oil until almost done.
Add the sliced onions and cook until onions are clear.
Add the canned tomatoes and potatoes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook over low heat until the potatoes are just crisp. Serve over rice.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix together; let stand overnight.
Put in favorite bread. Take out middle of bread to use as a bowl for dip.
Break remaining bread from middle into pieces.

title: potato chip chicken
directions: Melt margarine. Dip chicken breasts in melted margarine. Press into crushed potato chips; both sides of chicken. Place in 8 x 11 baking dish. Mix the soup and milk and pour over the chicken. Bake at 350°, covered, for 1 hour. Then uncover and bake for 15 more minutes.

title: coconut chess pie
directions: Beat sugar, margarine and eggs together until well mixed.
Add vanilla and coconut.
Put into unbaked pie crust and bake at 325° for about 45 minutes or until firm.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Using solid shortening or margarine, grease and flour 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Boil water and add rice. Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Add dry noodles. Cover and simmer. Brown sausage and cut into small pieces. Remove from pan. Drain most of the grease, leaving some to saute pepper, celery and onion.
Mix vegetables, rice and sausage. Put in casserole dish.
Top with salted nuts.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: toddler's warm milk
directions: Pour milk into a bottle.
Microwave for 1 minute on High. Lightly stir.
Place on nipple and serve.

title: finger jello
directions: In large bowl mix unflavored gelatin with flavored gelatin. Add boiling water.
Stir until dissolved.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking pan and chill until firm.
To serve, cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 9 dozen.

title: frozen delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together and press in a 10-inch pie dish. Bake at 350° until brown (8 to 10 minutes).

title: chocolate cake
directions: Sift flour.
Combine with sugar and set aside.
Put the next 4 ingredients together in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over sugar/flour mixture; mix well.
Add eggs, buttermilk, cinnamon, soda and vanilla.
Beat well.
Bake in 10 3/4-inch wide, 1-inch deep and 16-inch long pan for 20 minutes at 400°.
Spread with Icing for Chocolate Cake from this same book.
Sprinkle nuts over top, if desired.

title: salmon ball
directions: Mix well.
Form into a ball.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Roll in chopped nuts.
Serve with crackers.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack firmly into loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before slicing.
Makes 8 servings.
tags: cream of mushroom dry soup mix

title: oven fried fish
directions: Season fish well with seasonings at least 1 hour before.
Dip fish in milk, then crumbs.
Place in well-greased baking pan; season.
Drizzle oleo over fish and bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown sausage until crumbly; drain.
Add beans and other ingredients.
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Let stand about 30 minutes to let juices combine.

title: apple butter
directions: Cook apples until soft and put through a sieve, add ingredients and put in oven.
Bake 3 hours at 350°, stir occasionally.
Pour in hot jars and seal.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix together in blender.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch pie pan. Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken 'n rice
directions: In large buttered casserole dish, place 1 cup rice and package of dried onion soup.
In another pot, bring to a boil 2 1/2 cups water, 1 can cream of mushroom soup and 3 chicken bouillon cubes. Pour over rice and dry soup mix.
Add chicken pieces on top and dot with margarine chunks.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: banana split cake
directions: Mix melted butter and crushed graham crackers.

Pat into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Do not bake. Beat the eggs, butter and powdered sugar with electric mixer for 15 minutes. Spread over graham cracker crust. Cover with the bananas, then spread the drained pineapple.
Cover with the Cool Whip.
Sprinkle chopped pecans and cherries on top.

title: sweetened condensed milk
directions: Put all the ingredients in a blender and blend until smooth.

title: candied yams
directions: Pare yams and quarter.
Place in boiling water and cook until soft.
Remove with skimmer.
Place in pans and pour melted butter over yams.
Sprinkle with cinnamon, nutmeg and top with sugar. Then cook with syrup.
Bake for 20 minutes in convection oven.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: I use
a
combination of different colored bell peppers if you don't want to use the pimento.

title: margaret's chocolate chess pie
directions: Mix all the ingredients, pour into pie shell and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serve slightly warm.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Put noodles in bowl.
Pour in dressing, tomatoes, olives, cucumbers, onion and Salad Supreme; cover.
Put in refrigerator and let chill.

title: spanish-style couscous
directions: Slow cooker directions (crockpot):
Heat skillet over high heat until hot.
Add beef; cook until browned.
Pour off fat.
Place broth, bell pepper, olives, onion, garlic, cumin, thyme and beef in slow cooker.
Cover and cook on LOW 4 hours or until bell pepper is tender bring water to a boil over high heat in small saucepan. Stir in couscous.
Cover; remove from heat.
Let stand 5 minutes; fluff with fork.
Spoon couscous onto plates; top with beef mixture.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pineapple right side-up cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool.

title: copper penny salad
directions: Cook carrots until just tender.
Combine all other ingredients and cover the vegetables.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours to marinate.

title: salmon cakes
directions: Mix ingredients (with hands).
Make into patties or balls. Fry in small amount of oil until browned.
Don't overcook.

title: pistachio ambrosia
directions: In large bowl, mix both pineapple and sprinkle pudding on top. Gently mix and let stand 3 minutes.
Combine nuts and coconut and fold into mixture.
Fold in whipped topping and marshmallows. Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: heavenly ham salad
directions: Cook shells; drain.
Combine all ingredients together and toss dressing with salad mixture.
Serve immediately or cover and chill.

title: favorite company chicken
directions: Cooking Time: 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.
Servings: 4.

title: green bean salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion; drain and then add garlic, tomato paste, tomato sauce, salt and pepper. Simmer for a few minutes. Cook the noodles in boiling saltwater until tender and drain. Combine the egg, cottage cheese and 1 teaspoon salt; mix well. Layer in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan 1/2 of the noodles, 1/2 of the meat sauce, 1/2 of the cottage cheese, 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese and 1/2 of the Parmesan. Repeat the layers. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Let stand for 15 minutes before serving. Cover tightly with foil before baking; this prevents drying out.

title: hamburger bean casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Cook sugar, cocoa, milk, oleo and Karo syrup over medium heat. Bring to a full boil.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes.
Take off burner and add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Stir for a minute or two; drop on foil by spoonfuls.
Let harden, then eat.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix in mixer or blender.
Makes 1 cup.
Use apple wedges for dipping.
Store in fridge.

title: white salad
directions: Melt marshmallows with milk.
Add cream cheese.
Stir until melted.
Cool.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese.
Fold in whipped topping.
Refrigerate.
I decorate with cherries.

title: corn and rice casserole
directions: Brown chopped onion in butter.
Add corn, bell pepper and pimientos.
Prepare rice as directed on box.
Add rice to corn; stir in 1 egg, sugar, salt and pepper.
Top with grated cheese. Place in a 300° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: barbecue shrimp
directions: Dehead and wash shrimp well.
In a 9 x 13 pan, put in shrimp and the rest of ingredients.
Cover with foil and bake at 400° for about 1 hour, until backs lift off the shrimp.
Check every 15 minutes.
Shrimp will make water.
Eat with French bread.
